name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: This place is absolutely outstanding. It was a birthday dinner for my boyfriend and it definitely did not disappoint. The food from start to finish was immaculate, flavors were to die for and fab cocktails too. The service from the moment we walked in was great, as soon as we were through the door there was someone greeting us. The attention and care for their customer service was top quality, they even helped me organize a birthday dessert for him at the end. Highly recommend for a special occasion, with the price range it wouldn't suit a standard date night (for most people).

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Excellent dinner experience in the city center of Dublin. Book in advance is recommended. You can have the three course meal for a fixed price or a la carte. Highly recommended to take a look at the fine choice of aged meats. Varied and diverse choice of wines

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Outstanding from start to finish!

Enjoyed a wonderful evening at Fire.

Service was top notch in the bar and at our table.

Food was beautifully cooked and presentation was superb.

We opted for the 3 course set menu which offered really good value all round. Some of the dishes carry a supplement (the prawns amd the rib eye steak) but they are worth choosing if you like these!

If you like cauliflower then the side order of cauliflower is a must!!

Two cocktails were equally beautiful.

We sat on the terrace and the view of Dawson St as the evening closed in was wonderful.

We look forward to our next visit soon! Thanks to everyone there for a memorable time!

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Called in on a Saturday without a booking with my daughter. We were accommodated and brought to a terrace table. View was great and staff were excellent. My daughter who can be a tad fussy was thrilled with her food even though it was on a kids menu it looked like a grown up lunch. The food was fresh and tasty toilets were spotless and staff were brilliant. Thank you for making our day

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: We went today for lunch, food was amazing! The place is incredible and the serve was really good. Alex (from Greece) served us and he was very very attentive, very good looking at other tables, he said is new but he looked very calm and confident, definitely this is our new fav restaurant

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Such a great experience and the food was of course, outstanding. The building itself was beautiful, a great setting and the inside exactly the same, creating a vibrant yet sophisticated atmosphere.
All our food was exceptional and the service matched at every point from the moment you walk in. Very tentative. Unfortunately towards the end of the night, this did die off with staff members finishing their shifts and we had to wait a long time for someone to ask and then indeed follow up on the dessert order and the bill.
However I was pleasantly surprised when two small complimentary puddings were delivered for two members of the party who we‚Äôre celebrating their birthday. Great little touch.
Price is hight but not extortionate for a restaurant of this quality. You get what you pay for.
Overall a must if your visiting this fantastic city.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Amazing place. Since the receptionists who receive me whit large smiles to the waiter who help us and guided to order the best plate. My special thanks to Leonardo Bueno. This guy pay attention in each request from our small group and make this meal very special to us.
The food was tasty and delicious, we ate shrimp as entrance that surprise me. As dessert, the lemmon sorbet was perfect whit the irish coffe.
In a luxury saloon, you can spend some time being happy. This will be a great memory about a day that the place will be an essential part and i will really plan to comeback in my next visit to Dublin.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: My husband and I dined here this evening. I have always wanted to try it, and I'm so glad that we were able to go this evening! Our table was booked for 17:30 and, while there weren't many full tables at that time, there was still some great vibes and atmosphere. Food was amazing - we ordered from the ‚Ç¨60 set menu + ‚Ç¨15 surcharge for my husband's steak. Food was cooked really well, extremely tasty, and portions were deceivingly generous. Service was impeccable; formal but I really liked that. Our waiter was absolutely fantastic. Tables were large, and plenty of room between tables so you could have a private conversation with ease. As soon as I walked in the door, I felt like I was in an experience. I would absolutely dine here again.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Great food and very good service. It's one like higher Level on the average in Dublin.

We were 6 people with a baby. We have the Saturday menu of 40‚Ç¨ with 3 plates, starter, main and dessert. +15‚Ç¨ for the Rib Eye but it's worth it.

The service are aware of you and taking care of you and that you are not missing anything.

The place beautiful.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Beautiful restaurant with stellar service and excellent food. We came for dinner on a Thursday with a reservation we made the day before. We ordered the 3 course early bird special, which is a great deal considering the fantastic quality of the food.

Service: Our waiters were attentive and nice, and they gave us some good recommendations from the menu.

Food: We ordered the chicken caesar salad, Connemara rock oysters, prime sirloin center cut, wood-fired tiger prawns, chocolate fromboise, and Irish cheeseboard. All of them were delicious and served fresh, and the portions were big! The oysters were particularly excellent.

Drinks: We got the Noperol Spritz and Mango Caipirinha. They were both refreshing and a great complement to the meal.

Ambience: The restaurant is in a prime location right beside Grafton street and St. Stephen's Green. It is enormous and spacious, with a beautiful garden and fountain at the front. The inside is very chic and elegant, perfect for a special occasion.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: This is one of the best restaurant i have visited in dublin üòÑ. Till now ivy was my favorite restaurant for customization and service but Fire steak house and bar exceeded the expectations. The ambience is excellent and food is outstanding üëå when you enter you are taken care in a very royal way. The waiters are very professional and take outstanding care of all the guests üòÄ For vegetarian people also there are 2 steaks available cauliflower and beet steak. I prefer cauliflower steak and it was just delicious üòã. They have a 60 euro 3 course meal dinner menu which is amazing. The breads üçû served are remarkable and butter they give is just out of the world üåé. There is also an piano üéπ at entrance and they have 2 bar ine at bottom floor and one at upper floor. They also have party halls with capacity of 14 people with complete privacy and excellent seating üí∫ for birthdays, corporate parties and events. The staff is extremely polite and always does their best to make you happy üòä. If you or your friend has birthday they also give a small pastry with happy birthday written on the plate. At upper floor there are 2 seating areas one is inside and one is outside with heaters. I prefer outside area more and it was amazing experience. All my friends have said this was the best steak they had in their life till now. They also have a early bird menu where in 35 euro there is 2 course meal and in 40 euro there is 3 course meal. This is a must visit place in dublin and food is exceptionally great. This restaurant is located at a very premium location and there are amazing bars near it. üòã

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: We dined at Fire on a Monday and it was fantastic from start to finish. From being first welcomed in and offered drinks in the bar, the friendly service, ambiance, beautiful setting and quality continued all evening. The food was excellent- highly recommend the sea bream. Don‚Äôt expect this to be cheap - but you get what you pay for.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Amazing meal experience - ambiance, service, and meal. We had the early bird set menu. Bone marrow and Oysters for starters, Prawns for the Mains (inclusive of either salad or chips as sides), and additional cauliflower as sides.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Interior is beautiful, so spaces. Good food and vino selection. Staff extremely nice

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Fire offers a fantastic dining experience in the heart of Dublin city centre. It transforms the classic steakhouse into a fancy lively restaurant creating an immersive experience. The restaurant itself is a villa with its own garden and beautiful fountain, whats unique about it is that its surrounded by old buildings. The three course meal is well worth the price, and the food is beyond exceptional. However, service could be improved as you shouldn‚Äôt have to wave to order at such an expensive restaurant nor should dirty dishes pile up during the dining experience. Otherwise the restaurant is excellent, highly recommended for fancy dates and special occasions.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Splendid place, classy and tasteful. Goat cheese (starter) and rib-eye (main) were really delicious. The chocolate framboise at the final was also great.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
I‚Äôve been coming for years for especially for birthdays and it never disappoints .
So many things to say about this place and all positive , food amazing and service it top class
. Our waiter was great ‚Äú Danielle ‚Äú The atmosphere is buzzing
I‚Äôd come here for a special occasion since prices are on the higher end but it‚Äôs worth it. Well worth it !  The cocktails were great and wine !  as well but we were blown away by the food that was served! Thanks to Maria for helping to arrange our special birthday meal !

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: What a memorable night! So many great things to say about this place but right off the bad, I‚Äôd highly recommend coming here. Our waiter was great and offered us some great dishes to choose from. The vibe is spectacular inside and really makes it feel like an experience. The oysters were delicious and the steak was so juicy. I‚Äôd come here for a special occasion since prices are on the higher end but it‚Äôs worth it. The cocktails were great as well but we were blown away by the food that was served!

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Food is very nice. I was expecting less food in the plate and I was totally full! We had a very nice gentleman Who was serving the bread (spanish speaker) that was very kind with us.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: The food was pretty but lacked flavor, and my King Prawns  dish was overcooked and dry.  The service was lousy, and the way they serve bread is less than desirable....The steak was nice, but thats about it...I will not eat here again.... NOT WORTH THE MONEY.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: I was there last night. Came with my family for Mother‚Äôs Day. We booked a table for 12. Our table was for 8:00pm and as soon as we got there the reception said. ‚ÄúThe kitchen is closing at 8:15pm‚Äù this was a response to me telling her that my parents where on the way, they were just parking the car and they would be here in less than 5 minutes. She made us all feel very uncomfortable. However the waiters were nice and so was the manager. But how you get treated at the door plays a big impact on the night. Food was good. I am giving it 2 star because choosing the right staff is extremely important. It played a big impact on our evening.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Food was absolutely amazing, full of flavor, well prepared and cooked. Presentation of food was inviting and decor warm and intimate making for a great date or private family dinner. The only improvement that could be made would have to be to the service as coats were not taken until later after arriving, was given a glass that wasn't completely clean and staff knowledge of menu and wines could be improved. However a wonderful overall experience!

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
We got a booking on valentines night.. the food was absolutely fantastic ! Highly recommend !
Amazing staff - lovely atmosphere...

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Friendly service! Food and cocktails were amazing!! Relaxing ambience.. You guys made our day with this cute surprise on the dessert plate, evening well spent..! üòãüòã
owner_answer:
Dear Guest,

Thank you for taking the time to leave this kind review.

I am delighted to see you enjoyed all aspects of your recent al fresco dining experience.

I will be sure to pass your kind words on to our entire team here at Fire.

Kind regards,
Nicole Jordan
General Manager

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Came here with my husband to celebrate our 2 year anniversary and couldn‚Äôt have been more happy with his choice for this date.
The food is espetacular! It was the best steak I‚Äôve ever had!
The staff is beyond friendly and polite: we casually told the hostess that brought us to our table that it was our anniversary (when she asked how was our night going). They prepared us a little dessert that I found a nice gesture.
The place is very nice, make sure to dress up!
Really recommend it and can‚Äôt wait to go there again

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Great place for early dinner, delicious food, friendly staff, lovely atmosphere.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: One of my favorite places, honestly, if you have a special day. The staff are lovely, the place is sophisticated, the food is delicious (so much that I forgot to click dessert xD) with good portions, a solid drinks menu - unlikely that I wouldn't go back ‚ù§Ô∏è

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Steakhouse located in the heart of Dublin. They currently only have their Christmas menus.

We went for the 3 course lunch meal for ‚Ç¨52.  I went for the goats cheese to start which was quite nice. The cheese had a moussey texture which was unexpected but quite nice. The sirloin was delicious for the main course and I had a chocolate bar cake to finish which was delightful.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: The dining environment with friends before Christmas can still have a festive atmosphere, but there are many people. When ordering, the waiter misheard my steak and gave it medium rare... (I ordered  medium well).  Waiter  change another steak for me, But my friends have already finished eating when my steak coming  üò≥About 100 euros per person, the Christmas set meal we eat

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Absolutely amazing experience with my husband. Definitely recommend this place to everyone. The food was delicious! And service was perfect. Many thanks to our server for making our romantic date night dinner so special.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
The most friendly and fantastic staff ever. This place is pretty fancy from a humble craigavon mans point of view but they made me and my now fianc√© feel right at home. I told the waiters which if he see this, we were the guy with the pony tail and the lady with pink hair, we‚Äôll call them D and A for now but when I told them my plan to prepose they were all for it, all the staff joined in on filming it and a huge round of applause ‚ù§Ô∏è

They even offered us champagne and a little desert on the house as a congrats. Nothing but praise for the staff and we haven‚Äôt even reached the food! OMG THE FOOD! I had the Christmas 3 courses starting with the Butternut Squash Soup 9/10 tasted fantastic but nothing new, then the Turkey‚Ä¶ it was an absolute 10/10 it was wrapped in bacon cooked perfectly with delicious mash and cabbage with bacon, desert was the Gateaux which I think was a 8/10 but I‚Äôm not a big coffee guy but it was my fault for seeing Gateaux and jumping on it honestly everything together was 10/10 the service alone‚Ä¶ Perfection!

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Our food was delicious and the atmosphere was lovely. A bit pricey, but definitely worth the money!

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: The food was very good. Tried the dried and Hereford steak which turned out just as good as expected. Salad on the side was just perfect with the meat, and I actually would preferred the dish without sauce. Cosy and modern interior and really nice service.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Went for my wife's birthday, food was good enough but not worth it, portion size very poor. All round very expensive and ‚Ç¨5.50 for water. 4 steak with a very small side and 6 drinks ‚Ç¨225

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
After weeks trying to book with them I finally was able to book for 12 people, as they are extremely busy.

First problem was that they put 12 of us on a table that was for 8 people, so it was extremely uncomfortable. I rang them in advance and specifically told them that we would need more space, as there are some big guys in our group. Well apparently they didn't care.

The place looks excellent but the food is not worth it the 60 euro for the fixed menu. Prawns were good, but the meat and the dessert were not good at all.

Our waitress, a Mexican girl, was charming and super professional. Also the bathrooms were terrific.

I'm short, 3 points over 5. One for the prawns, another one for the bathroom and a star for our waitress.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: One of the good restaurants to visit in Dublin. The steaks were excellent. It‚Äôs a great venue for hosting events as well. There were 50 of us in one section of the restaurant. The location is easy to get to and it has a nice compound. The restaurant on level 2 overlooks the garden. We had several other dishes besides steak. Mostly good. No complaints.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Ambiance: 4/5
Food quality: 3/5
Friendliness: 2/5
Vegan and vegetarian options: 1/5
Service: 3/5
Taste: 4/5

The only vegetarian main course option available was cauliflower steak, which wasn't too bad but there should be more options available.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
I love Fire. That's the first thing I have to say if anyone ask me what do I think about this restaurant.

First of all, I love meat and second, I love a good place that serves a nice steak, wine and good food combo, like the poached egg they offer as a steak's side üëåüèΩ Delicious! üòã

I got a beautiful rib-eye with a side of poached egg and I know it's crazy, but the egg yolk goes very well with potatoes and steak, that's why in Chile we have chorrillanas ‚ù§Ô∏è

Anyway, I've been wanting to go to Fire for a good while. Whenever I parked in town or walked by Dawson street, I smelled that beautiful fired coal or wood mixed with the meat. It's amazing.

I'm happy I finally went and I'm planning my next time after my son is born because my wife can't enjoy a well done steak ü•©
It's gonna be her postpartum celebration üéâ

Lovely place. Super recommended.
Write me a DM on Insta if you didn't like it because I couldn't agree with that üòÇ

Atmosphere is great! Fancy place, lovely cocktails and I like the idea of a welcoming area/bar before you go to your table. I think it makes the difference and it reminds me all the resorts I've been. Just love it.

Well done, guys!

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Fantastic interior, terrific service, great food and steaks.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Price is relatively good. Service is nice. Food is‚Ä¶.
Soso.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
You've read it in other reviews: from the service to the atmosphere to the food, this place has it nailed. I don't have a single negative thing to say.

We came in a large group of 17. They handled us at 2 tables with great attention, we're friendly and took amazing care of us.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Without doubt, one of the the best meals i have eaten. The starters were perfect, I could have eaten the salad as a main. The steaks (both sirloin and rib eye) are incredibly flavourful and the creamy peppercorn sauce is fantastic. I am not a desert person, but had to slow down because I was eating so fast. The cocktails are moorish and the wine selection is great. I cannot recommend this restaurant enough.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Staff are highly professional. Menu is varied and interesting - a good variety of wines and cocktails. Property first class - try to book a table in the front window section. ...  Nice Saturday afternoon bottle of Cloudy Bay.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: We have had many nights out here. It was just as super. 2nd Christmas Dinner in December. Even though we had fab oysters üòã at Christmas , dinner and desert where just as delightful. Thanks for service x

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
Surprisingly, I had dinner here after reading all good reviews, and got disappointed of customer service, the lady who was at reception was very cold when i arrived, she asked if I wanted to wait in the reception (we booked a table and i arrived on-time , my friend was still on the way), i said no i would like to be seated, then she got another lady to walk me upstairs to our table. We booked an outdoor table, there were other 2 tables at that time (so not too busy), waiters/waitresses who served our table were nice (especially the man in suit, i guess he's the manager),  but they got my drink wrong, and i also had to remind them 2 times for my coke to be served. Food is great but the display is somehow not met my expectation. What upset me the most was  when we left I said thank you and bye to the same lady at the reception but she did not response. Nice food but i will not come back!

Updates: i saw a few reviews mentioning staffs judge if you're underdressed, right that day i wore jean, that may answer!

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
I've been waiting for years for an opportunity to get in here, and it lived up to my expectations. From the quality of the food to the wow factor of the place, it is a unique place for a great experience.
We were a party of 6 and we all got steak, absolutely delighted with it and recommend it. I also got a side of those chestnut mushroom with caramelized onions, it was absolutely gorgeous.
They do offer a great selection of wine to pair with your meal.
I highly recommend it !

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Starter was my Highlight 5/5, main and dessert a 3/5

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Food is amazing, staff very friendly and nice atmosphere. . Been here a few times and will definitely go again.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text:
This place is suitable for a special day‚ú® I am amazed at its enormous interior and atmosphere. It was pretty satisfying experience. Most of staffs are friendly.
I mentioned that this is for a celebration when making a reservation and at the end of the course, I got a dessert in the pictureüéÇ

The oysters were incredibly freshü¶™, and the steaks were thick and lovelyü•©
However, as I am expertised in meats, I would say the part of the meat I got wasn‚Äôt the best.

name: FIRE Steakhouse & Bar
review_text: Beautiful building with a great atmosphere.  Our server, Danielle, was very friendly, put us all at ease and helped us work through the menu.  Food was delicious, with our whole party very impressed. Had the prawn starter, with lots of garlic butter. Sirloin steak cooked to perfection with a hot peppery sauce and chunky chips, ended with the cheese board. Will definitely be back

name: NoLIta
review_text: This is an very amazing place to meet friends üòÄ. Food is delicious and there are many vegetarian options available. Price is also reasonable for food. Ambience is nice staff is extremely polite and it is great place. Only thing after 10 music is very loud and one can not talk to their friends. Music after 10 was so loud you can hear it outside the gate also. Giving 4 star because of very loud music which made it difficult to talk to my friends.

name: NoLIta
review_text: The cocktail menu at Nolita is very good. They have some unique drinks and will also make the classics for you on request. After 10pm it becomes more of a club, everyone is dancing and they have a DJ/live artists for the music. There‚Äôs lots is seating space, mostly indoor. Would recommend booking a table in advance.

name: NoLIta
review_text: Can only speak about the cocktails and they were fab. Especially loved the Spanish Harlem. The doorman was sound as were all the staff. Would definitely return and hopefully try some food the next time.

name: NoLIta
review_text:
Great buzz the night we went.
Reasonable prices for a club in Dublin and no entrance fee which is a huge plus.
Had good music and also a guy playing the trumpet which added a great vibe, I haven't danced as much in a long time!
Recommended if you're in the area!

name: NoLIta
review_text: I've been here twice and each time it has been exceptional. The food and cocktails are an experience not soon forgotten. Stylish interior with a roof terrace.

name: NoLIta
review_text:
Service was a little cold here.

The pizza we had was great and full of flavour we loved the sauce that was on it. Atmosphere is nice and would be nice to take a booth if you were having a work dinner or something as it‚Äôs quite private to talk.

Cocktails were nice but nothing special.

name: NoLIta
review_text: We had dinner for 13 of us for my birthday. The food was great and the menu has lots of variety for the picky eaters haha. It broke into a great atmosphere with drums around 11. A DJ at 12 and the place goes public at 10. Big bookings have a surcharge but it's totally understandable. We had a blast

name: NoLIta
review_text: We needed somewhere that served not quickly but efficiently as we had a ferry to catch.  The service was perfect. The decor was lovely - high ceilings,  spacious and light - and the food was delicious, good sized portions and extremely tasty. All in all an excellent meal and the set menu was good value for money. No complaints whatsoever.

name: NoLIta
review_text: Lovely place with nice food and cocktails. Had a nice brunch. Service pleasant but quite low-key.

name: NoLIta
review_text:
The vibe is nice there, nice place to chill with friends or to date.
Drinks and food is good.

name: NoLIta
review_text: I only wish I had found NoLIta my first night!!  The food was beyond amazing!  The pumpkin ravioli and spaghetti and meatballs was simply outstanding!  Yhaz, our server was so attentive, polite and accommodating!  I cannot say enough great things about this establishment!  The brownie was decadent and so very good!  Do yourself a favor and run to eat here!!!  Atmosphere was also beautiful!

name: NoLIta
review_text: I bought ticket to celebrate my birthday with some friends. It would be an 2000‚Äôs event so I was really excited. I try to book a table five times and asked if it was possible to bring a cake. They didn‚Äôt answer my email properly. They just answer they were fully booked. I followed the instructions that I should have requested table for they put us together. So they didn‚Äôt allowed me to cut the cake there. The waitress was rude. Plus on friend of mine didn‚Äôt have ticket and tried to buy in the day. They weren‚Äôt allowed him even we have a plenty of space in the table. So the space and food is really good but the customer service ruins it. I found another pub to be treated as a person who was celebrating. I hope the management team take care better their customers in the future.

name: NoLIta
review_text: A great atmosphere, fantastic starters and italian pizza. Highly recommended.

name: NoLIta
review_text: We have great time, good dinner, Perfect music .

name: NoLIta
review_text: Was a bit sceptical because of previous reviews have to say food was fab and staff were really good defo 5 star rating no faults

name: NoLIta
review_text: Rather disappointing. Hostess was cold and not welcoming. We brushed it off and sat down. The server was very friendly but clearly new to service. He took our entire order at the on set drinks, appetizers, and mains. I ordered the burrata as an appetizer & was informed that he wasn‚Äôt sure if there was any left. What shocked me was that our entrees arrived at the table even before our drinks (at least 5+ minutes, yes we waited along time). Secondly, he didn‚Äôt come back to tell us they were out of burrata. Maybe he thought because he said they might be out that was enough. I don‚Äôt know, but he didn‚Äôt even come back to tell us or ask if we wanted something else. The margarita pizzas we ordered were mediocre at best. Lastly, I had to go to the bar counter to get a second round of drinks and for water. They did have a good acoustic guitar player in the bar area entertaining. He might‚Äôve been the best thing about this place besides the d√©cor & interior. I do not recommend eating at this place maybe just drinking at the bar. Worst service we‚Äôve experienced on a long time.

name: NoLIta
review_text: Went to the "Summer BBQ" on Saturday, the space was tiny, the saxophone player was only on for 20 mins, the food was mediocre at best and the staff seemed like they wanted to be anywhere else but there. One person in particular was quite rude, there was nowhere for us to sit and eat, one staff member kindly said it would be fine as the table wasn't in use until 5:30pm to only be told by another guy that was setting up tables upstairs to move and in quite a rude and aggressive manner, to he honest the experience left a bad taste in my mouth,  didnt finish my food. Unfortunately it was a massive fail for me and find it comical that I spent ‚Ç¨29 for the privilege it's a hard pass from me!

name: NoLIta
review_text: Great night out.. very welcoming and staff  all very nice to deal with. Prices of drinks were good and pizzas are great

name: NoLIta
review_text: Wonderful customer service by Juan. We were 12 ladies coming in without a reservation but they thankfully accommodated us. Finger food and mojitos were delicious. We‚Äôll be back, thank you Juan!

name: NoLIta
review_text: I tried to booking a table for my birthday party and changed for a totally mistake. I did this with more than 15 before the chosen date. Unfortunately by the website isn‚Äôt possible because the number of guests. By phone isn‚Äôt possible either. By email I have no well explained how works after 5 emails exchanged I was telling the no more booking available for the day and time. Totally disappointed with the neglecting of the service

name: NoLIta
review_text: Cocktails absolutely incredible, food mouth savouring. Honestly the best meals Iv ever had. Service is very good, fast arrivals, very mannerly. 100% would recommend

name: NoLIta
review_text:
**Update: Nolita staff took my call, and were very understanding and great about my complaint. I appreciate there response! üíï
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Last night I arrived with a group of my friends for a 32nd birthday drinks booking. WE WERE ALL REFUSED ENTRY.

The bouncer said ‚Äúwe did not fit in with the dress code ‚Äú. In the meantime the same bouncers ignored us and allowed others who wore jeans and trainers üëü into the venue.
I was so disgusted as now it was apparent that the dress code NO BLACKS ALLOWED!

My friends and I were upset and embarrassed about this display in front of others but as God would have it, complete strangers of caucasian üë©‚Äçüíº skin colour stood for us and argued with the bouncer‚Äôs for discrimination! Other guest‚Äôs who had been given entrance during this came back outside and demanded to know why we were being treated this way. The bouncer told our heroes to mind there own business.

To the amazing brave women and men From last night, God bless you! Thank you üôè so much for the love üíï, support.

To Nolita however, I was really disappointed and saddened by my experience at your establishment. It was humiliating and embarrassing to have been treated this way by your staff on account of upholding your standards.

Advice! If your staff at your door do not represent your values as a company, then they shouldn‚Äôt be there. Because now you left us and others with a bad view of Nolita, which may not reflect your true business.
With that being said, you retaining the same security staff at the door üö™ after this nightmare would be a clear indication of your values.

name: NoLIta
review_text:
Located in the heart of Dublin, Nolita Bar stands out as a trendy and vibrant spot for socializing and enjoying a night out. With its chic decor, lively ambiance, and delectable food and drinks, Nolita Bar offers an enjoyable experience that caters to a diverse crowd.

As you step into Nolita Bar, you'll immediately notice its stylish interior design. The combination of contemporary and rustic elements creates an inviting and comfortable atmosphere. The dim lighting and carefully curated music playlist contribute to the overall cool and relaxed vibe.

The bar staff at Nolita is known for their friendly and attentive service. They are always ready to provide recommendations and assist with any special requests. The mixologists behind the bar are true masters of their craft, skillfully concocting a wide array of creative cocktails. Whether you prefer classic favorites or innovative mixes, Nolita has something to satisfy every palate.

One of the highlights of Nolita Bar is its impressive drink menu. From artisanal cocktails to a great selection of craft beers and fine wines, the bar offers a diverse range of options. The bartenders are knowledgeable and passionate, ensuring that each drink is expertly crafted and presented with flair.

When it comes to the food, Nolita Bar offers a delightful menu that perfectly complements the drinks. The dishes are a fusion of international flavors and modern twists on traditional favorites. Whether you're in the mood for small plates to share or a satisfying main course, the food at Nolita does not disappoint. Don't miss their signature dishes such as the mouthwatering sliders or the flavorful sushi rolls.

Another standout feature of Nolita Bar is its live entertainment. On select nights, the bar hosts talented local musicians and DJs, creating an energetic and vibrant atmosphere. The performances add an extra layer of enjoyment to an already fantastic experience, making Nolita an excellent choice for a night of entertainment.

The only minor drawback of Nolita Bar is that it can get quite crowded during peak hours, which may make finding a table a bit challenging. However, the lively atmosphere and the opportunity to meet new people more than compensate for this inconvenience.

In summary, Nolita Bar is a trendy hotspot in Dublin, offering a winning combination of stylish decor, exceptional service, and a fantastic menu of drinks and food. Whether you're looking for a night out with friends, a romantic evening, or simply a place to unwind, Nolita Bar is well worth a visit. Just be prepared for a bustling crowd and a memorable night of fun and enjoyment.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text:
The Ivy in Dublin is a beautiful and elegant restaurant located in the heart of the city. The moment you step inside, you are greeted with a warm and inviting atmosphere that sets the tone for a wonderful dining experience. The decor is stylish and sophisticated, with plush seating and elegant lighting.

The menu at The Ivy offers a wide variety of dishes to choose from, including contemporary European cuisine with an emphasis on fresh, locally sourced ingredients. I had the pleasure of trying their duck salad, which was cooked to perfection and served with fresh vegetables. The steak and fish dishes were also delicious. The sides and appetizers were also well presented and tasty.

The service at The Ivy is top-notch. The waitstaff are friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu.

Overall, The Ivy in Dublin is a fantastic restaurant with great atmosphere and delicious food. Highly recommend visiting for a special occasion or a night out with friends.

I want to point out about Ben and his hosting services were impeccable and I loved his Gucci tie and Bow tie change the next day! Manager Diago was extremely helpful and got my cocktails at the bar really quickly so as a customer, with a busy bar area, he was able to manage the customer service with a smile and also a very nice double breast suit jacket. There are some Strong Skilled Female Cocktail creators too and I want to note they were super friendly and need to be acknowledged! Lucas for Argentina thank you for being friendly, although not my server he was engaging and I love the international vibes here.

I have to ENCOURAGE bringing CASH for tipping the staff. I will say everyone and the service and food is just amazing however I want to know the staff are being tipped for their work and that they don't have any troubles keeping their tips. I carry cash and got my waiter Fortis to give me some change and was able to tip him directly.

Fortis (Greek) was fun with my friends and was able to serve the table with ease. He took photos for us and was no trouble at all when I wanted to check the bill to pay it without having the birthday gal seeing the bill. His ability to work with me and be effectient and professional and engaging was appreciated.

Thank you for great food and beautiful cocktails and wine - I love the Ivy.

But once you walk in and ask to be seated, the staff are very supportive and willing to help out. Someone will come and attend your table right when you sit down.

When we went, with my partner we asked the staff if they can make changes to our meal due to dietary requirement and it was possible.

Waiting time was reasonable for the food to arrive.

And if one needs to relief themselves there is a lavatory facility available in the basement level. And let me tell you, it's a very fancy lavatory.

Prices are decent and you get good portions (at least for the meals we've had).

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text:
The Ivy Dublin Dining.

Imagine this: It's a chilly Friday night in Dublin, and you and your friends are dressed to impress for a birthday celebration at one of the hottest spots in town - The Ivy Dublin. As you approach the restaurant, the sight of its luxurious exterior and chic signage makes your heart skip a beat.

Upon arrival, you're greeted by the friendly staff and shown to your reserved table. However, as you eagerly wait for your food to arrive, you can't help but notice the time ticking by. Finally, after 25 minutes of anxious anticipation, your table is ready, and you're ready to indulge in some top-notch cuisine.

The menu is a feast for the senses, and you're already salivating just by reading it. The chefs at The Ivy Dublin truly live up to their reputation, and every dish that arrives at your table is a work of art. From succulent meats to delectable vegetarian options, every bite is bursting with flavor and leaves you wanting more.

But the experience is not just about the food - the interior of the restaurant is breathtakingly beautiful, with intricate details and elegant furnishings that transport you to a different era. The atmosphere is lively, but the noise level is just enough to create a vibrant ambiance without detracting from the overall experience.

As the night wears on, your friend's birthday is made even more special by the attentive staff who surprise him with a complimentary dessert. And as you leave The Ivy Dublin, with satisfied tummies and happy hearts, you know that this is a restaurant you will return to again and again.

My burger was tough,  chewy, I left most of it. Dessert was ok, duck salad was definitely not made fresh it just felt like it had been prepped a few hours b4 and the microwaved duck added after.  I would not go for the food, maybe just for a drink and a,nibble .
