review_text: Gorgeous restaurant in the heart of Dublin city. They serve fluffy pancakes for brunch -all gluten free üëçüèº you could even say that the Ivy is to Dublin what Caf√© Reichard is to Cologne.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: One of our best meals in Dublin. Fancy place. Waiters were tuxes. Wear a shirt with a collar and pants or you will feel under dressed. Everything about this place was great. Reservations a must.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Super nice luxury surrounds lots greenery colourful murals staff very friendly excellent customer service and my favourite.... an offer of a complimentary second cup of ‚òïÔ∏è oh they had me on that ü§£

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text:
Atmosphere, plants, service are great.
food are fine, price is not cheap.
Booking is needed, online booking is enough

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Went for breakfast. The food was fantastic and the service was excellent. Can't say much about atmosphere as it was early morning with few people around.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Great food, great atmosphere, and a very friendly staff. I would recommend it! I came in the winter and got the Shepard's pie, which was the perfect comfort food dish for a cold rainy day!
owner_answer:
Good morning, Thank you so much for your feedback. I am so pleased to hear you had such a great time when you dined recently. We look forward to seeing you in the restaurant again soon¬†

Kind regards, 
The Ivy Dawson street

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text:
pretty nice restaurant, amazing service.
food was delicious, atmosphere was alright a bit noisy.
owner_answer:
Good- Thank you so much for your feedback. I am so pleased to hear you had such a great time when you dined recently. I will be sure to pass your kind words on to the rest of the team. We look forward to seeing you in the restaurant again soon¬†

Kind regards, 
The Ivy Dawson street

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: I haven't been yet.   Booked 9th December.  Will post a review then.  I must say I loved the food.   Had venison.  Its rather expensive as main course did not include any vegetables.   It would be better if the price of the main course included sides.   Price looks OK until you order a complete meal. Very good service.  There is a limited time.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text:
Super posh place
Great decoration
You need to be dressed up
The food is very tasty and you can choose from a variety of dishes

It is a bit expensive but worth it to celebrate something
owner_answer:
Good afternoon, Thank you so much for your feedback. I am so pleased to hear you had such a great time when you dined recently. I will be sure to pass your kind words on to the rest of the team. We look forward to seeing you in the restaurant again soon¬†

Kind regards, 
The Ivy Dawson street

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Beautiful restaurant with a great vibe! Had a delicious brunch
owner_answer:
Thank you so much for your feedback. I am so pleased to hear you had such a great time when you dined recently. I will be sure to pass your kind words on to the rest of the team. We look forward to seeing you in the restaurant again soon¬†

Kind regards, 
The Ivy Dawson street

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: In any good cocktail bar anywhere in the world a cocktail is accompanied by a glass of water and some little snack. Some olives or nuts or crisps ?? Not in the IVY Dublin. ‚Ç¨5.95 for 10 olives, no exaggeration!! Nice room, good service, mediocre food.
owner_answer:
Good morning
Thank you for your feedback. I am so sorry to hear you did not enjoy your experience when you dined with us recently. We take all feedback extremely seriously here at The Ivy Dublin and we would really like to¬†address the issues you have raised. If you follow the link below and fill out the feedback form, one of our team will be in touch¬†to discuss your comments with you in more detail.

https://theivydublin.com/contact-us/

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Food is always good; service has been terrible last two visits: everyone working looks like they don‚Äôt want to be there, and are rude and moody. Very bad considering the reputation the restaurant has worldwide

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Sat at the bar on an early Sunday evening. Immaculate service, great menu with an Irish twist, really buzzing atmosphere. Good value too!
owner_answer: Thank you so much for your feedback. I am so pleased to hear you had such a great time when you dined recently. I will be sure to pass your kind words on to the rest of the team. We look forward to seeing you in the restaurant again soon¬†Kind regards, The Ivy Dawson street

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: The cocktails were good but the food preparation wins hands down for me. The halloumi grill is the most flavourful and tasty dish I ever tasted in Dublin in years. Very busy tables but the staff were highly attentive. Fair play to the team.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text:
We enjoyed a celebratory meal here and would absolutely recommend this venue for it's beautiful setting and decor. The Ivy restaurant is well-known for it's monkfish and prawn curry and this dish definitely didn't disappoint.

The highlight of the meal for me was the chocolate bomb dessert, although I was well-informed, that the cheesecake was also delicious. I didn't try the cocktails and thought they seemed a bit pricey but I don't normally go for fancy drinks. üçπ

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: The interiors of the Ivy are really great. It‚Äôs quite a busy restaurant, would recommend always booking in advance. The menu has lots options and also has a separate vegetarian menu. The food was delicious but the service was a little slow.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Food is not their strength, from what we could taste. Eggs Royal were nice and so was the steak sandwich. But not outstanding though. Ordered Pancakes and berries afterwards and it was a disappointment. Portion is ridiculous small and it came hard like if you bought from a supermarket and warmed up in the microwave (actually I would rather eat it from the supermarket). The waitress apologised and took it off the bill. But still charged us for the ‚Äúsauces‚Äù it came with: strawberries and maple syrup. ‚Ç¨8 for these ‚Äúsauces‚Äù. To go on with the disappointment, we ordered cream br√ªl√©e, which came cold and lacking consistency. Overall, it‚Äôs a very beautiful place, nice atmosphere but food is not worth it for the price they charge. By the way, the 12,5% service charge fee certainly doesn‚Äôt go to the staff as tips. That‚Äôs shameful.

name: The Ivy Dublin
review_text: Food was fabulous and the atmosphere is amazing. I would highly recommend you make reservations here.
owner_answer:
Thank you so much for your feedback. I am so pleased to hear you had such a great time when you dined recently. I will be sure to pass your kind words on to the rest of the team. We look forward to seeing you in the restaurant again soon¬†

Kind regards, 
The Ivy Dawson Street

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: The food was amazing, we had the chicken liver parfait which was a very generous portion followed by the Seabeam and a side of mash then the pear and plum cobbler. We really enjoyed the food one of the best meals we have in a very long time. The staff were very friendly and service was excellent just one little negative was we were only given one menu to choose from but apparently there are a few, would have been nice to had the choice. The restaurant was immaculate as was the facilities just a few wobbly tiles on the gents tiolet floor. There was a service charge but we don't mind that as the service was great as was the malbac even though we had the tasty red wth fish. Definitely recommend here and we'll be back.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Beautiful, cozy and romantic restaurant with fireplaces burning and candles lit on the tables. Well dressed and pleasant staff. All the food was absolutely amazing! I'd eat here a thousand times over, well done!

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
My favorite dish from this restaurant was the hummus! Overall, it was an excellent place to visit!

For parents for toddlers, I didn't see highchairs. The restrooms were located upstairs. There could have been a lift for people with a wheelchair ‚ôøÔ∏è but I didn't see it.

In closing, I would visit this restaurant again.!

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Best onion rings I‚Äôve had! We came in to check out the venue as a potential space for a future event. But the vibe was so energetic and fun that we decided to stop in for appies and drinks. We‚Äôre so glad that we did! Highly recommend (besides the onion rings) the burrata and carrots. Too bad that we didn‚Äôt have room to try more.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: A nice place with great atmosphere, got many options both in veggie and non veg. The cauliflower is delicious. Bean stew too !

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: I had to post as soon as we got back from dining here. It was absolutely first class in respect of service but the food oh my goodness was outstanding! The padron pepper snack was delicious with a creamy garlic and chorizo sauce. We then had a spinach flat bread, delicious carrots and onion rings and fries. Two fab cocktails were so well made and presented so nicely. We prebooked for a Sunday night but it was really quiet. Maybe three or four other tables taken we could see. The night before it had looked bursting at the seams but this was much better for a meal for couples. I wouldn‚Äôt hesitate to recommend and I would definitely come back again. Just love everything about the whole place.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
I can definitely write pages and pages about the incredible experience we had at this restaurant. The food is so delicious. I can say hands down one of the top 10 restaurants I have ever been to anywhere in the world and definitely the number one best bread I have ever had in my life.
I wish the wine menu was a little more extensive. Make sure you leave room for desert because as you think you have just had the best food you could have asked for the desert gives you something else to remember for a really long time. Oh and good luck getting a table without reservations in advance!

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Went to the rooftop for drinks with friends and we were very welcomed by the staff. We had no reservation but the waitress (Isabele) did her best to accommodate us all. The manager was also very friendly and concerned on getting our drinks quickly.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Slightly disappointed üòû.  Atmosphere inside was not great and food "Sunday roast" was just okay. Was looking forward to more.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
It was a very nice experience at this restaurant. Tasty food, many cocktail options (and non-alcoholic).

The service was quick, our server took care of our table the full night without a problem.

Definitely a place to visit again.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
My sister and I went to this restaurant, as we had  the Rustic Stone booked and unfortunately it did not open.
Firstly, the staff are incredibly, efficient, friendly and attentive.
Secondly,  the food is delicious, ever bite was an explosion of flavours,  a symphony of pleasure.
Thirdly, the food looked beautiful when delivered to the table. A wonderful presentation.

I am extremely impressed with this restaurant.  Very clean, staff in all areas were very good.
We got Gluten free: they don't have a great selection of starters gluten free (and who wants a half starter as a substitute. I dislike this option from any restaurant).
However, the main course we ordered was amazing,  so this disadvantage disappears.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Food was good but service was poor. Drinks were forgotten, and staff were unpleasant which is not what you'd expect for the prices they charge. Additionally, when we were booking over the phone we were told that we could not book a table in the rooftop bar as you are not allowed to eat in the rooftop bar, only drinks are served there so they put us into the restaurant section but when we moved to the rooftop bar for drinks, everyone there was ordering and eating food from the same menu. It would have been fine if they had just told us there was no availability at the time but there was no need to lie about the food service. That said, the rooftop bar is a nice place for drinks. However this doesn't excuse the fact that staff were unpleasant when seating us and taking our orders. Wouldn't normally mind but it is not a cheap venue.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Really enjoyed this venue, one of by favourite places, would definitely go back. The venue is quite popular so I‚Äôd recommend booking at least 3 days in advance. The chicken liver parfait was really nice, it‚Äôs a big portion. Pork belly and potatoes were well seasoned and very tender. Desserts (chocolate choux bun and pavlova) was amazing. I found the portions big and the meal filing so definitely go hungry. Even with a large packed venue the service was quick and efficient allowing enough time in between courses. The facilities were very clean. The kitchens are open Palau so you can see the chefs working away, the pizza also looked incredible. The venue was dimly lit with red exposed brick and redish brown decor giving it a rustic feel. Our meal was reasonably priced for drinks and 3 courses. The steaks slate more expensive c150 but these are sharing steaks and looked amazing. Can‚Äôt wait to go back!

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Picked this restaurant to meet our daughter and her boyfriend with our family.  So thankful it had online booking and it was on time.  The cocktail menu is quite extensive which was great to see.  It has a lovely selection of menu items and everybody was very pleased with the choices.  Our waitress was not so attentive and managed to spill the water and juices from the oyster plate down the boyfriends sweater.  The dessert menu was a hit with all.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: After looking for a place to eat after 9pm in Dublin as all pubs just serve drinks, the Fade Street Restaurant was a great find. Fantastic food and great service.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Delicious food, great venue. We had a 3 course menu as a group, I liked my meal (which doesn't happen that often).

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
Hamburger and fries were really good, as we're the cocktails.
Ate dinner on the rooftop, where most others were drinking only. Music blasted a bit. People smoking cigars as we arrived but they soon left.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: A restaurant with a good vibe. A bit of an expensive place but the food is quite decent. Being a vegetarian I found the main course could have had more options. It just had the mushroom dish. All the vegetarian options had too much cream in it which could be improved. As vegetarian food is more than that.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
Upstairs bar was nice and service was decent, good bar staff.
The restaurant was crammed, crowded and not a relaxed atmosphere. The food was decent but not special. The table staff were pleasant but the team of all male (who i assume were managers) were awful. Rude, intimidating and unhelpful. None of my table were impressed and none will return, mainly due to the unpleasant managers.
It was very much a conveyor belt system of getting customers in and out with little thought going into the customers experience.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
My wife wanted a low key 50th birthday celebration dinner, so I, with recommendations from friends, booked Fade Street Social to have a little intimate dinner.
From the minute we arrived, to the minute we left, we were looked after with a level of service that was second to none.
The food, the wine, and the cocktail choices were fantastic, and there was something for everybody.
The whole evening was just one wonderful social experience that I, my wife, and friends would recommend to everyone.
This was my and most of my friend's first visit to Fade Street Social but are already planning a return visit.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Last Saturday, together with my friend, we visited the place and the truth is that we were very satisfied, not only with the food and the cocktails but also with the service that Ugo provided us. We will definitely go back. Highly recommendedüòã üëèüèº

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: The roof is a nice location but the service was absolutely appalling. There were times where my table had to wait over 40 minutes to receive a drink and at several times during the night we had to ask again where our orders were. The staff seemed more interested in chatting to each other than serving people. The food is pretty average and not worth the money.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
First time dining in the downstairs restaurant, having been at the excellent tapas style bar a few times. Food was delicious though pretty pricey for what was served - the short rib Mac & Cheese was unbelievable though, will be back for that!

The major drawback was the heat in the place; Dylan, I understand the open kitchen concept but please sort out the air conditioning. Every table around us was melting and it drove us out of the restaurant before we were ready.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: The environment is really nice, but the food was not as good as expected. We ordered the pork belly and the minute steak. The pork belly was okay, but a bit dry. What was most shocking was the minute steak, that looked more like an ‚Äúhour steak‚Äù from how dry and overcooked it was (even burnt). Do not recommend.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Fabulous steaks and starters. I had onion soup and chateaubriand. Friendly service and overall the place looks and feels good. Again - if you visit, I really recommend to order steak, it‚Äôs top notch. They have also a nice list of cocktails - I had the one with prosecco and elderflower - was good but too sweet for my taste. Truffle fries - very good too.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
Everyone agreed that the burger was in the top 3 best burgers they ever ate.

HOWEVER, drink service was EXTREMELY slow. The restaurant could have easily doubled their drink revenue of our table if they were simply quicker at taking orders and fulfilling them. I had to chase sien our waiter to order a glass of red with my steak, but by the time it arrived, I only had a couple of bites of streak left (despite delaying eating).

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
5 stars to our waitress Alex (also known as Alexandra) she deserves a raise! She makes the experience - so attentive and just bringing all the energy needed for a good meal evening.
What an amazing vibe of a place though, I mean it was a bit loud (music played quite loud, hence the 4 stars) couldn‚Äôt really hear my partner infront of me.
Food though... another level, so good and yummy ... pricey yes but so yummy!!!
Would definitely recommend! We were in the Woodfire and cocktail part of the restaurant, inner courtyard. We had the ribs - 10/10 credit to the chef.
Thank you

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Fantastic dinner. Staff super attentive but also not overbearing. Food and drinks were incredible and would highly recommend. Unexpected gem.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: One male member of staff on cocktail terrace rude and snappy we  were hurried to order. Also for some unexplained reason when two of our party wanted to pay separately they weren't allowed. Is this a policy? We asked could we eat upstairs when booking but were told no.  We ate downstairs then moved upstairs to our reserved seats where we were surrounded by people eating. Very confusing. While the food and surroundings were grand the serving staff left a lot to be desired

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Blackberry pavlova was absolutely amazing and my favorite desert on our trip to Dublin I had! The fillet was almost amazing paired with a cherry wine sauce. VERY lively when we went so be preperered to talk a bit louder to your dining guests.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
If you only visit one restaurant in Dublin, make it this one!
The food is unbelievably good for the reasonable prices. The service is attentive and both the food and drinks were the best in Dublin.
I‚Äôd definitely visit again and would recommend not missing out on a chance to go yourself!

The food pictured is the duck and goats cheese calzone, roast pork belly, sweet potato pur√©e and fries.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Very pleasant experience. Bread appetizer absolutely slapped. Burger was very solid. Pizza good- but crust was way too dominant. Crust was about 3x the size of the pizza. Vibes decent, will say we went at lunch on a Monday. If you hit this place during prime time, the vibes will likely hit differently

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Fantastic food, brilliant service and just overall a great experience.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
Nice food , beautifully presented but personally, for the price I was a little disappointed. I had a vegetarian option. The starter and pudding were nice but the main (bean casserole) was a let down.  The dish was very salty and the presentation was lacking. The first few bites were nice but it soon became a struggle to eat.
The biggest let down was the service which was very slow although staff were very pleasant and attentive when they were with you.
I don't think I would go back again.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Found it on Google and went for dinner to try out ! Nice vibe and service was good, but food was bit disappointing, starters were nice but the main course we ordered which was steak and fish , both were over cooked , sent back the steak as it was way too well cooked , fish was very dry as it was over cooked too .

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Always amazing! Easily one of my top 3 favourites in Dublin. Dylan McGrath is simply culinary genius. Service is also always fantastic. Solid 5/5 every time I have visited in the past 7+ years.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Normally I wouldn‚Äôt order a burger with the words ‚Äúdry‚Äù in it (I‚Äôm not local to Ireland so maybe it‚Äôs the thing to say here!) but thank goodness I did order it. Dry Aged Burger - I think it‚Äôs one of the best burgers I‚Äôve ever eaten. Worth conquering! Enjoy this gem of a restaurant. ‚ò∫Ô∏è

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
Chaotic and overfilled. I will admit it was Paddy‚Äôs day however the aggression I observed by one particular waiter was atrocious. He treated the younger staff terribly and almost caused an accident whilst impatiently grabbing customer‚Äôs dishes and shoving them on their tables.

I don‚Äôt mind spending money on food however I do not appreciate being lied to either. Everyone surrounding us were eating this beautiful stacked burger. I asked for it and was told ‚Äúit was part of the kids menu‚Äù - no child could possibly finish this burger which was most certainly an adults dish.

I will never step into this restaurant again

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
Great place for cocktails, it has an internal heated garden perfect to share a good time with friends.
Small bites are good!

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Food was nicely presented, perfectly cooked with quality ingredients; only to be ruined by the sides and parts of the dish that were incredibly salty. There was no reason for that amount of salt to be in the food.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: A foodie Dubliner treated us to a delightful lunch here. Loads of vegetarian options, great service and beautiful presentation. Highly recommended.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Delicious food and great cocktails. If you are a fan of Mac n cheese don't miss the short rib Mac n cheese here. Also, highly recommend Cod and Buratta appetizers.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Had the roast pork belly and the passionfruit pavlova for dessert. The food was very tasty. Ambiance a bit loud. Good service.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Fantastic place in the heart of the city. Especially the conduct of the staff waiting the tables were amazing. Food was even better. Highly recommend

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Tonight myself and my friend went to fade st at the tables outside for a quick drink before a dinner booking. We asked for two glasses of Sauvignon blanc. After a bit of a wait we got a text that our booking was ready and asked to cancel the wines. We were told by staff that wasn‚Äôt possible and was made to pay ‚Ç¨19.90. We asked for takeaway cups. After another long wait we went to the door to check on the progress on the drinks and after another long wait was handed two glasses of red wine in a takeaway cup. We said we asked for white to which we were told no you didn‚Äôt. We protested this and said we did (as we were sober and remembered) and we‚Äôre again gaslighted. We took the drinks and left. Absolutely ridiculous that we could not cancel our drinks in a timely fashion, especially as we had not even paid for them! Very annoying, will not be back

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: I had a fantastic experience at this restaurant. A group of 3 girls for dinner and cocktails. We really enjoyed the drinks and pizza was so tasty. The staff are friendly and attentive. We were really impressed with the service. Lively atmosphere here which is a bonus too.

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: 40 euro service charge for a table of 4 with no mention of it until we got the receipt. Also, steak sauce is not included and we weren't asked if we want it, they just broght it and charge it.. the cutlery were included. 400 euro later we were rushed out so they can make another bob on that table. Meh..

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Frist time 55 wedding anniversary celebration Jay waiter excellent cocktails drinks food fabulous recommend saddle of lamb finished night off rooftop bar where Chris and ladies barstaff were fantastic met great people be back night to remember x

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text: Really nice restaurant! It‚Äôs definitely expensive, but the food is delicious and the service is great, the staff seem to make every customer feel special!

name: Fade Street Social Restaurant & Cocktail Bar
review_text:
The lady host working on Saturday was flawless, and also
her colleague, who was also helping to find us a table as we didn't have a reservation.
We ordered two ribeye medium rare, but we received them nearly blue. No complaints because the food was delicious.
It would've been five stars if only one of the managers looking after the front room had shown a little more enthusiasm, especially when I had a polite query about one of the products, and he seemed entirely disinterested.
Good food mixed atmosphere.

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Really good place to get tapas and wine. It is not very pricey as other places are, and service is great. Great value for the money we spent there. Absolutely recommend!
owner_answer:
Hi Gordan,
Thank you so much for leaving such a positive review on your experience at the Market bar, we are delighted you enjoyed our tapas & wine!
We hope to see you visit again soon!
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Quite a great spot for drinks and food. There is a range of food and drinks available here. Lots of space both - you can sit indoors and outdoors (smoking area). The staff is really nice and the interiors are gorgeous. Good place to catch up with a friend over a few drinks! Do try the patatas bravas :)
owner_answer:
Hi Sanghamitra, 
Thank you for taking the time to review Market Bar restaurant. We're thrilled to hear that you had a great experience at our establishment and enjoyed the range of food and drinks available. We take pride in our spacious indoor and outdoor seating options and are delighted that you found our interiors to be gorgeous. Our staff is dedicated to providing excellent service, and we appreciate your kind words about them. We're glad to hear that you enjoyed the patatas bravas and we hope you'll visit us again soon!

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: The food was OK. Not the most authentic spanish food, so the second time we went, we ordered chicken wings because as far as bar food goes, they taste great! The atmosphere is very nice. Easily accessible by wheelchair with a disabled toilet.
owner_answer:
Hi Amy, 

Thank you for sharing your experience at the Market Bar restaurant. I'm glad to hear that you enjoyed the chicken wings and the atmosphere of our restaurant.

While it's unfortunate to hear that the Spanish food didn't meet your expectations in terms of authenticity, I'm glad that you found something on the menu that you enjoyed.

Thank you for taking the time to leave a review, and I hope you'll consider returning to the Market Bar in the future.
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Lively spot at the side of George's Street Arcade. Great for groups on a pay day Thursday with an early bird menu of ‚Ç¨26 for two tapas, bread & dip, patatas bravas and a glass of wine/cava/pint. Music is good, staff are attentive and food is delicious üòã
owner_answer:
Hi Una, 
Great to hear that you enjoyed your visit to the Market Bar. It's always a pleasure to host groups on pay day Thursday, and we're glad that you found our early bird menu to be good value for money. We strive to create a lively and enjoyable atmosphere for our customers, and we're thrilled that you found the music to be good and our staff to be attentive. We take pride in our delicious food, so it's especially rewarding to hear that you enjoyed your tapas, bread & dip, and patatas bravas. Thank you for your kind words and we hope to see you again soon!

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: i needed the toilet so popped in for a drink while visiting dublin center (mainly to use the facilities) and was pleasantly surprised. lovely building with great character. staff were very attentive without being overly pushy and made a great whiskey sour. didnt eat but from my visit im sure food would be up to a good standard. drinks were slightly on the pricey side however.
owner_answer:
Hi Douglas,
Thank you so much for leaving us a kind review! We hope to welcome you back to the Market Bar to try our food the next time!
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
The food was incredible - you just have to order the right thing. The prawn dish (gambas pil pil), breads & dips and unlimited patatas bravas were INCREDIBLE. I also had an amazing glass of red wine. The place is a really cool space too.

Meatballs were mid. Probably skip the nachos for another dish!
owner_answer:
Hi Brecklyn, 
Thank you so much for leaving your kind words and 5 star review! It's great to hear that you enjoyed the food, especially the prawn pil pil, breads & dips, and the unlimited patatas bravas. It sounds like you made some great choices! Thanks again for sharing your review, and we hope to see you again soon here at the Market Bar. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Beautiful place, service was great and the food delicious. We ordered 2 lunch menus that was ‚Ç¨17 each, with bread and dips for starter, bork belly, fish tacos, patatas bravas and saffron rice. And also a sangria that was ‚Ç¨25. For dessert we had churros for ‚Ç¨8,50 if I am not wrong, that was warm and really crunchy. I went with a friend and it was a great place to chat, music was great and not too loud, it was just right. I‚Äôll go back there with my husband in a couple of weeks. And next week I will take a picture of the menu.
owner_answer:
Hi Raphaela, 
Thank you for leaving your kind review with positive feedback. We are so delighted to hear that you enjoyed everything from start to finish here at the Market Bar. We look forward to seeing you again on your next visit. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Always reliable and kind service. The owner personally sat me at a table and ensured I was well taken care of and the tapas were amazing. One of my tapas dishes was taking longer than expected. So the restaurant brought out potatoes bravas on the house to apologize for the wait. Class establishment that treats their customers well.
owner_answer:
Thank you Tammy, for leaving such a kind review and 5 stars! We are delighted that you enjoyed your experience with us here at the Market Bar and hope to see you again soon! 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
The tapas formula offered is quite interesting!  There is a good choice of dishes and beers. Food is tasty and the portions are big enough. I went there on a Saturday, so it was very crowded and the dinner menu quite expensive for what we get. Patatas bravas should be bottomless, but due to the high number of people, the service was slow and we got food all in once, and patatas bravas only once. We didn't had the change to order dessert since the kitchen was closed by the time we got to finish our food.
The atmosphere is nice as well as the place, but I think the service should be improved, so that people can really enjoy the time there, maybe eating something during their chats.
owner_answer:
Hi Donatella, 
Thank you for leaving your review and much appreciated feedback as we are always trying to improve on what we can here at the Market Bar. We are delighted to hear that you enjoyed the food and the atmosphere. We will be sure to pass on your feedback to management. 
Thanks again Donatella, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Good vibes and good food!
The service was great and the food was also great. They have a variety of platter options for sharing.

The cocktails are amazing.
owner_answer:
Hi Goodness Adegbenro, 

Thank you so much for your kind review and comments. We are delighted that you had such a positive experience with us here at the Market Bar. We hope to welcome you back again very soon. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: I‚Äôm horrified at the experience i just encountered in this bar today. I came in with a group of work mates  from a bar near by and ordered 4 drinks, 3 Guinness and one cider. The floor staff took at least 10 minutes to give initial order and 30 minutes to receive the drinks. There is 4 tables with 16 people max here, all served and waiting on nothing. The pints were dead and a foul smell and taste I recommend people to stay away if you value your time.
owner_answer:
Hi Aoife, 

Thank you for taking the time to leave your review and feedback. 
We deeply apologize for the disappointing experience you encountered at the Market Bar.
We understand your frustration and would like to assure you that this is not the standard of service we strive to provide. Your feedback is invaluable to us as we continuously work towards improving our operations.

We sincerely apologize for the delay in taking your initial order and the extended wait time for your drinks. We take full responsibility for the lapse in service and will be addressing this issue with our floor staff to ensure it does not happen again.

Regarding the quality of the pints and the unpleasant taste and smell, we are truly sorry for this unfortunate occurrence. We hold ourselves to the highest standards when it comes to serving our beverages, and it is clear that we fell short on this occasion. We will thoroughly investigate the matter and take immediate steps to rectify it.

To apologise, we would like to invite you back in with our compliments, please email us over on feedback@marketbar.ie and you will be looked after there. 

Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: It‚Äôs a nice place with really good service. But I was disappointed by the quality of the tapas. I expect better from a tapas only place. The atmosphere is nice though.
owner_answer:
Hi Rudolf, 
Thank you for leaving your review & feedback! We are disappointed and sorry to hear that you were not happy with the quality of our tapas, we will ensure to pass this feedback onto our head chef. 
We hope to see you return to the Market Bar for a more pleasant experience next time! 
Kind regards, 
The Market Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: My friends and I went to have dinner and we loved it. The personnel are super kind, they mistakenly brought a tapa we didn‚Äôt order and let us have it, asked about our allergies and constantly refilled our water. The atmosphere is also very good - you can have a proper conversation as the music and acoustics are not loud. I don‚Äôt give them the 5 stars just because they add to the bill a service fee that I personally prefer to add by myself. Nevertheless, would definitely recommend and repeat!
owner_answer:
Hi Cristina, 
Thank you for leaving your review and feedback. We are delighted to hear that you had an enjoyable experience here with us at the Market Bar. We appreciate your comment on the service fee and we will ensure it is passed onto management. We hope to see you return again very soon. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Went here for a group leaving do. The food was grand, and the staff made an effort to make vegetarian options into vegan ones for more choice. The room is a little echoey due to the high ceiling so it was sometimes hard to hear the other end of table. The staff took their time with the drinks and patatas refills. Some of the food took a while to get to us meaning you might be finished eating one dish before the other even gets to you but they tasted good when they came.
owner_answer:
Hi Christina, 
Thank you for leaving your review and feedback. We appreciate your comments and we will pass them onto our management team so these can be looked into and fixed. We do hope you had a enjoyable time with us overall and we look forward to welcoming you back to the Market Bar soon. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Expensive brunch (14‚Ç¨) poached eggs and very small portion drowned in mayo not tasty IMO.
The lunch tapas deals (17‚Ç¨) is better priced but still a bit crazy for the tiny amount of food you get.
Would be great with some more dairy free filling options.
Beautiful location and nice jazz live band.

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: I was there for a work event, and overall my experience was really nice. One of the dishes I ordered had a bit of delay, and when they were reminded of it, they were so nice to give me a bigger portion than the usual. I am giving three stars to the food only because it was not my favorite Cuisine, but for someone else it might be a 5!
owner_answer:
Hi Andrea, 
Thank you so much for taking the time to share your experience at The Market Bar. We truly appreciate your feedback and are thrilled to hear that you had a nice time overall during your work event.

We apologize for the slight delay in one of the dishes you ordered. However, we're delighted to know that our staff responded well to the situation and provided you with a larger portion as a gesture of goodwill. We always strive to ensure our guests' satisfaction and it's wonderful to hear that our team went above and beyond to accommodate you.

We hope to welcome you back again soon to the Market Bar. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: We took our mother out for what we hoped would be a lovely lunch but unfortunately the service let everything down. We waited 25 minutes of trying to catch staff‚Äôs eyes to take our order and when we finally called someone they were quite unfriendly. Our food arrived well before our drinks and when we ordered a jug of Sangria it took 20 minutes and a prompt to staff from us before it arrived. We had already finished our food! The food was a mix of good and poor. The chorizo in particular tasted very cheap but the calamari was lovely. I believe that adding a mandatory 12.5% tip to every bill has left no reason for the staff to offer good service and is really letting the restaurant down. It was not particularly busy and the staff were standing around a lot. The music was also very loud and we found it he‚Äôd to hear each other. Overall a very expensive and disappointing experience
owner_answer:
Hi Jen, 
Thank you for taking the time out to leave us a review. We are so sorry to hear that you had a disappointing experience with us here at the Market Bar. This is not that standard of service that we aim for and your comments and feedback will be passed onto management to ensure that these issues are looked into and fixed immediately.
We would like to invite you back in with our compliments to apologise and hopefully makeup for your negative experience, if you could please email us over on feedback@marketbar.ie and you will be looked after there. 
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
I have been here for a number of work nights out. The food is usually pretty good and the staff are very nice, they will make up any cocktail you wish. Doesn't matter if it's on the menu or not.
There is always a good vibe here and it can get very busy. For some reason, they don't have Creme de Menthe stocked in the bar which is needed for one of my favourite cocktails.
owner_answer:
Hi Derek, 
Thank you for leaving your review! Please do let us know if you have any feedback on your experience we would love to hear from you on feedback@marketbar.ie 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Very good food. Getting ready for St Patty's day. Met my wife's cousin who attend University of Dublin.
owner_answer:
Hi Thad, 

Thank you for sharing your experience with us and leaving us 5 stars. We're thrilled to hear that you enjoyed our food, and we hope that our preparations for St. Patricks Day added to the festive atmosphere of your visit. 

Thank you again for your patronage, and we hope to have the pleasure of serving you again soon. 

Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Went on Saturday day and it was dead.

The food was nice and the server too.

The only one less star is the tip is already included in the bill. The customers shouldn't have to pay your employees wages if you can't afford it. They should be on a livable wage. I would have tipped anyway because of our server but I don't appreciate it being already included.

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Beautiful concept. Reusing and converting an old mill but keeping the history. Love the openess, high ceiling. The place was packed yet didn't feel claustrophobic. Great ambiance and nice staff
owner_answer:
Hi Jash, 
Thank you for your 5 star review! We appreciate your kind comments and we are delighted to hear you had an enjoyable time with us here at the Market Bar. We look forward to welcoming you back again soon. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
"It's bigger on the inside!" - Doctor Who

Probably the biggest brunch place I've been to in that area and such a great vibe! The lunch deal they have (on weekdays I think) is a great bargain. There is a wide choice of cocktails to choose from and of course, Guinness on tap :)
Friendly staff, quick service and delicious food. What else do you need? 10/10 would recommend. I'll be visiting again for sure!
owner_answer: Thank you so much for posting such a lovely positive review for your time at The Market bar. We hope to see you again soon!

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: A really nice place to go with friends, the atmosphere was amazing staff also very friendly, nice drinks and food. Was very crowded but really nice food came very quickly. They have some special offers to lunch and dinner highly recommend this option. The music it's a apart chapter, different styles for all tastes.
owner_answer:
Thank you for leaving your kind comments and 5 star review Victor! We hope to see you again at the Market Bar soon!
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Really enjoyed this on a work outing. We had most of the food on the menu shared out and all of it was delicious.  Staff couldn't be friendlier. Will deffo be back
owner_answer:
Hi Ian,
Thank you for your kind 5 star review and feedback. We are delighted to hear you had a positive time with us here at the Market Bar. We look forward to seeing you again soon.
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Nice place to have Spanish tapas in the heart of Dublin. For lunch you get 1 small and 1 large tapas included. If you are not sure what to try, go for the lamb and chicken skewersÔºàserved with couscous and rice) and you won't be disappointed. Portions are huge and price tag very reasonable. They also offer pasta for kids. Highly recommended üëç
owner_answer: Thank you for reviewing The Market Bar and mentioning our great value lunch offer. We also have an additional lunch offer on for the mid-week afternoons which includes a glass of Mistinguett Cava each. We‚Äôve plenty of room and families are always welcome at lunch and weekend brunch.

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: We couldn't decide what we wanted to eat so we wandered up here to the Market Bar for a little bit of everything and what a decision we made!! The customer service, the atmosphere, the artwork and the staff's shirts matched the food...amazing!! It feels a little out of the way bit so worth the walk, everything we had from the Mushrooms to the Aubergine to the chicken was simply mouthwatering, definitely returning on our next visit.
owner_answer: What a exceptional review Barry! We can't wait to welcome you back next time!

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: I went for the first time with a friend and the staff was very attentive and friendly. They were checking on us every time, asking if we needed anything. My friend ordered calamari and she really liked the food (i just stack with the wine). The place is decorated amazingly and it has this Irish-Spanish vibes that we liked a lot. We will come back for sure :)
owner_answer:
Hi Beatriz, 
Thank you for your lovely feedback & review! We are so happy to hear about your positive experience in the Market Bar! We will be sure to pass on all of your compliments to our staff! 
Thank you again and we hope to see you very soon! 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Visited as a group of seventeen as part of a hen weekend. Turned up to find I had made a mistake and booked the wrong day - the staff were absolutely amazing and accommodated us with friendliness and professionalism.
The tapas sharing menu was superb- a good mix of vegetarian and meat options and generous portions. Brought out as it cooked but close enough together to enjoy a taste of everything.
Prices were fair for the portions given.
Highly recommended for any tapas fans visiting Dublin!
owner_answer:
Hi Saul, 
We are so delighted that you enjoyed your dining experience with us at The Market Bat, and that our food and service lived up to your expectations.

We take great pride in using only the freshest ingredients and preparing each dish with care, and it's always rewarding to hear that our efforts are appreciated. Your kind words mean a lot to us and we look forward to welcoming you back soon for another delightful meal!

Thanks again for your kind feedback & review. 

Kind regards, 
Kate

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Incredibly overpriced for average tasting food. Paid ‚Ç¨100 between two people and left hungry. Chicken salad was just a bunch of rice with 3 pieces of chicken. Positives: staff were lovely and the venue has a vibe but would not go back
owner_answer:
Hi Rodrigo,

To apologise we would love to invite you back in with our compliments, please email us over on feedback@marketbar.ie and you will be looked after there. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Went last night for the first time in a while and was quite disappointed. The Market Bar used to be a firm favourite of mine. The staff were not very attentive, and there was an automatic 12.5% service charge added to our bill. We were only a table of two and received minimal service. I should have argued this at the time but didn't. Won't be in a rush to return, unfortunately.
owner_answer:
Hi Jennifer,

The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Very over priced group menu. Not worth the price. Staff repeatedly forgot drinks orders. Bottomless bravas were being scrimped on, total 5 bowls for 15 people. The meatballs were the only thing everybody liked and they gave 20 meatballs between 15 people so mostly 1 each. Overall nobody at our table would recommend or return.
owner_answer:
Hi Sarah, 
Thank you for leaving your review. 
We are so sorry to hear that you had an unpleasant experience with us at the Market Bar. This is not the impression that we want to leave on our customers and your comments will be passed onto management to ensure that they are discussed. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Although most of my trip to Ireland is a blur, too many trips to Temple Bar ü§üü§§ the one thing that stayed clear is how good the food was! Never heard of Beans and Mash until I got there and now I'm addicted! Market Bar mixes all of Ireland into one, bottomless booze and amazing food! I definitely suggest hopping over there on any trip through Dublin!ü§üü§§üçÄüçª
owner_answer:
Hi Michael,
Thank you so much for your kind 5 star review! We hope to welcome you back to the Market Bar very soon!
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: We visited a couple of weeks ago and after reading the recent reviews was a little hesitant but we had a voucher so gave it a go.The staff were lovely, very friendly and great with our 1yr old daughter. Food took 45mins for the first dish to come out which we subsequently sent back. The rest of the food came out and was warm and the portion sizes small for the price. Having read previous reviews about food poisoning, I was very careful in checking the food. Unfortunately when my daughters food came out, the chicken was warm to touch and ice cold on the inside. Staff apologised and replaced the dish. At the end of the meal they took her dish and my soft drink off of the bill. Will we return 'no' but do I hope things improve to what was a great tapas restaurant.
owner_answer:
Hi Suzie, 

Thank you for sharing your experience at the Market Bar restaurant. I'm sorry to hear that your visit did not meet your expectations, and that you had some issues with the food and the wait time.

It's great to hear that our staff were friendly and accommodating towards your 1-year-old daughter, and that they made amends by taking your daughter's dish and your soft drink off the bill.

I understand your hesitation to return to the restaurant, but I hope that the Market Bar can address the issues you've mentioned and improve the quality of their food and service in the future.

Thank you for taking the time to leave a review, and I hope you'll have better dining experiences in the future.

Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: I found service very slow. Staff member is quick to take drink orders, but when it came to food, it took ages for them to come back. I think price for food was overpriced as well for portions you get. Mix up in our order did not help as well. Overall nice place bit overpriced but good food and nice atmosphere.
owner_answer:
Hi there, 

Thank you for taking the time to provide us with your feedback. We apologize for the slow service you experienced during your visit. We always strive to ensure that our guests receive prompt and attentive service, and we are sorry that we fell short on this occasion. We will be reviewing our processes and providing further training to our staff to improve our service speed.

Regarding the price of our food, we understand that our prices may not suit everyone's budget, and we apologize if you felt the portions were not adequate. We always aim to provide our guests with high-quality, fresh ingredients and to ensure that our menu items are priced fairly.

We appreciate your positive comments about our food and atmosphere, and we are pleased that you enjoyed these aspects of your visit. We take all feedback seriously, and we will use your comments to improve our offerings and service for future guests. 

Thank you again for your feedback, and we hope to have the opportunity to welcome you back soon.

Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Great service and delicious food!! We ordered 2 small tapas patatas bravas and nachos - they were quite a big portions... you can share them like proper tapas. And 2 big tapas- lamb koftas with couscous- which was full of amazing flavours and calamari that were melting in my mouth... For dessert we had churros...  Lunch was delicious and staff was super nice. Also they have a great deal where you can choose one small and one big tapas for 17euros. Will be back soon definitely !

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Would not recommend at all. We weren‚Äôt told that dishes could not be served a la carte until we were ordering, so we ended up spending far more per person than we intended. Some of the food was fine, but mostly it was unremarkable or just bad (I was really excited for the chicken skewers but they were tasteless). The service charge was odd too, and with our bad experience, we opted not to pay it.
owner_answer:
Hi Toby, 
Thank you for leaving your review with some feedback. We are deeply sorry to hear that you had a disappointing experience here with us at the Market Bar, this is not the standard that we aim for and your comments will be passed straight onto management to be dealt with. 
We would like to offer you to come back in with our compliments as an apology on behalf of the team. 
If you could please email us on feedback@marketbar.ie you will be looked after there. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
I had a great time last Friday having dinner in The Market Bar with my friends.
The food and the drinks were amazing!
Giselle our waitress was kind and quickly.
I also love the bathroom decoration, the music and the beautiful lights hanging in the restaurant
Lovely place to go, I highly recommend
owner_answer:
Thank you for the lovely 5 star review Emily, we are so happy that you enjoyed your experience with us at the Market Bar. We will make sure we pass on your praises to the staff & Giselle.
We hope to welcome you back to the Market bar very soon!
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Very nicely decorated and the staff were extremely friendly. The food portion sizes were slightly larger than a usual Tapas dish.. Sharing portions are larger than expected.
The food was tasty and cocktails were 10/10. Family friendly and also a nice place to celebrate any type of occasion.
owner_answer:
Hi Devansh, 
Thank you kindly for leaving your review and kind feedback! We are so delighted that you had a positive experience here with us at the Market Bar. We look forward to welcoming you back again soon!
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Large group and had to have the sharer menu. Not enough of some dishes came. Only 1 portion of prawns meatballs and chicken so I didn't get any of some of those. Apparently they were nice.
What I had was nice. Good atmosphere and food was quick.
owner_answer:
Hi Claire, 
Thank you for leaving your review and feedback! We are so sorry that you didn't get enough food for everyone around the table, this shouldn't have happened and it will be passed onto our head chef to ensure its dealt with. 
We are delighted that you enjoyed your experience in the end and we hope to see you back again soon here at the Market Bar.
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Tried the Market bar during covid and it wasn't great and unfortunately it hasn't improved. Nachos unfortunately terrible. The salsa and guacamole looked like something from a jar and tasted terrible. The calamari was nice but again nothing special. Fish tacos were very plain. Meatballs ‚Ç¨13 euro for five and again nothing special. Got the churros to finish and probably the worst I've ever had! To top it off 12.5% gratuity added to EVERY bill! Seems like management know the food is bad but are doing nothing to improve it. Honestly, don't visit here there's much nicer places to eat.
owner_answer:
Hi Alan,

Thank you for taking the time to share your review and provide feedback on your recent experience at the Market Bar. We want to express our sincere apologies for not meeting your expectations during your visit, as well as on subsequent occasions.

Please rest assured that your feedback is extremely valuable to us. We have shared your comments with our management and chefs, and we are actively working to address the issues you raised. Our main focus is to enhance the quality of our dishes, specifically the nachos, salsa, guacamole, fish tacos, meatballs, and churros.

As a gesture of apology, we would like to invite you back to the Market Bar as our guest. We truly value your patronage and would be delighted to have the opportunity to make amends. If you would like to take advantage of this offer, kindly reach out to us via email at feedback@marketbar.ie, and we will ensure you are well taken care of.

Once again, we genuinely appreciate your honest feedback, and we sincerely hope that you will consider giving us another chance in the future. It is our utmost goal to provide you with an exceptional dining experience that reflects the true quality and taste we strive to offer.

Thank you for your understanding, and we look forward to the opportunity to serve you better.

Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: The ambiance is great. Food is not at the expected level. I suspect they heavily use these microwave / oven. It‚Äôs easy to see with chicken meat. But worth a visit.
owner_answer:
Hi MJ, 
Thank you for leaving your review and feedback. We appreciate your comments on the food as we are always trying to improve on areas where we can. 
We hope you enjoyed your time with us otherwise and we do wish to see you again very soon. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Great place for a quick tapas if you are in the city centre. Everything was delightful and tasty especially buttermilk aubergine. I recommend getting 2 tapas plates per person. Usually busy but a big place so you might have luck and just walk in.
owner_answer:
Hi Sonja,
Thank you so much for your kind positive 5 star review! We are delighted that you enjoyed everything and we hope to see you again very soon!
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Pablo made sure our family reunion with the American cousins was a special one. He was attentive, knowledgeable about the food (coeliac in the group), and very friendly. Thanks to all for a great evening.
owner_answer:
Hi Grainne, 
Thank you for your kind review and feedback. We are delighted to hear that you had such a wonderful experience here at the Market Bar. We will be sure to pass your kind words onto Pablo, I'm sure he will be delighted as are we! We love the photo too!
Thanks again, Grainne. We look forward to welcoming you back to the Market Bar very soon. 
Kind regards,
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Great place with nice food and drinks on the menu.

Tapas were tasty as well as our Mojito. However, the price of the cocktail was a bit on a higher side and I did not expect it until we received the receipt.

All in all, staff is very friendly, Covid rules well respected  and would definitely recommend to anyone who wants to enjoy some lovely tapas with drinks in the area.

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Had table booked at 4:15 and arrived at 4pm, plenty of space inside. In terms of Covid, bathrooms were very clean and hand santiser on each food table. There are also a lot of tables outside, super nice if the weathers lovely. Great drink menu, ordered a jar of sangria for ‚Ç¨36 which was enough to fill up six glasses, so three each. Ordered dinner deal which is ‚Ç¨23 for one small and one large tapas, so we ended up sharing all four meals. Ordered: croquettes (very yummy highly recommended), bruschetta with aubergines and zucchini, calamari and best part of the meal - chicken wings. These wings were so gorgeous, hot and dipped in honey, nom! I love my chicken wings so I always know if they're fresh, which they definitely were. Great place to come for food if you want to try many dishes at ones with friends, great tunes also! We were allowed to stay for 1 hour 45 mins and then had to leave but i will take that over lockdown any day!!!
Thanks so much to the whole team
owner_answer:
Thank you Paula for your very welcome and detailed review. We are delighted to read it!
Rory
The Market Bar

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Unfortunately, we caught food poisoning... which kept us up all night and which is why we had to spend the next day in bed.

The evening itself was nice, great location, delicious food but unfortunately a few hours later my boyfriend and I were already worried about food poisoning.

We haven't found another review on the subject either, so we're wondering if this was a one-time thing? Did anyone else get food poisoning 03.04.2023?
owner_answer:
Hi Lucina, 

I'm sorry to hear that you experienced food poisoning after dining at our restaurant. We take food safety and hygiene very seriously, and we apologize for any discomfort or inconvenience this may have caused you.

We would like to assure you that we have thoroughly investigated your report of food poisoning and have taken all necessary steps to address the issue. We have reviewed our food handling and preparation procedures and made adjustments where necessary to ensure that all food is prepared and served in accordance with the highest standards of hygiene and safety.

While we cannot comment on the experiences of other customers, we appreciate you bringing this matter to our attention so that we can take appropriate action to prevent any future occurrences.

We're glad to hear that you enjoyed the location and found our food delicious. We hope that you will give us another chance to provide you with a positive dining experience in the future. Please don't hesitate to contact us if you have any further concerns or questions on feedback@marketbar.ie

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: To be honest, I hated every item of food we got. This place only gets two stars for the fact the staff were nice and the atmosphere is nice in the restaurant, but the food is awful. We ordered off the dinner menu and got the chicken skewers, nachos, patatas bravas and the bread to start. The bread was stale and the dip it came with was flavorless. The patatas bravas were soggy flavorless potatoes with some kind of cold tomatoe sauce and some other white sauce on top of them. They tasted of nothing but wet spuds. The nachos were mediocre at best. The cheese tasted so artificial and it was bright orange and the nachos were all soggy. The chicken came out barely cooked and with no seasoning on it, just grilled chicken and some yellow sauce that was apparently ‚Äúsaffron aioli‚Äù that tasted like mustard. Overall I hated the food and the fact a 12.5% service charge is charged on every table doesn‚Äôt make me want to like this restaurant any more. Wouldn‚Äôt recommend for food, Okay place for drinks however the drinks are more expensive than most places. A pint of Guinness was 7‚Ç¨. Save your money.
owner_answer:
HI Ailis, 

Thank you for taking the time to leave us a review and your feedback. 
We are so sorry to hear that you didn't enjoy your experience here at the Market Bar. It's always disappointing to receive negative feedback, but it's important to hear both positive and negative comments in order to improve our overall experience for future customers. Thank you for highlighting the friendliness of the staff and the atmosphere of the restaurant.

We take all feedback seriously, particularly regarding the quality of our food. We will review our menu items and ingredients to ensure that the quality of our food meets the standards that we pride ourselves on. We apologize for the stale bread, soggy patatas bravas, and artificial cheese on the nachos. This is not the standard that we aim for and we will work to improve in these areas.

We hope that you will consider giving us another chance in the future. If you do, please email us over on feedback@marketbar.ie and we will look after you from there. 

Thank you again for your feedback. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text: Horrible experience, menu is detailed with dietary / gluten free options but it ended up being all highly cross contaminated. We were a table of 4 and opted for the dinner menu. First they had ‚Äúrun of‚Äù sangria and then of the patata brava, which were supposed be all you eat. Its a shame that such a location, and beautiful settings, can‚Äôt cope with the bookings on a Sunday night of a bank holiday. Disappointed!
owner_answer:
Hi Serena, 

We are very sorry to hear about your disappointing experience at the Market Bar. We strive to provide all of our customers with the highest quality food and service, and it seems like we fell short during your visit.

We take all dietary requirements seriously, and we apologize for any cross-contamination that occurred during the preparation of your meal. We will be reviewing our processes and ensuring that our staff is fully trained to handle dietary requirements correctly and safely.

We always aim to ensure that our guests have a memorable dining experience and we will take steps to ensure that this does not happen again.

We appreciate your feedback, and we will use it to improve our service and offerings for future guests. We hope that you will give us another opportunity to show you our commitment to providing excellent food and service.

We would like to invite you back in with our compliments to apologise, if you could please contact us on feedback@marketbar.ie and you will be looked after there. 

Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Going to the Market Bar in group was a really disappointing experience.

Besides the drinks we drank, we had no options whatsoever. Due to the Group Menu, we felt like in school where you have to eat the meal of the day.

And the best we got from the staff was a very condescending comment from the manager saying "you received an email with all the conditions". Honestly, as a constructive feedback, it is not reasonable to think that a group of 12 people will happily take a compulsory menu just because someone tells you that "everything was explained in an email". Especially if there is just one person out of the 12 who received the email.

Very rigid experience with just alright food.
owner_answer:
Hi Javier, 
Thank you for taking the time to share your experience at the Market Bar.  I'm sorry to hear that your experience was not satisfactory. It is important to us that all of our customers feel valued and have an enjoyable experience. 
We understand that having limited options and a compulsory menu can be frustrating, especially when dining with a group but to serve large groups we need to have a limited menu so our kitchen doesn't get overwhelmed and we apologise for the inconvenience that this may have caused.

We would like to invite you back into the Market Bar with our compliments with a table for 2 to make up for this experience , please email us over on feedback@marketbar.ie and you will be looked after there. 
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: The Market Bar Restaurant
review_text:
Very disappointed Sunday lunch
We assumed as booked we got lunch set deal - order one main and side tapas -( where supposed to get Brad and dips they didn‚Äôt arrive ) potato newbas where really bad - dry - not nice - prawns again where not great - fish tacos - ok nothing great - automatically service charge for 5 people but unusual and lunch deal wasn‚Äôt on menu which was weird as that‚Äôs what we booked  - overall very disappointing!  Wouldn‚Äôt be back ..
owner_answer:
Hi Paul, 
Thank you for sharing your feedback regarding your recent Sunday lunch experience at our restaurant. We deeply apologize for the disappointments you encountered during your visit, and we appreciate you bringing these issues to our attention.

Regarding the food, we are so sorry that it did not meet your expectations, We strive to deliver consistently high-quality dishes, and we apologize for falling short on this occasion. Your feedback will be shared with our kitchen team to address these concerns and improve the quality of our offerings.
We are truly sorry for failing to meet your expectations during your visit. 

Your feedback is valuable to us, and we would love the opportunity to make it right. We would love to invite you back for a complimentary meal on us if you could please email us over on feedback@marketbar.ie and you will be looked after there.
Kind regards, 
The Market Bar Group

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
I really enjoyed the Sunday Roast chicken. I dropped in for an early dinner to avoid a thunderstorm and had a Sunday Roast and they were able to seat immediately.

The chicken was perfectly cooked, seasoned well and juicy and the trimmings were very tasty ~ very flavorful greens and carrots, well cooked potatoes and stuffing. I was underwhelmed by the sides (skinny fries and classic stuffing, but I think I may have received Yorkshire pudding instead), so I'd skip those in the future.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: The environment is very nice. It feels upscale, clean, and cozy. However, just based on the quality of the food I wouldn't necessarily recommend it to anyone. You can get much better food elsewhere for much cheaper. I also wouldn't say the service is extraordinary just mediocre.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Cozy spot with nice wine-list and dinner menu. Our group ordered the shepherd pie, half chicken, and steaks, bread with butter and steamed orange cake. Superb! Used open table app for reservations. Friendy staff wiith fantastic recommenations.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Can observe a decline in food quality and value for your Euro from years ago, but still very good service and one of the best atmospheres in Dublin.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely incredible food, very reasonably priced (3 courses x2, a bottle of wine and 2 cocktails for ‚Ç¨100). The only issue I had was when we arrived the person who seated us was quite snappy and rude but the other serving staff were very pleasant. Would definitely recommend it and will be returning.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: There is a huge problem in the service and behaviour of the staff. Foods were ok, not super tasty. For price/performance it is only 2 stars.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Best desserts ever! Deep fired courgette and mozzarella was a delight. The service was great. Value for money for sure. Don't get to the city much but can't wait to go back to Brasserie Sixty6.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: The interior was very nice and cozy, it had a jazz club kind of vibe. When we went there it was a very busy night but despite that the service was relatively speedy and the food was good! If you like Smokey kind of flavour and kind of dark then you‚Äôll definitely like this. We ordered the pork belly as a starter - it was nice but it could have been softer. I had the burger and my boyfriend had the bacon roast. The burger could have been sweeter and spicier but the fries were delicious. The bacon roast however was amazing - tender and crispy and tasty and the mash was absolutely gorgeous but do yourself a favour and ask to change the sauce to a peppercorn one instead - it‚Äôll taste a lot better. However for what the food was, it‚Äôs definitely overpriced and not worth it. There‚Äôs a lot of restaurants nearby that are cheaper and better, we only stumbled upon this place because every other place we tried was fully booked

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Went for a work dinner. Was impressed by menu good range if options and some interesting twists. Enjoyed the food especially liked the celeriac soup - service was fine and friendly. Only down side was the atmosphere - place was completely empty on a Thursday evening - might be a benefit for a larger group but for our table felt a bit echoey

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Went there to have dinner on our wedding anniversary. Had beer/cocktails, chicken wings & parfait and shepherd's pie in mains. First of all they took years to deliver our food, like one hour we were waiting for mains after starter. Parfait is very bad. They did mention something about anniversary dessert 0 eur but we have never received. Didnt wait to waste time to order desserts. Overall it's a bad experience for a place where they charge 10 eur for this kind of service. Sick. Not again and will not suggest anyone. Thanks.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Irish breakfast and veggie irish breakfast. Both okay, but I don't think quality and price matched. Portions were really big, but I prefer quality over quantity. Huge plus from juice/smoothie, those were really refreshing.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
It was my first time in Brasserie Sixty6 and definitely won‚Äôt be my last! The service was impeccable, the atmosphere is warm and inviting and there was a lovely buzz there last Friday afternoon. The food is possibly the best I‚Äôve tasted in a long time.
Igor, Aaron, Daniel and Donna were so lovely and accommodating! Thank you!

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Place is cool and staff was nice.
Food was the problem: it's unacceptable to pay 13 euro for a Burrata and being served just a slice of it.
The rib eye was one of the worst eaten in Ireland, for the same price (34 euro) you can eat way better somewhere else.
The dessert was fine.
I think I won't come back

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Out of all the places we had dinner in Dublin, Sixty6 was the most expensive. We don't mind spending a little extra when eating out, but the service and the food need to be worth the extra dime.
This was not the case at Sixty6. The food was okay, not great. It was not very flavourful and it was a long wait before we got our food. The waiters in the restaurant were not very friendly. It felt a bit like we weren't welcome there.
It could have just been a bad day to visit, but we did not have a great experience here. The restaurant itsself does look very nice on the inside.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Staff is very important!!! Specially this place. It is amazing with their high quality dinner

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Ridiculously overpriced. Three of us dined last night - we ordered 2 starters and 2 chateaubriands between 3 of us - 3 cocktails and 2 glasses of wine - the bill was over ‚Ç¨300. ‚Ç¨77 for each of the steaks alone, no sides or sauces included, and they were grand, nothing special, all the sides were extra and small portions. They also charged ‚Ç¨7 for 2 tiny ramekins of pepper sauce. Also charged a service charge of 12.5% for 3 people. Won‚Äôt be going back in a hurry.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Over all I would recommend this place.
Their version of Shepard's pie was a bit disappointing.  Not a style I've had elsewhere in Ireland during our trip.
The coffee martini was the best I've ever had.
The roasted chicken was amazing.
I recommend.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Shocking experience.
Booked well in advance for a table of 6 people for a special anniversary meal. Arrived on time at 8pm, shown to our table right at the door, beside where the waitress greets customers so asked if we could move as we saw a large table free towards the back. They told us to sit and wait & then eventually moved us. Our starters didn‚Äôt arrive to 9pm. And main courses 10.10pm. The mains arrived with a burnt burger bun, cold chips and cold veg. Asked if they could be reheated & they did come back out fresh & fairly quickly. But the whole night to be honest was a shambles. No waitresses around to ask for things, no one came to ask for extra drinks/ to see if all was ok. I understand on a Saturday night they are busy but have more staff on or else don‚Äôt accept a large table at 8pm. Don‚Äôt recommend as there are a lot of other better options in Dublin City Centre.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Had dinner here with my Mother & some family & our waiter had literally no interest in serving us as he was flirting with a group of girls on the next table to us! He rushed us thru our order & didn‚Äôt even ask us about drinks as I had to call him back to order drinks!
Absolutely no one came back to our table after that & I really wanted more drinks but instead all the staff stood gossiping out loud at the til area. I had to walk to the till to ask for our bill & I did complain & told them their lack of service was really really bad & this was to be a special meal for my mother - I was disgusted to say the least.
