I have since written to them but got no answer at all.
So I for one will never set foot in the place again!

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Disappointed, if I‚Äôm honest. The interior was nice and it was clean but it stops there. We both had the bangers and mash which was very salty. The service wasn‚Äôt bad but wasn‚Äôt great. Definitely was not made to feel welcome and felt like they wanted us in and out quite quickly. Disappointed given the amount we paid, wouldn‚Äôt recommend.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Food was good, very little in vegan options so not great for myself. All the food looked very good and was very well presented. Staff were very helpful and tried their best to accommodate.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Food was pretty good, drinks were decent. Staff wasn't the best and we didn't like the atmosphere. Overall okay but wouldn't return or recommend.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: The food was great. I liked the entree, the sirloin and the desert. I went there for a corporate event and it was jam packed. I only gave them a four star review, because the desert only came when half my table had left‚Ä¶ Yes the restaurant was full, but they should have been prepared since the reservations were done with over a week‚Äôs notice.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: The one waiter we had was rude although the rest seemed nice enough. Pork belly and burger was fairly bland. Best part was the bread and butter.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Lovely piece of serenity off the busy main Street. Delicious meal, good wine and fine service. Tried the chicken & steak. Also the tiramisu and panacota. Everything was good.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Nice food, good service but a 12.5% Service Charge added to our bill has left a sour taste. We are regular tippers but felt this was a little cheeky being a party of only 2. Will think twice about returning.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: This is a gorgeous place. Really classy place in the heart of Dublin City Centre. The food is really well thought out and offers set menus as well as a la carte. We use the place regularly in our travel club and they are kind enough to give us a portion of our tab back in the form of travel points, which makes the decision to eat in the gorgeous place a bonus.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: We were looking for a place to have a brunch the morning after our wedding for all of our guests and this place was recommended by our wedding coordinator. They were very helpful in putting together the brunch we were looking for and the food was amazing!

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Staff was amazing   very nice and friendly   however food wasn't that good,  just the salad (very small for the price) but not the main dish which was a cauliflower risotto.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: food was fantastic. but for the price, i expect more attentive and speedy service. friendly though.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Had the nicest time here. Atmosphere was so lovely, food was stunning! Definitely get a margarita if you‚Äôre going. Cassio was the nicest waiter who looked after us so well. Couldn‚Äôt recommend!

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
The food and cocktails were very good. However we waited 15 minutes to get our places (no problem here, it happens, but without any explanation or people coming and talking to us) and after ordering we waited one hour to get our plates - the food arrived cold with no excuses or explanation.

too bad...

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Cosy place
Good food, little bit on the saly side but still delicious!

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Very good kitchen and very friendly staff. We had a sirlion and a rainbow trout for starters. Both dishes were very well seasoned, with a glass of Malbec - excellent!

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Nice place with great food and lovely staff.
Strongly recommend!
We had lunch here twice, amazing sandwich and salad:)

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: This is a really excellent all round restaurant. The focus here is on delicious food and it hits the spot with every course. We had the set menu with white wine tonight. The calamari was amazing, the mains especially the fish was cooked to perfection. The atmosphere is well thought out. The service was top class. Must eat.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
There is a very welcoming atmosphere here.
Great for groups as well as couples.
Every dish looked and tasted delicious, wonderful brunch menu.
Staff efficient and helpful at all times.
Will be visiting again.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: The dinner was delicious and very well served, I loved the cocktails especially the cherry boom! Tomahawk super recommended and more if you ask for it with bearnaise sauce and smash potato as a side accompanied by the wine they have from Argentina, mascota or something like that is the name of the wine. For dessert I recommend the ice cream to finish off your delicious dinner. The service was very good considering it was Saturday night and it was super full, very nice waiters, I think the name was jack or something like that. Personal recommendation: make a reservation especially if it is Friday/Saturday.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Table next to the door, so already off to a rocky start. Food was poor quality, orders were wrong too. Took close to 15 mins for all the ordered mains to arrive, meaning food was cold once everything was there. Had to ask for cutlery each course also. Just poor all round to be honest.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Came for valentine's while visiting the city. Very nice food. Service was good and decor was nice. Good range of cocktails. Pricey cocktails but well made. Would recommend and come again.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
What an amazing experience
Greeted by two very professional hosts 1 short balding and dapper a used car salesman type and 1 tall and handsome with flowing locks, from there we were taken on a journey we hadn't quite expected from such an unassuming facade, a culinary delight with service to match‚Ä¶‚Ä¶
I wish i could award six stars they were that good‚Ä¶..well done Dylanüëèüëèüëè and team

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Slightly more upscale restaurant bar. Service is very attentive and trying their best but very busy and thus a little slow. The food is slightly expensive, but very good and diverse (can range from local traditional to more fancy). I would recommend the menu which is, all in all, a better deal than ordering single dishes. Portions are very big depending on what you order.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely fantastic restaurant.  Food was second to none, and the service is excellent.  Highly recommended üëå

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Beautiful ambient restaurant
But expensive - a rib eye steak and chips (no veg) is euro 32.50 - that's way too much! The same meal in a fancy restaurant in Berlin is 18 euros
Rip off Ireland still well and truly here!

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Staff were very friendly and the meat eaters in our group were very happy. The vegetarians, less so. Veggie options very limited and the gnocchi were a big disappointment.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Beautiful restaurant and good atmosphere. Food is a mix bag. Chicken wings are sensational, fries are delicious and all desserts went down great. But the mains were so average. Pork belly was nice but the sauce had absolutely no flavour. The ‚Ç¨34 ribeye tastes like charcoal, whatever seasoning on it was burnt and tasteless and  the fat wasn't rendered down at all, just blackened from burning it quickly. The chicken was dry and the potatoes were rock hard. Cocktails were good and the staff were friendly but considering the 12.5% service charge for our table the service was so average and slow. Absolutely nothing they did deserved the automatic ‚Ç¨73 tip from our table.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: Very nice food, great atmosphere friendly staff. Had the evening menu at 39‚Ç¨, duck leg was a small and kind of weird dish. Main course the rib eye was great, can recommend that. The rom raisin ice was great, but that's one of my favorites anywhere. All in all a nice place, a bit loud music thou for talking during dinner.

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text: We came here using a thetaste.ie voucher, which  allowed us to have 3 courses, a bottle of wine and a welcome cocktail, we were able to switch our wine for a bottle of ros√® and pay the different  which was decent of them. The food was excellent and the service was tip notch. I would highly recommend you try dining here sometime

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Food was absolutely amazing as always ,top class....
But the service we had from particular staff was OMG....
Big apologies Brasserie66 management for bringing this out.
Our group of 13 persons on 28.01.2023@5pm
Best wishes

name: Brasserie Sixty6 Restaurant
review_text:
Great atmosphere, the service was great. They're drinks and cocktails were excellent

Food came out in good time and was all well presented and very enjoyable.

For starters I had the mushroom soup, highly recommend it. With some parmesan olive oil and pickled enoki mushrooms it really was an excellent soup

The catch of the day was very well presented with baby potatoes, black olives sun-dried tomatoes and grapefruit, although being a little bit dry it was still a very excellent dish and would get it again.

For a busy city centre restaurant the standard of quality was very noticeable for everything from the food to the service to the restaurant setting.

Would highly recommend

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Restaurant was a short distance from our hotel and therefore was a easy dinner option for the evening. Heads up if you have minors with you you must make a reservation before 7pm as this restaurant strictly follows the rules that any restaurant serving alcohol does not allow children inside after 9pm. Had the Cod with beans and it was plentiful. Hubby had the curry which he thoroughly enjoyed. Also live music which is a nice added touch.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: This place‚Äôs interior is absolutely beautiful. Food is amazing. From the main dish to the dessert, it keeps getting tastier and beautiful. We were 6 to visit. However, you need to reserve in advance. We struggled to reserve for two consecutive days but eventually were able to book a table after. I would absolutely recommend it if you‚Äôre visiting Dublin. The waitress was super open and welcoming. Also, don‚Äôt expect it to be calm dining, there is always music and dancing happening on the ground floor. Price wise acceptable, we paid around 50‚Ç¨/person and each person had a drink, main dish and dessert.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
We had a great time on both of our visits!
Our waiter William was fantastic! He was so attentive and personable, so much so that we specifically asked for him the second time.
He also gave us a list of towns to visit on our next trip to Italy. He went above and beyond and exceeded our expectations!
Each visit we then sat at the bar for a few night caps after dinner. The bartenders were the best in Dublin!
Very professional, entertaining, and we were impressed by the precision of their work, like a fine oiled machine. Hats off to the Bar Manager, he also engaged in conversation with us.
The food was delicious, especially the mango & lime chicken wing appetizer. Best wings ever! I ordered them on both visits.
The Restaurant Manager (the gentleman with the beard) was so friendly and helpful, he answered all our questions.
Thank you to everyone at The Church for making our nights special!
The entire hard working staff deserve kudos.
If you‚Äôre visiting Dublin, I highly recommend you put the Church as #1 on your to-do list!

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Are you in Dublin? Then you must experience the Church Cafe. Stunning atmosphere. Great history. Personable staff. Great food selection. We focused in specialty cocktails, seafood appetizers  and broad range of dinners. Whether two of you or 15 like us. Totally worthwhile.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
I had been curious about the Church for some time now because of the unique atmosphere. The vibe of the place definitely lived up to the hype and the cocktails we ordered were pretty good. We also saw some traditional Irish dancing, which was fun.

That being said it was VERY busy (hard to find seating) and it was on the pricier side. I would say it's good to see and have a drink at once, but then find a cheaper place.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: The Church is a must stop in Dublin. Their food and drinks are fantastic. The atmosphere is amazing. And the Irish Step dancing and music on Sundays is the icing on the cake. Plan ahead and make reservations.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Generally a good place to have some mostly good food. The quality does not deserve the price however. Don‚Äôt buy the steak.

Pros:
Old church, beautiful architecture, nice vibe with live singing, playing and dance, some of the things on the menu are good.

Cons:
Service is a bit lacking, not frequent or attentive enough (but friendly and helpful), the steak was an insult to steak-lovers (DO NOT ORDER THE STEAK - I literally had to spit out 25% of it because it was so tough and unpalatable), the cocktails are alright but a bit watered down and lacking substance (no professional bar, just employees who do a good job imitating a good bar).

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: One of the most interesting dining experiences ever. The restaurant/pub is located inside of an old church. The atmosphere is great, there is live Irish music and dancing Sunday to Thursday. The food is tasty and the service is great. Can truly recommend a visit here if you are in Dublin. If you want to be there for the live music and dances it‚Äôs best to book a table in advance as it can get crowded.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Had dinner as part of a group while visiting Dublin. Reservation seems a must as few people in front turned away as so busy. Building is beautifully lit and decorated retaining many original features. Service was great and we had a table in the celler bar. Not as noisy as the open area, very nice booths and bar down there a more relaxed dining experience. Food was good, not fine dining by any means but was great and solid choice. Staff very helpful, service was fast and food was well presented. Highly recommend a visit as building is beautiful along with its history

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Visually, an amazing restaurant. It‚Äôs quite large with different sections, so if you want to sit in a particular part it‚Äôs best to email them before you arrive for your reservation.

Lots of vegan options, and a large drinks selection. The place is pretty busy, so service can be a bit slow, but otherwise everything was pretty good.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Great place to come for entertainment, drinks, and decent food. The Guinness is good here, and the staff do what they can though they seem understaffed. Reservations recommended.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Very cool site. A historic church that has been made into a restaurant. They had excellent live traditional music and also they have Irish dancing (I was seated too far away to see the dancing but the music was fabulous). Great cocktail and menu selection with some delicious food to treat yourself. A bit spendy but great for a night out! I enjoyed the "peachy blinders" cocktail, the plum Guinness ribs, and the buffalo chicken fries. Great for date night as well, romantic location with stellar servers.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Fantastic building with a really wonderful retrofit. Not a bad seat in the place. My nachos were so-so which serves me right in some ways. My partners food looked wonderful, he had the stew.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: This was one of our Highlights when staying in Dublin. Live folk music, tap dancers, in a real church and good food (-1star because my chicken was a little dry) we had a blast here, you have to check out this place!

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: This famous cafe in Dublin occupies the former church where Arthur  Guinness was married. It preserves some of the decor of the church, including a pipe organ. The food is really good, although service was a little slow. Worth a visit.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: A must go in Dublin. A restaurant located on what used to be a church. Service is a bit chaotic due to the high volume of people, it took me 3 different requests to get a beer. Food is good although the proportions are a bit small.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Amazing. Great food, great service and great venue. Thoroughly recommended as a place to visit. We went on a pre-booked midweek evening meal in May, and we were shown quickly to our table, all the waiters were very good, and the food was faultless. The live music wasn't too loud from the gallery where we were seated.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Amazing restaurant. We were outside because the weather was nice, good atmosphere but the inside is beautiful too. Loved the concept it is a restaurant in a literal church. About our experience, we got fish and chips and it was absolutely fantastic. Strongly recommend it if you go to Dublin.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: What a great time here. ABBI was an absolute delight serving us the evening. I will certainly recommend this place for good food , ambiance and booze. But yes it does get very busy during weekends so preferably do make reservations and go

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Got intrigued by the church turn to restaurant. The alcohol whiskey was good, the lamb stew was so tender, and the calamari was superb. The best of the best is the spectacular service by IAN. Service with a warm smile sets the ambiance of a great meal.

Thank you Ian. Keep up the good work.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Awesome pub - 100% Irish. Really sensational decor of the premises and a one-of-a-kind atmosphere. There are original church organ played and created by Georg Friedrich Handel (including Messiah)!
The wonderful taste of perfectly poured Guinness. Nice, cultural and helpful service. I recommend to everyone!! wonderful taste of perfectly poured Guinness. I recommend to everyone!!

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: I really don't know how people don't give this  place 5 stars. From the start of our meal, I did the whiskey tasting and was guided through some Ireland distillery's. The waitress and bartender were amazing. They gave suggestions on different whiskeys to try. Then we had oysters, fish and chips, and a burger with very delicate meat. This was one of my favorite places in Dublin, and I will be going back.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Great place for dinner. The food was excellent - I had the lamb stew. The place is unique as it is in an old church‚Äîquite an exciting setting. Make sure you have a reservation; else it can be hard to get a table for dinner - especially during the weekend.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Great Ambiance and Tasty Food!

We recently dined at this restaurant and I must say, the ambiance was great! The church decor and interiors made the dining experience unique and memorable. We pre-booked a table for our group of 5 and we were seated promptly upon arrival. Our waitress was very attentive and friendly.

The food was delicious! They had a variety of vegetarian options and their vegan fried rice was an absolute delicacy. The cocktails were refreshing and beautifully presented. We thoroughly enjoyed our meals.

The bar area was also great with live Irish music playing throughout. We even got to see some tap dance which was an added bonus. The staff were very friendly and accommodating, making our dining experience even better.

Overall, I would highly recommend this restaurant. The combination of great ambiance, delicious food, and friendly staff makes it definitely worth a visit.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: We went there for lunch. We were not really convinced by the menu and the food itself but the staff was super friendly and welcoming and the place looks gorgeous inside. I think that we should probably go again but more for drinks than food that was basic but really expensive.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: I have visited The Church cafe a couple times so far. Definitely a spot to visit in Dublin. The venue is beautiful, service is great and food is good. My only concern is very limited offer of vegan options but they are alright. I hope to see more vegan alternatives in the future.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: We had a wonderful time here today. The food was exceptional, and Abbi provided excellent service! We definitely plan to revisit this place in the future.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
The service was fast and perfect, thanks to our server Leon who was just exceptional!! The food was just amazing! Really tasty and at a good price. The location is somewhat weird but it makes the experience really nice. The music is nice and traditional!!!
Overall the experience was excellent and I highly recommend this place!

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
It‚Äôs kind of one of those ‚ÄúMust Do‚Äù things when in Dublin I guess, but I think it‚Äôs a little over rated.
We each had the gluten-free‚ÄúTraditional Irish Stew‚Äù, along with a glass of Chardonnay and an Apperol for ‚Ç¨55, which seems a little steep. The Apperol was watery and the stew was rather bland. It all came at once within about 5 minutes of ordering, leaving little time to enjoy a conversation over drinks.
I guess you pay for the ambience which I admit was pretty cool, although the online photos make the church seem so much larger.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: The service is good, the atmosphere is great and the space itself makes up for the whole visit. Our dishes were tasty and everything ran smoothly. Book ahead, definitely with the visit whilst in Dublin

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: What a unique place‚Ä¶for a drink, for a meal, even to dance if you want in the club basement. Good food, pleasant service, nice entertainment.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Me and my friend were so excited to be there!! The food was very good, the live music and the dancers were amazing. The atmosphere is typically Irish, so I absolutely suggest it!

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
It's beautiful.
And great idea to turn a church into a colorful restaurant.
Our 2nd time drinking in a church, ( first time was in Amsterdam.)
But the food is just ok.
Service is just ok (maybe too busy.)
A bit disappointed.
Can't change seat.
Can't order food if you seat at bar.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Great atmosphere with Irish dancing. The food was good and the drinks were delicious. The service was however very slow and the waitress forgot about us after our main course, waited half an hour for the dessert menu which never arrived.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: I had seen this place already, a church transformed into a restaurant with terrace and a bar. Never stopped before today for lunch. Very agreeable surprise. Our salads were fresh and original. The service by a young lady was very nice, the cold rose wine on a hot day was as good as you can get. We will be back !

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Truly Amazing Place, different from any of the pubs in the city center. As the name suggests, it's an old Church, converted in a fantastic place to hangout. Food is delicious ( meat suggested ), cakes are very good. Booking suggested.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Amazing experience. The location is an actual church with a lot of charme and an impressive interior. The service is excellent and the food and drink is good for fair prices. You don't have to be formally dressed but shouldn't be dressed in joggers. My highlight was the irish music and dancing.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: This restaurant is nearby and looked interesting. We had a very short wait for a table, so we sat at the bar waiting. They do not serve food at the bar, so we just waited. Our table was prepared rapidly, but we were expecting a 40-minute wait. We had great service from our waitstaff. I ordered Market Fresh Fish and Chips, my wife ordered Grilled Cornfed Irish Chicken Supreme, and my son ordered the Chef's Special, which was Teriyaki Marinated Sea Bass. Food arrived at a reasonable period of waiting. Once it did, we all shared a bite with each other because we were impressed with the flavor of our entree. After our meal, we took advantage of the dessert special. Dessert and coffee for a good, low price. Overall, this was probably the best meal we have had this entire trip. This location is highly recommended!

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Lovely place, great atmosphere for a few drinks and a catch up but food is just OK.... nothing special and arrived just barely warm. Loaded chicken fries waste of money wouldn't order again. Prawns were cooked in hot sauce..bread was cold

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: This place is a pretty awesome stop. The food was good, drinks were good, dancing and music made for a great atmosphere. Oh and the building itself is amazing.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Warm, inviting, and steeped in history this cafe/pub/restaurant is the perfect stop! Lamb stew btw....amazing. But not nearly as fantastic as the music and the dancing. Get in early to get a good seat! We arrived at 5:30 and got seats right near the stage on a Tuesday.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Great place ! Went for a beer , but downstairs restaurant was not very busy - so decided to stay for food - great decision! The portion of mussels to share was huge! Will come back to try other things

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Have you ever eaten in an old church? Not me.
If this is not one of the most bizarre cafes/restaurant/bars then what is.
This place is amazing. Located in an old church with the organ still in place as well as the inscriptions on the walls. The old crypt is a bar while the inner church a cafe/restaurant.
If it is one place you should visit at least for a quick coffee is this.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
What a fun place!!! Upon arrival we noticed the beautiful features of this unique pub. The former church was bright and airy.
The entertainment was perfect for our last night in Ireland. They had traditional music with skilled Irish dancers. We enjoyed every set!
Our dinner was delicious. Service (Katie) was excellent. The food arrived fast and hot. The fish was so fresh. One of my dining companion commented the next day on how that was the best fish she had had.
This pub is on my must do for the next trip to Dublin.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Discovered this beautiful bar whilst on holiday in Dublin and the photos do not do it justice, came here for drinks and it was absolutely stunning inside and out and the drinks were slightly cheaper than most places we'd visited in Dublin. Would definitely recommend and come here again.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Loved it here! Entertainment was great, dancers and musicians were so enthusiastic and really made our evening. The service was amazing and food was great too. Recommend this place for anyone wanting a something a bit special.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Honestly one of the best meal I had in Dublin, the typical show was amazing, we had the luck to be in a good spot , staff is really helpful and the price is fair enough for the whole experience

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Lovely place, great cocktails. Food is splendid. Staff is friendly and the whole area is very nice.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: No wait and we're seated immediately. Peachy Blinder was huge and delicious. The had too much ice, though. The Chicken Supreme and Traditional Lamb stew melted in our mouths! After a day of walking in the city, topped our meal with the apple crumble and brownie and peanut butter. Both were flavorful. A scoop of ice cream with the crumble would have made it even better.

name: The Church Caf√©, Late Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Food was Lovely, great portion size on the mussels. Everything was very tasty and fresh.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: The place, the atmosphere and the food were great. We had the 3 courses menu at 60‚Ç¨. Everything was tasty, hot and perfectly seasoned/presented. The only small issue was the noise. It was very loud due to the amount of people inside, even though our table was booked for 9.15pm. Pity for a chic restaurant, which you expect to be calm and relaxing.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Great ambience, food was tasty. However, it did not meet my expectations with regard to the price. I ordered Sea Bass fillet, Scallops as main course which was good. For desserts, I had brownie and deconstructed pavlova - loved it. For cocktails, I had a mango drink, which was excellent. I was not served starters as I arrived a few minutes late for my reservation.
Service was good and friendly staff.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: We love seafood and wanted to find the the best place in Dublin. Sole was recommended by friends who had visited the city earlier this year. We are grateful for that recommendation since it was a perfect seafood dinner. Scallops, oysters,  sea bass were all perfectly prepared. Good wine selection of wines and our white was chilled to the ideal temperature. Service was great. We had an advance reservation which turned out to be the way to get in into this very popular restaurant. One of the few places I can highly recommend without any reservations.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
I am delighted to share my experience at SOLE Seafood & Grill, where every aspect of the dining experience was nothing short of exceptional. From the moment we stepped in, we were greeted with the warmth of the cloakroom service, which set the tone for the evening. Our table for two at the bar was the perfect vantage point to witness the masterful cocktail-making skills of the bartender. It was truly a work of art, and we were in awe.

The Tuna Tartar starter was elegantly presented and tasted even better than it looked. We paired it with a superb French Sauvignon bottle that complemented the dish impeccably. Our waiter was knowledgeable and attentive, making the dining experience even more memorable.

For our main courses, my partner opted for the Mussels with Creme White Wine Sauce, which was cooked to perfection and beautifully presented. Meanwhile, I savoured the Fish and Chips, which were generous in portion size and cooked to perfection. The flavours were exquisite, and I was thoroughly impressed with my meal.

The dessert selection was just as impressive as the rest of the menu, with a mouth-watering selection of ice creams, including vanilla baileys and pistachio. The kitchen staff went above and beyond by adding a special birthday message for my partner, complete with a candle and a baby meringue. It was a lovely touch that made the evening even more special.

The atmosphere in the restaurant was buzzing, and the manager's attention to detail and professionalism was exemplary. We left SOLE Seafood & Grill with a sense of satisfaction and can't wait to return. It was an experience that will linger in our memories for a long time.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Oysters were fantastic, scallops on point but mussels had a few bad smelly ones. I could smell the smelly mussels as it was served, am sure a chef could‚Äôve pick it up too.

Sole was beautifully done. Apart from the mussels, everything was delicious and beautifully cooked.

Wally was a very attentive server as well. Intuitive & brought us extra lemon wedges without me needing to ask as he saw the one served with the sole wasn‚Äôt enough. üëçüëç

As for the atmosphere, the hard walls bounced the vocals all around, making the space a tad too noisy.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Fabulous night last night at SOLE food amazing , Prawn cocktail so fresh , chargrilled tiger prawn( 2) so full of flavour  steaks cooked to perfection Fish of the day was Halibut it was fab , Prime Donna Cocktails and the service was exceptional from all the staff

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: We had an all round excellent experience with food, wine and Jonata who was attentive and discreet. We had oysters and scallops as starters. Main comprising moules frites and sea bass. A shared desert of spiced panna cotta all washed down with local beers and a South African Chardonnay. We will be back!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Wonderful dining experience from beginning to end. You can enjoy about 2 hours without being rushed before the next seating. We got a last minute reservation. Food is thoughtfully prepared and paired with sides. Come with an appetite because the portions are large!  I had the king scallops which were delicious but very rich.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Modern interior design. Professional and friendly team of people working there.
Definitely perfect place for a date or anniversary diner.
Very reasonable prices!
Food fresh and cooked to perfection!

Definitely will be going back.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Best beef carpaccio I‚Äôve tried in dublin city.
We went to celebrate my birthday, the food was fresh and up to the expectations. It is a bit pricy but totally worth it.
If you‚Äôre into raw food I highly recommend the oysters and the beef carpaccio!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Food was great and flavourful. Ideal for those who love fish. Staff friendly and nice. Unfortunately long wait inbetween courses and dirty plates sitting a long time at the table.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
I had a great Saturday lunch at Sole.
Took advantage of the set menu and enjoyed Oysters and an absolutely amazing Sea Bass, severed in a morish Thai curry cream, I had to get some extra bread the help mop up the sauce, I didn't want to leave any behind.

The service here was top notch, from when I walked in the door til when I payed my bill, the staff were attentive, Martin, my waiter, was great, I'd ordered a glass of wine to be served with the Bass and it was. Kudo to all the staff

I will be back

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: The best seafood restaurant that I've been to across a number of countries. For starters I recommend the scallops, the best I've had. For mains we had the SOLE Seafood Tower with a side of broccoli. Really good. I highly recommend this restaurant. The service was exceptional from start to end. The presentation of the food was delectable. We'll definitely beef back.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
My wife and I went here for dinner on a Sunday evening at 18:30. Restaurant was pretty full, and unfortunately that meant you were quite tightly packed in to your tables, so it felt a little bit like you were eating with another couple.  The food was fairly good. The dishes came with plenty of seafood, which all tasted nice.

Service let them down on this evening though. We were welcomed nicely at the front door, and taken straight to our seats.  The service from then was pretty average, certainly not the level you expect for the price you pay.  We ordered a bottle of wine, which never arrived, and at no point were we asked if we wanted anymore drinks. During the meal no one checked in to see if everything was okay, and despite my wife being clear about her allergies, she still had a very minor allergic reaction to the starter (nothing a benadryl couldn't sort straight away).

Overall the experience was okay, but for the price it felt a little lacking.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Service was really 6!   Our dinners were awesome.   My wife did the early bird since it was what she wanted anyway so it was a great deal.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: We‚Äôve had the best time celebrating our anniversary at Sole. Amazing, delicious and fresh food, great atmosphere, and the best service we‚Äôve seen in a long time. All the staff, but particularly Bruno and Gustavo, were incredibly attentive and made sure every little detail of our special occasion was unforgettable. Thank you so much!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Incredible place!

All the dishes were  delicious and served in a beautiful and aesthetic way. excellent service.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: It was hard to find a nice place on Sunday but I did it) very nice restaurant with suuuuuuper service... why are they so friendly. is is legal ?

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Having postponed a dinner here more than  a year ago I am so glad to have finally ticked it off my restaurant bucket list (however absolutely will be returning again..and again.)

The ambience when you walk in is classy, clean and warm and you instantly feel transported to a different part of the world. Greeted by wonderfuly pleasant staff and seated by the window I was delighted with life!

Martin our server was so friendly and attentive.

I simply can not choose a favourite dish as every single one was incredible. We had the following for two and in short it was one of the best meals I've had in a long time:

Crab claws (so sweet, simple and comforting)
6 Oysters (Achill and Connemara were particularly amazing)
Scallops (unreal)

Lobster Thermador (absolute must. Our first time having a full lobster and it was everything we hoped for. 85e and worth every penny)
Monkfish (so meaty it was glorious and the arancini was out of this world)
Side of fries

Lemon tart (stunning)
Deconstructed pavlova

Glass of wine (NZ Sauvignon ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ)
Glass of beer
Tea (how come the tea was also 5 stars?!)

In total with tip our bill came to 230e which for the quality, quantity, atmosphere, service and all round taste sensation was fantastic value for money.

We cannot wait to return and I have not stopped recommending to people! Thank you!

‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
You‚Äôll need to book this place as it gets very busy. My partner and I had a nice meal, but we felt it was nice at best due to the cost.

We sat close to the bar on tall stools which was fine as it gave us a good view, however, it would‚Äôve been nice to sit at a normal table as opposed to in an elevated position.

Our waiter was obsessed with us, providing a review and including his name on there, as I‚Äôm not sure whether they get paid for positive reviews on Google which would make sense. Due to his obsessive behaviour, however, it feels inappropriate to do that.

As a whole, the dining experience was pretty good and the food was flavoursome. I had lobster and my partner had a fish dish. Having seen other peoples orders, I would next time go for the lemon soul which looked amazing.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: My husband is happy with his steak the best steak he had so far he said üòÑ . I had rope mussels and my son had chicken goujons the chicken goujons are juicy not dry . Steak is tender and juicy. Mussels are nice and good portion. They have lovely chocolate brownie  that melts in the mouth .Service is good we don‚Äôt have to wait that long for the  food to be served . Staff are friendly not like beef and lobster in dame streetü§≠ overall my family had an awesome experience thanksüëçüèΩ

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Nice spot. This is a sister restaurant of Fire. The food is tasty and we preferred it to Fire. The staff were friendly and attentive. Glad to have tried it and would recommend, especially if you‚Äôre into seafood.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Just had an amazing meal here. Staff are brilliant, service was brilliant. Food was incredible. Highly recommend it.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Very overrated honestly and the service suboptimal although I did not go in peak hours.

The lobster was ok 6/10
The carbacio was amazing 10/10
Sea food showder 8/10
Oyster tempura 2/10 i couldnt eat it.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Second time coming to Sole - just as good as the first time!

Bruno our server was excellent, he couldn‚Äôt have done more to ensure our experience was pleasant.

The food was perfect, there wasn‚Äôt anything I would change at all - we ordered the 3 course for ‚Ç¨60; which was a bargain for the quality of the food.

It was my partners birthday, so the team facilitated my request at bringing in my own cake to present at the end - there was no fuss and they even added some fruit and writing to make it look beautiful - this is going the extra mile for an excellent experience.

Thanks a mil to the team at Sole, there‚Äôs a reason you‚Äôre one of Dublins best restaurants!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Wonderful place for good quality seafood. Really busy place so u know the foods fresh. Wonderful staff. Thanks for looking after us Alessandra!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
The atmosphere of the restaurant is very nice and from the time you enter you feel very welcomed. They had a bit of a mess with the order, the waitress explained there was an issue with the system but after she double check my order, still missed some items and we had to ask several times.

The food is good but definitely overpriced. We were there for a birthday, and in fancy restaurants they usually don‚Äôt charge the dessert for the birthday person, which here they did. The bill also came with a few things we didn‚Äôt ordered, I guess because of the system issues they mentioned. Overall, it didn‚Äôt meet my expectations.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: We went here for my wife's birthday dinner on our first night in Dublin, and it couldn't have been more perfect. From the incredible seafood and oysters to the in-house dry-aged steaks, we loved every bite. Our server Lucas was both hilarious and attentive, and also gave us time to talk and celebrate. Wonderful experience, 10/10!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
One of the most beautiful meals I have had in a long time.
Service was excellent, staff went above and beyond. They were so helpful with recommendations based on your own personal taste.
Every plate was well balanced, presented beautifully and the quality of ingredients used spoke for itself.
I am looking forward to going back again and again
Thank you Sole

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: I had a really nice time with my husband today at Sole seafood and grill restaurant. It was my husband birthday. The food was lovely. The service was excellent. The staffs were welcoming and even the waitress that looked after us was very nice and polite. I think her name was Kasia. When booking online I had requested for a desert written happy birthday on it for my husband and they did it as requested. I really appreciated it. I would definitely recommend this place.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Over rated. Manager needs training in customer service. Salad looks like the pre packed ones from groceries. Chowder was dry. It says lot when a restaurant fails on those simple things.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Very expensive and not filling.
Paid well over 100 per person for food only but was top little so we had to order another proper dish to be satisfied. Looking around, at least two couples did the same, not to mention that the one of them ended up with a full blown stake after having the seafood dishes.
Wine and service very good but so the price. Spent ‚Ç¨650 between two but I would have expected a bit more for that money.
Won't be back that soon unfortunately.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Lovely food and really nicely designed little restaurant! The early bird set menus were good value as well!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Came here because of reputation for being a good seafood restaurant. Three of the five of us arrived early so just sat outside enjoying the neighborhood. About 20 minutes passed and a host came out. We told her we were just waiting till our friends arrived. She asked if we would like to see a drink menu and we agreed. She never brought it out. When our other two friends arrived I went it to ask if we could be seated even though we were about ten minutes early. The same host recognized me and must have realized we were still outside waiting for drink menus. I told her we were all here. We were seated. Joe was our server. Two of us ordered martinis. I asked for an Absolute Martini straight up with three olives. My friend asked for a dirty martini. The drinks were awful - far too much vermouth. My friend said she couldn‚Äôt even taste the vodka because there was so much vermouth. We decided not to complain at the moment but would alert Joe after that the martinis were made wrong - not wanting our money back but just to be helpful. Joe said that ‚Äúin Ireland martinis are made with a 1:1 ratio of vermouth to vodka.‚Äù  We all at the table thought that was odd but since this was our first time in Ireland we didn‚Äôt pursue it. Later when we got back to our hotel we asked the bartender there how martinis were made in Ireland because we were told at a restaurant that they were made differently than in the US. The bartender seemed puzzled but told us martinis in Ireland are made just like the US - shot of vodka and just a tiny splash of vermouth. We don‚Äôt like being told a tale by Joe, the waiter. Maybe he thought that he was telling the truth but an apology for not liking the drinks would have been nice. BTW the food was okay but nothing spectacular.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Everything about Sole was fabulous from the moment we entered to when we left. The staff, the food, the ambience were all top class and couldn't be faulted.  First time but not the last, we will be back...üíû

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Staff was very kind from the start all the way to the end. We had a great server named Jesus he was above and beyond with the work he did. The food was also very nice with a good blend of flavour and looks. The food was very fresh. Would come again.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Fantastic service, incredible food! Scallops are incredible, highly recommended üëå Niamh and Lucas were incredibly attentive, friendly and knowledgeable!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Beautiful place with excellent service and very fresh, delicious seafood and dry-aged beef.  Pretty fancy but the prices aren‚Äôt too bad.. would be a nice date spot for seafood lovers.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
Beautiful Seafood Restaurant In The Heart Of Dublin City Centre.  Wonderful Selection Of Fresh Seafood And Matured Steaks. Very Popular So Make Sure To Book Ahead.
Professional, Warm Friendly And Very Welcoming Staff.
Very Highly Recommended

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
A very popular place, with wonderful ambience, good food and great service!

We headed over here after having to make reservations; after our arrival we could see why the place is so popular. Service is very attentive, and the atmosphere is great! Love the nautical-themed bar/seating area.

I was not too hungry so I ordered only appetizers; the shared prawn cocktail along with fish stew was plenty. The Husband had seared mackerel as an appetizer and said it's the best he's ever had.

The deliciousness of the food is reflected in the prices, but it's not overdone; our bill for four people was ‚Ç¨240, and this included a few glasses of wine and liquor.

If you're looking for a finer-dining experience while in Dublin, SOLE is a very good choice!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
I loved the service of Jesus and Gustavo.
they made a special day for my friend.
they always came to the table to ask if everything was ok, and they were super friendly, affectionate and attentive.
the food was great, but better than the food is their service.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: My family and I have been very blessed to eat at 5 star restaurant around the world. When we made it to Dublin we looked up top restaurants, Sole was listed at number 1. The wait staff had no problem quickly serving us our food but the quality of the food was far from a 5 star restaurant. The lack of sufficient air conditioning is why we rated the atmosphere low. We found the whole experience underwhelming.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
We booked Sole for our anniversary and when we arrived the restaurant was full and with a really good buzz  however we were sat at a table where you couldn‚Äôt really see much. When the table next to us left the staff proceeded to get ready for a table of eight. There was lots of moving tables, dragging chairs and general noise setting up. This could have been done with minimum fuss but unfortunately it wasn‚Äôt.

We ordered sparkling water and a bottle of Cloudy Bay and then our food. At this level and prices you expect everything to be faultless. We had crab claws and a quinoa salad to start, both were delicious. Our mains off salmon and fillet steak arrived but no veg or garlic butter for the steak. Also the steak was extremely undercooked. The fries were not as described on the menu (string cut) but were actually I think frozen. I called over a manager and my steak went back. This is where Bogdan took over looking after us and he was a star. The steak arrived back cooked perfectly however still no veg or butter. I had to ask for these and then eventually ordered pepper sauce. The pepper sauce was terrible and the veg was cold and tasteless. Overall the temperature of all our food was questionable. We ordered cheesecake and a cheese board for dessert. The cheese board was amazing.

As mentioned Bogdan is a real star and without his intervention our meal would have been a total disaster. He really rescued the night. A real nice guy.

Restaunts at this level charging these prices need to have impeccable service and food. The highlight of the night was the wine. We wouldn‚Äôt rush back.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Wonderful experience,  lovely seafood, beautiful ambience and friendly and welcoming staff. Delicious food. We ordered the lobster platter for appetiser and catch of the day and scallops for main course.  Perfectly made with perfect seasoning. Would highly recommend but make sure to book in advance.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: The place looks great and is spacious. Dishes well presented and look elaborate. However we got personally disappointed in the price-quality/quantity ratio. Prices are on the high side, quantities are not that generous but we got mostly disappointed with the slightly fishy smell & taste of our fishes (monkfish and sea bass) which did not reflect positively on the freshness of the fishes... Which we were told came from Ireland (so in theory it should be good). On the positive side, although there were just a few, the oysters were really fresh and tasty. I was never a fan of those before but I got to like them now üôÇ

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
We sat at the bar - highly recommend that but not for a 6 course tasting menu, then I became a bit long.

Staff was super friendly, engaged a lot in the wine choice which was appreciated. Inconsistencies in terms of presenting the food - we chose the tasting menu but some waiters neglected to present what it was we were served (without the menu at hand we had no way of knowing everything but what we could visually tell).

Food was really nice. Good, honest food with amazing produce. The only remark here was that they served the food too hot to eat so we had to wait a weirdly long amount of time before eating sometimes (champagne problem though). We were super happy with all of the courses apart from the dessert, where everything was really yummy and flavorful, but the meringue was not well baked - the bottom of it was like chewing gum.

Will 100% come back with a larger group for the shellfish trays they had!

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: It was wow! Food was amazing, service very nice and attentive. Now it will be hard to go back to ‚Äúeveryday‚Äù sea food eating and preparation, because SOLE opened a new doors for our taste buds. Highly recommend this place and already looking forward to go back.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Gustavo was our waiter tonight and he was perfect, no fault, the best waiter I‚Äôve had here. I travel from Liverpool to Dublin just to come to sole and it‚Äôs perfect every time. Thank you so much for the service and food

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text: Incredible food & service! Everything was so tasty and the service was brilliant from start to finish.

name: SOLE Seafood & Grill
review_text:
We were greeted by a welcoming & friendly member of staff and we couldn't help but notice how wonderful their seafood display was and also, the atmosphere. Throughout lunch, our attentive waiter (Thiago) also made sure everything was OK. Every plate that came out of their kitchen was presented well. I ordered the scallops and the sea bass fillet in Thai style curry sauce.

The scallops had a lovely texture though it could have used a bit more seasoning and could have been seared a bit more (there are some representative images posted by others here). Nevertheless, the scallops were still delicious, but not as delicious as it could potentially be!

The sea bass was superb. It was perfectly seasoned and the skin had a lovely, crispy texture. The flavours of the Thai style curry sauce had a rich, spiced, coconut flavour that went well with the umami of the fish. Splendid meal!

Overall, we're really happy with our experience at SOLE food and would definitely visit again!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Incredible traditional Irish food. The beef stew is exceptional and the seafood chowder is very authentic. The Irish cottage pie was delicious as well. Fish and chips is safe as always. The pub is on the second floor and offers a very homey and intimate feel, especially when bustling. A true Dublin experience. Highly recommend.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: One of the most magical places we visited in Dublin. Best Irish stew and Guinness stew ever,big chunks of meat, thick consistency accompanied by bread & butter and mash. Coffe was delicious so does Bailey's cheesecake. Great music and decor where you can feel the spirit of Dublin for sure. Prices are pretty decent as well.  Thank you for hosting us, great team work. We will definitely come back there

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely loved the food and the place. Employees were very friendly and got us a place to sit soon. We ordered a traditional Irish stew and the meat was utterly tender, delicious and the stew was made to perfection. Portions are huge and worth the money spent. Thank you for a good experience and would highly recommend this place for its food and friendliness.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: We went to this restaurant while visiting Dublin. We ordered 2 course meal. Everything was so delicious and good! Creamy seafood chowder and especially good. The portion were so big so there‚Äôs no chance you will leave this restaurant hungry. Stuff was very friendly and helpful. Overall experience is just amazing.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Great spot for delicious food and drinks. Cozy interior and friendly staff. Tried the cottage pie which was delicious and of course pairs delightfully with a cold beer. While in a touristy area, definitely noticed lots of locals in too. Would definitely recommend when in Dublin.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Nice place if you want to have tasty food that is reasonably priced ( as for Tempe bar). Stew was huge and fresh and we did not have to wait long for food.Clam chowder was fine as well.Service is quick ( as for a very crowded and busy place). The restroom are very dirty : the tap did not work and there were beer barrels in the toilet ( hope they are not serving beer from them). Overall would recommend ‚Ä¶

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: The best food and drinks we had both in Ireland and Scotland!! I loved the cottage pie and vegetable soup. The bailey's coffee is wonderful too. Only con was that they rush you a bit because they're so small and busy. 10/10!!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Tasty food and kind service. The cottage cheese was great and the bread and butter pudding dessert is worth it (generous portion, so it can easily be shared).

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Our first meal in Dublin for the weekend. Food was very good..huge portions. Had a feel it was catering for the American visitor but was very good. Do not judge by the outside as the venue is upstairs and is much nicer inside.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: It's a great place for beef stew. Very delicious üòã.  I like it so much. The beer is fresh, too. The place is also quite historic and a bit small, but it's worth it. The service also are warmth.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: This review is for breakfast. Awesome. Just classic full Irish breakfast. Bacon and sausage were first class. Tea was strong. Service was friendly. Also the music was really good, like 70‚Äôs dad laid back rock. Reasonable prices in my opinion.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
This is THE place to eat in Dublin. We ate here on our first night and were so impressed that we had breakfast and lunch there everyday. The restaurant is pretty small and can get pretty full in the evening but it is really cute with all of its traditional irish decorations. Then there is the service, to be honest it was pretty bland and subdued in the morning but maybe that suits most after a night on the guiness. It was still efficient but nothing special. But in the evening it was great, very friendly and professional. They even sang happy birthday on my birthday and stuck a candle in my cheesecake.
Now, the food, just perfect! During our stay, I think we tried most items on the menu. The irish breakfast with crispy bacon and black and white pudding was a great way to start the day before a day of walking about. Then  all the traditionals were spot on too: both the irish stews, the chowder, fish and chips, amd the lamb shank was so tender. I will recommend this place to everyone that travels ro Dublin plus we will definitely be back.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
Food & PRESENTATION deserve 5 üåü; however, there's got to be better wait options.  Standing in line on staircase up to restaurant just doesn't seem necessary or safe.

Shout out to Dr. Claudia (strangers sharing a meal); you were a blessing to my day and such great conversation...take your hubby for apple crumble!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: The pasta here is absolutely amazing!! Even just the tomatoes in the dish were packed with the flavor of an entire pizza. The presentation of each item was also great and don‚Äôt even get me started on the delicious hot bread pudding. Stellar! I have an upcoming layover in Dublin and this place will be my first stop for a bite to eat.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
A nice restaurant on the upper floor (access by stairs) in a touristy Temple Bar area of Dublin. Had a great Irish pub/restaurant feel, which makes you feel right at home.

Both the cottage pie and lamb shank were delicious. Prices were decent and service was quick. Would recommend for a good meal.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
I wish we would have had this food tour the first day we were in Ireland. It is a great way to try a variety of traditional Irish food in good portion sizes.
My only complaint is that the tables are tiny and close together and only one server was serving the entire room.
We had soup and dessert as well as what is pictured.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: This is the meal that redeemed Irish food for me. After a week of dining from Dublin to Galway and back, the taste of Ireland for two at the Old Mill really was the best meal I had while on the Emerald Isle. I'll definitely go back next time I'm in town.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
One of the tourist restaurants but reasonable priced with good portion sizes and prices.

I enjoyed my Cottage Pie and coke for under 20‚Ç¨. Was very filling and delicious.

I would come here again.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
Cool place in the heart of Dublin with feel of history and super nice atmosphereüçª
Food is delicious üòã  been here few time within stay in Dublin
Recommend: irish stew, Baileys cheesecake and many more. Be cautious ‚ö†Ô∏è  potions are big and you need to come hungryüòÑ

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
We had  a fantastic Christmas party here! Absolutely amazing food! Extremely friendly staff went above and beyond!
Thank you Gerry!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: A cozy and intimate restaurant where you'll be in close proximity to diners on neighboring tables. Not suitable for wheelchairs (you have to climb stairs to get there), those who worry about Covid or those who value privacy. Otherwise, it serves good food at reasonable prices and the service is swift and friendly.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: For temple bar the prices were reasonable. We had the Irish stew and goats cheese walnut salad which were both really good. Only downside for me was the food came out instantly (we went on paddy‚Äôs day so they were rushing tables) and my wine wasn‚Äôt very nice at all. For 2 drinks, 2 mains, 1 dessert and tip we paid ‚Ç¨60.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
The selection was good. Traditional Irish breakfast or lunch options.

Had the Cottage Pie, no chips. Was more than I could eat. Filling, delicious. The traditional Irish stew was good but a little tough on the meat.

No drinks as we had just left the Guinness tour and had empty stomachs. I will say it was extremely warm inside and about half full. Food was quick.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Staff were nice, seafood chowder was really creamy and tasty. Very small place so think twice if you have a pram.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
Lost start reason: The restaurant was overbooked, got pressure to leave quickly to accommodate a overbooked guest. Poorly manages.

The restaurant was recommended to me by a friend. It was a pleasant experience, Cottage pie is slightly salty and the beer is great.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: What can I say?!? We are traveling with twin toddlers and had spent the day touring Dublin. We wanted to eat dinner in the Temple Bar neighborhood before calling it a day. The twins were not in the best of mood and kid friendly in America seems a bit different than kid friendly in Dublin. Lots of small restaurants and not much room for buggies and toddlers. First two restaurants we tried were just not good. My wife found The Old Mill, it was near our car in Fleet Street and I figured, worth a shot. We got the restaurant and a staff member on the street gave us a menu. Then I noticed the stairs. I try and be very respectful of staff and other patrons. Bringing cranky kids into place of business can be tough. Lugging the days stuff upstairs was daunting. The hostess insisted we would be fine and we would just need to fold down one of the buggies. She had staff help us up with our stuff and they got us seated. The Old Mill was about half-full. The waiter came and got our food and drink orders. The staff paid lots of attention to the boys and generally kept us all entertained while the establishment filled up. Our food came out (kids meals, my wife got their lamb, and I got the two course special, simple burger and garlic bread). The meals were terrific. The twins had their first fish and chips and loved them. My burger was juicy and the large strips of bacon added salty, fatty amazingness. The brown gravy was a wonderful touch on the side. My wife's lamb was perfect. Juicy and falling off the bone. To be completely honest the staff was so amazing, the food could have been inedible and I would still rate highly. But the food was sooooo good. On our way out the manager helped me carry our louds to the street, we chatted for a few minutes, and I felt as if I parted dinner at a distant relatives home. The Old Mill turned our evening around and put what was turning out to be a miserable evening into a very pleasurable one instead.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
Nice and tasty experience in dublin to try the local food.

Big dishes. Full of tourists but quite quick service.

The dishes are big enough to share as well.

The space its very coloring. A little bit of dust on walls but well‚Ä¶ nothing to do with the experience at all.

We enjoy much the food!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: The food was absolutely delicious and they serve big portions. We ordered the slow cooked beef with Guinness sauce, cottage pie, and burger. The service was very good and restaurant is decorated nicely inside. Definitely recommend if you want some good Irish food.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Great place to wind down in - good for tourists with a traditional Irish, down-to-earth cosy atmosphere and cool interior decor. Giant cider size, somewhere around 550ml! Suitable for gluten free.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Very convenient location, food was tasty, service was fast and accurate and, the portions are huge. Very affordable prices. And yes it‚Äôs ‚Äútouristy‚Äùbecause it‚Äôs in the heart of the tourist area‚Ä¶why would you expect different.  Over all great spot for a good meal in Temple Bar area

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Please stop by and eat here. It was a cool upstairs bar with super friendly staff and quick eating! The food was just amazing. The seafood chowder was one of the best we‚Äôve ever had.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: You would think that this place would be poor quality due to the abundance of tourists lined up outside but the food is definitely legit. By far the best fish and chips I had during our stay in Dublin. It is likely to be crowded but the tables turn over quickly. Shockingly excellent food.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Had a wonderful Irish lunch with family and we love the food including my 8 years old son. Surely revisit the restaurant again.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
The food was so so.
Big portions though and not expensive.
Good location.
Service was very good.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Nice big old bar, with cocktail bar and smoking garden. It is so huge, lovely food, good service. The charcoal beef burgers are amazing. Highly recommendüëåüçîüòä

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Even though it is super touristy (they even have many different language waiters) the ambiance is actually quite nice in this bustling place. The food is traditional with generous portions at a very agreeable price. The fish was very fresh and the dishes all quite delicious. Try the platter for 2 which is certainly worth the money. Recommended.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Overall a pleasant experience. Food is tasty but a bit pricy. And one menu that u get from the entrance has 10-15% smaller prices that the one inside, which is not a nice move.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Looks touristy but taste great! We ordered the taste of Ireland and got to taste the best dishes on the menu. Recommended for family and friends.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Very good Irish food a great beer. The staff is helpful and friendly.  I recommend this place.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Very good food! Well prepared and delicious!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Went there for dinner and a few pints. It was quite busy but I guess that‚Äôs expected considering how good the food was. We had the Irish stew, the traditional coddle, a goat cheese salad and the soup of the day. All dishes were delicious, the staff were kind, polite and very professional! Great experience and highly recommended!! Unfortunately, couldn‚Äôt resist the temptation of eating their food so there are no pics

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Highly recommend. Really kind, helpful and amusing staff. The Irish stew was great and the portion size was huge - would definitely recommend it with the price being not bad as well. However the burger was nothing extraordinary, for the price not worth it.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: We tried about 80% of the menu and it was so delicious!!! The gravy that came with the shepherds pie was heavenly. 10/10 on all boards.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Great spot for authentic Irish food in Dublin (temple bar area).  I ordered the cottage pie and it was delicious.  Service was great too.  My only complaint is that the restaurant is small and tables are crowded together.  The food was great, I will be back for the cottage pie!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: The food is really delicious but we were a bit disappointed with the service. We had to wait more than 40 minutes for our starter while everyone who got in after us already got their food - the waitress apologised after us pointing it out but it would have been nice to get at least a drink on the house or something like that. After we were done and declined a dessert, we immediately got the receipt even though we hadn‚Äôt asked for it.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Amazing food, reasonable prices, super attentive and friendly service. Highly recommend!

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
Service was sooooo nice to our group, and the food was great!

We called ahead, so there wasn‚Äôt too long of a wait even though they were quite busy.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text:
Nice restaurant in the heart of Dublin.
Multiple options including meat, traditional meals and even vegetarian section. The plates are big enough for a good meal.
There are 2 sitting areas, one outside and another one upstairs.
Medium price.
Ideal to go with friends or on a date.
Kind staff.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: Went there for dinner and I had the traditional irish stew. It was nice but i did not like the bread. I think the best was the staff (we had the Mexican waiter and he was super nice) and the whole vibe of the place.

name: Old Mill Restaurant
review_text: If you think of what Irish Pub food should taste like, look no further. This is #1 in my book! Great braised beef and Guinness stew. The sauce is so good; especially, on the mash. The apple crumble with cream and custard was wonderful. It was hot with slices of apple and some raisins in it. Not sweet. Just plain good tasting! Great meal with Moscow Mules to go with it. The Mules were made just right, too! We'll certainly will be going there many more times while we're here for a week of Pub food and drinks. When you're in Dublin, enjoy their Irish Pub food!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Authentic Spanish food with a complete Spanish service! The addition of potato to dishes makes it even better! Share concept, make sure to try as much as you could. In the heart of camden street, very busy place and they even take your credit card details to book you a place, but worth it.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Went at around 9pm on Sunday and managed to get a table without any reservation. Excellent service from staff and food was delicious. Would highly recommend if you are looking for authentic tasting Spanish tapas.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
I simply loved this place. It took me back to the time that I lived in Madrid. I had never tried the white sangria in Spain, in I absolutely loved .
Lovely food, staff and the price is good. A special thanks to Javi, who was really friendly and looked after us.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Great place and its unique atmosphere. The service, including the owners, is kind, cultural and helpful. The dishes are delicious and presented very nicely. We had a great evening! Spain in Dublin! I recommend highly!!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Food super achieved. Really taste of Spain. Ingredients brought from Spain. Spanish staff as well, kind, helpful, and chatty. Also an Irish guy recommended us the cheese cake as was his favorite, and omg!! Amazing ‚ù§Ô∏è thanks . Price affordable for Dublin‚Äôs prices.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Owners and other staff were so friendly and had wonderful recommendations!! I wish we lived in Dublin so we could come back. We had the Manchego with honey, Tomaquet, Ham Croquettes, Bomba de Barcelona, and prawns and loved every bite! Finished with churros!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: I haven‚Äôt seen such a cozy and welcoming place for a date before. The staff was super friendly without being too interrupting. The food was amazingly tasty. Never had such tasteful spanish food. The cheesecake was so delicious yet light and creamy. The ham croquettes took us by surprise with the creamy taste . Overall very good for dinner dates.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
My favorite food in Dublin!
These tapas took me back to Spain. The patatas bravas, pan con tomate (they had a different name on the menu, but this is the name by which I know this dish!),  gambas, and crema catal√°n were amazing stand outs! I was disappointed in the croquetas, a think they were formed too big. So, the filling to crispy battered "shell" ratio was off...they seemed too heavy and fatty).
The restaurant itself is dark and cozy and full of life and laughter! Highly recommend this restaurant!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
The best restaurant in Dublin.
I am a very critic person and always consider all aspects of a restaurant when giving a review, so read the below and you will definitely book a table in ‚Äúlas tapas de Lola‚Äù soon.
1) fast booking on the phone.
2) professional service. Waitress was native from Spain, knew the best tapas to recommend, and always spoke with patience and a smile on her face.
3) environment: well distributed tables, all tidy and clean. Even toilet was small but pristine clean and with soft scented sticks.
4) THE FOOD: we ordered olives, croquetas, gambas, octopus and pork. Octopus goes definitely at the top of my list. I have never eaten such a soft and tasty octopus on top of potato slices! The jam croquetas were made by God‚Äôs hands. I am not joking. The olives‚Äô oil was at the exact spicy level, and they came with valencian almonds! The pork could be divided by only pressing with the fork. For dessert we got cheese cake. WOW, so smooth, with soft vanilla flavor, without dough at the bottom.
Overall, the best food experience in more than 4 years.
You can‚Äôt miss this place.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Probably the most delicious food in Dublin! Great atmosphere and fantastic service. Returned here a couple of times during our visit to Ireland. Strongly recommend dishes with octopus, prawns, and pork cheeks üòä

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
GREAT FOOD; Experience meh...
Randomly found this place while visiting Dublin without any expectations. Unfortunately the whole thing started on the wrong foot because we just walked in without waiting to be seated and the waiter had to educate us (stupid tourists) that in Ireland you must wait to be seated at a restaurant.
The food and drinks were just like we remembered from Spain. Service was great, except for the guy at the door.
It gets crowded fast, therefore also very loud, no chance to have a conversation without shouting yourself.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Gorgeous food, excellent service. Was so delighted to see espinacas con garbanzos on the menu - delish. Tortilla could have fed a family of four. Totally understand why this place is so popular. Book early to avoid disappointment and it's worth the wait.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Great Spanish food menu! Bustling. Friendly staff. Try to book or else you may miss out! Croquettes were great.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
I've been wanting to go to this place for a while.
Got a reservation but when I got there there was a mixup and we didn't have a table. However they were so nice about it and made everything in their power to accommodate us. We had to wait for a while in the pub next door and they even went there to get us.. and also gave us some complimentary starters for the confusion. Amazing service!! The food was sooo good too. Great experience. Would recommend.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: The tapas were nice but there was too much garlic and in some of them, it was the only thing I could taste :( the white sangria surprised me! Better than the red one.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
The best Spanish cuisine.
Loved the food. Staff is very friendly.
It‚Äôs definitely worth a try

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Made my first visit here this weekend and won't be my last. Superb food, I sampled a range of dishes but the Carrillada will live long in the memory. The food was matched by the service and value. An excellent place to dine

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Lovely atmosphere and friendly staff but unfortunately the food did not live up to expectations. 6 dishes, only 2 were good. The rest were very oily, lacking flavour and over seasoned. Jug of sangria was pretty much ‚Ç¨40 juice. Would not recommend.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: We went there for our one year wedding anniversary, staff were so lovely and their Burnt cheesecake was top notch. Their sangria was so nice and the food was delicious. Definitely be back again

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Had an absolutely amazing meal here last week. We ordered 6 tapas between 2 of us, 5 probably would have been enough but we wanted to try about 15 different dishes so opeted for 6. Everything we got was absolutely excellent, my favorites being the prawns and the pork belly. Washed it down with a nice jug of sangria, which while very nice, came off quite expensive at ‚Ç¨37.50 (or so).
