Despite being absolutely stuffed we strove on and ordered desert, both of which were very good. The service here was second to none, some of the friendliest and most accommodative front of house staff I've come across, really great. I'll definitely be back.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: One of the most beautiful restaurants in the country, because the staff made the experience worth it! Every piece of food was filled with flavour and cooked to perfection! The atmosphere was gorgeous, everyone smiling and talking! 10/10! Roman is very kind and helpful, an absolute gentleman!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: I wish I could give more than five stars to this place; probably my favourite restaurant in Dublin, and I've been several times, Including my last two birthdays. The food is excellent, the service is great, and the price is great. My only complaint is that it's so hard to get a table and how great is it that other people obviously love it as much as my friends and I.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Easily one of the best restaurants in Dublin, maybe Ireland. I go regularly and they never fail to impress. Always a warm welcome and a genuine goodbye at the end of the meal. Food quality is of the highest standards. Service is swift and friendly. It's also very fairly priced. You will not be disappointed, it is an absolute must visit!!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Very good food, incredible service and a perfect evening! Thank you!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Such a wonderful place! Fantastic service, tapas arrived fast and staff were very attentive and friendly! Would recommend about 5 tapas between 2 people. The gambas were cooked well and presented sizzling, the ham croquettes were warm and crispy, the patatas bravas were soft and covered in a red sauce & mayo, the barcaloneta bombas were okay, and the crema catalana came in such a big portion! And definitely try the homemade cheesecake! Fabulous!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: We were so lucky to have followed a recommendation from a Dubliner who told us to go try Las Tapas De Lola. We had fantastic food and drinks in a great atmosphere. It was one of our best meals on our visit to Ireland. Would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone lucky enough to be in Dublin.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Extremely delicious tapas, every dish was full of flavour, the service was genuine and heartfelt, was busy but the staff seemed relaxed and happy. Good lighting and atmosphere, every dish was perfected! Loved this place.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: The food and atmosphere is amazing as always. The hosts Anna and Vanessa make you feel right at home and are a pleasure to talk to. Can't recommend this restaurant highly enough. I'd give it more then 5 stars if I could! Love love love it!!!üòç‚ù§Ô∏è

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Wonderful Spanish restaurant.  The service is outstanding.  The food is well prepared, fresh and tasty.  The decor is kind of tropical.  Great place to go with close friends and for romantic encounters, to chat and have a snack.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: The waiting list speaks for itself, great food (especially the chilli garlic prawns!) Very attentive and friendly service with a smile & the atmosphere was awesome, a relaxing/cosy atmosphere and right outside the window is the hustle and bustle of busy Wexford St. can‚Äôt wait to go back!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Had this on our list of places to try for a long time, and wasn‚Äôt disappointed. Food was absolutely delicious. Pork Belly and Pa amb tom√†quet were really nice. Chorizo with black pudding and prawns with garlic also super.  Chicken thighs and patatas bravas rounded out the mains. Prawn dish was the standout, but all excellent. Finished by sharing the churros and a coffee. Great food and great buzz in the place. Really feels like being in Spain. Tried a glass of both the red and white sangria, just to round out the tapas experience, but reverted to beer for my final drink. The only slight negative was the service. While our server was very pleasant, he was often distracted when at our table. He also overlooked a drink order which had to be requested again. Also a little too efficient at removing empty plates, but overall this didn‚Äôt distract from what was an excellent dining experience. We will be back.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
Food is super overrated, and the staff are incredibly rude - managers in particular and by looking at the snarky and defensive tone with which they respond to criticism here, seems consistent.

I‚Äôd heard about this place as the go-to spot in the south city centre, but it was truly underwhelming. Plenty of other spots I‚Äôd suggest going to rather than here. *cue inevitable ‚Äúsorry, just confused‚Äù.. attitude from owners*

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: My favourite restaurant in Dublin. I really struggle to book anywhere else as Tapas de Lola is so good. Have frequented it for 10 years. Excellent sangria, wine, staff and food to die for. You can always change it up too. Reasonably priced too. Desserts are the only thing that have been hit and miss

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: The best Spanish food outside of Spain! Amazing flavours, authentic dishes made of highest quality produce. Excellent customer service. Finish the night with an amaretto sour cocktail! Book well in advance as the place is always busy

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
Ever wondered why this restaurant is mostly fully book ?   Here is why...
Lovely place to eat.
Food is having excellent quality.
Service is very good.

So book your table prior to visiting other you will return home with an empty stomach.

Ps : 3 tapas per person is more than enough.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Manager found us a table on short notice and we really appreciate the effort. Food was very tasty. Octopus and loads of other seafood tapas to enjoy.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Amazing food, very authentic. You will not be disappointed. Sit in the conservatory part really nice vibe. Excellent price point and service is very friendly and very attentive. Thank you for the experience. Will return for sure.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: This is just the best place I've ever had tapas in. Not just in Dublin, everywhere! They're delicious, come in generous portions and are authentic (you can also tell by the amount of Spanish people eating here). I recommend the tortilla de patatas and the prawns.  The waiters and the owners are also lovely and very attentive. The restaurant isn't extremely cheap, but it's worth every cent!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Great tapas!!! Efficient service and cozy ambiance. You have place to sit out if you don‚Äôt have reservation.Staff looked worked out but kept their good customer service with smile and friendly attitude. Food was good and presentation was nice. Red sangria could have been better as I felt was little diluted. But overall had good experience. Would visit again!!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Gorgeous tasty  food, friendly staff, a delightful  way to spend a Sunday lunchtime

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: My family and I went there after reading all the good reviews online. It was a Tuesday evening and we did not expect a long queue. We were told that we need to wait for at least 30 mins for a table. One would not regret waiting coz the food was so good. The staff were extremely friendly. Love their crispy baby squid especially.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: If I only ordered by recommendation I would‚Äôve given this place one star, the octopus was too salty and tasted nothing even close to what I had in Spain. The drinks and another dish we ordered were tasty but it was just one tapas out of 5 dishes we ordered, others were overwhelmingly dull and salty. I didn‚Äôt complain, but wrote an email to the booking team asking for a table when the dish we used to love comes back onto menu. Then they came back with an angry long reply, accusing us not being appreciative? I said nothing bad but just plain asking for something used to be on the menu, then from this request they read that we were not satisfied with the food that night, oh great so you do know you did not serve great food, the correct way is not trying to manipulate your customer but to improve yourselves. Such a shame.

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: This is my second time in the restaurant and it was better than the first time! Complementary drinks on arrival and delicious food, the staff was really nice! Would recommend to anyone!! I would add some agua de Valencia to the drinks menu!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Born and raised in Spain for 25 years. I can honestly say this is the best Spanish restaurant in Dublin BY FAR! The quality of the food is outstanding, it is quite clear that the Chef is Spanish or at least has absorbed amazingly the Spanish culinary culture. Eating the Patatas Bravas, or Spanish Tortilla or even the Fideu√° I did not even notice that I was in Dublin, I could perfectly be in Barcelona and I would not even have noticed the difference. They gave us two Pimientos del Padr√≥n as a gift, the staff was extremely nice and the servings were really fast. To finish we had the best end possible, Crema Catalana. Being Catalan myself I have a very strict criteria for this one, but again they nailed it!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
Such a little gem! Food is authentic and delicious, the bombas and croquetas are the absolute winners.
Nice vibe and our server, Andrea, was wonderful and attentive.
Overall highly reccommended

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: The food was fab, ordered 12 tapas between 4 of us and it was more than enough food. It‚Äôs great value for money as the size of each dish is quite big. There is a real family feel with photos of the owners family on the walls and we even met and spoke to one of the owners which was really lovely. The staff are really friendly and attentive. I can‚Äôt wait to eat here again!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: It is one of the fav date restaurant of ours with my husband. You need to reserv a table a week in advance but there is a walk in possibility if you are lucky enough. The best tapas rest of Dublin by far

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: Fantastic place for Spanish food. Staff ultra professional,  we got great food recommendations and it did not disappoint. It would be 6 stars if there was an extra one. üçª cheers

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text:
Yesterday, It was our first time at Las Tapas de Lola. We arrived without booking and straigh away we got a table. Food was amazing and fast, we really enjoyed tasting the two variants of Lustau vermouth. The service was very attentive. Mar, the spanish waitress, took a really good care of us recommending her favourites dishes that turned out to taste deliciously: carrillera, goat cheese and prawns.
The preces and the sizes are generous.
We will be back soon!!

name: Las Tapas De Lola
review_text: It exceeded my expectations! The delicious pig cheek was tender and succulent, while the croqueta was simply outstanding. We also savored the perfectly prepared Pulpo a Galicia and succulent Gamba al Ajillo. For dessert, the Tarta de Queso was heavenly and beautifully complemented our Spanish red blend wine. The service was warm, kind, and efficient, making for a splendid dining experience. A must-visit gem in Dublin for any tapas lover!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Nothing extremely fancy; the pizza was great, but half of the BBQ ribs were not perfectly cooked (some of them perfect, with the meat melting, but others were just bad).

If I have to choose something impressive from the place would be the lemonade, FANTASTIC!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: worst food eaten in dublin! hot dishes because the food is all heated in the microwave. cream and parmesan in linguine with fish. low quality fish as well as everything else. too loud music and expensive bill for such poor food.
owner_answer:
Hello Fiorella,
Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback.  We‚Äôre sorry to know your experience was anything less than spectacular. As you can see from previous reviews this is not a regular occurrence for us, so we‚Äôre sorry to know this was your experience on this occasion.  We will be looking into the issues you have raised immediately and hope that you might return to us again soon!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Lovely place for an Irish breakfast or bap to start your day ! I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of my bap and the staff are so good as well. The food was well presented on the plate. In my opinion, this is good value and well worth the money. The menu is extensive as is the interior. You can sit in the conservatory looking onto the street or inside. Everywhere is clean and warm. It is centrally located on O‚ÄôConnell Street near to the Gresham. Definitely worth a visit, and reading the reviews, most fellow diners think so too !

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Extremely busy restaurant situated in the Heart of O Connell St. Has traditional dinners with good variety. Staff are friendly and helpful even though restaurant is mainly at capacity so well done. Asking for a "tip" on paying might turn some people off maybe having tip jar at counter might be better approach .

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
My wife and I visited twice on our trip to Dublin. The first time was on a musical pub crawl and it was a truly wonderful time.  The service and the environment for our visit was top notch.

The next evening we returned to get dinner to experience the food. The atmosphere was again great, they were quite busy but still felt mostly taken care of. The food was very good, not great but quite enjoyable and the overall experience was well worth the money. Would visit again.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Lovely food, restaurant in a pretty good location. Had to queue for 20 minutes but was worth the wait. Was a very busy evening so service wasn't amazing, but understandable. The price was about average for Dublin.
I had the wings & ribs combo and was delicious, My partner had a pizza which was also tasty. Would visit again if in Dublin

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Hard to believe its nearly 40 years since I was last in Flanagans. I had great memories there and was really pleasantly surprised with the new " new to me " look of the place.

Very friendly service, great atmosphere and really quick serving drinks and dinners.  Portions sizes were perfect.

Most importantly the food was delicious.

5 Stars no hesitation.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Stopped for a quick bite with the Lady. Food and service was great, has an old town feel and vibe. Please go in and enjoy!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Popped in here for food one evening we were in Dublin, service is good and very friendly ,fast service with the food which was great as we were starving this night. Mixed enough menu with plenty to suit I had lasagne with chips, found the lasagne a little sweet so didn't eat it all but was lovely meal and anything served to our group was lovely.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Just in for breakfast, we were seated quickly and food arrived minutes after ordering which was great. Lovely traditional fry, tea and toast included.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Great value kids meal, includes a drink & desert, that's why we keep coming back

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Very nice place and very good food. Fantastic people inside so... from Italian guy this is one of my favorite place in Dublin!!!!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: We came in for lunch. My mum had the bacon and cabbage which she said was absolutely delicious.  I had the vegan burger which was the best I've ever had. Friendly staff and good value for money. Would definitely recommend and visit again whenever I'm next in Dublin.
owner_answer:
Hello Alison,
We are so grateful that you took the time to share your feedback with us. It's our pleasure to serve customers like you. Have a wonderful day!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Me and my partner had a great evening meal sat in their outside seating. Menu has plenty of options and clearly states any allergens.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Located in the heart of the city. The restaurant was quite big with closely packed tables, can be very busy at times. Requires no reservations, can walk in subject to availability. We had a fulfilling lunch here. The food was freshly prepared with generous portion sizes and fairly priced. Overall service was good.
owner_answer:
Hello Ranjith,
Thank you so much for the lovely review. We always try our best to provide the best dining experience to everyone and we appreciate that you were able to have that. We look forward to your next visit!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
The food was delicious and the location is right in the middle of everything a visitor could want.

Atmospherics were great and the staff was also friendly. The only reason for the lost star is because it was expensive for what it was. Yes, it‚Äôs downtown Dublin, but other places on the same street were cheaper for equally excellent food.

That said, it‚Äôs not a reason to stay away. If the quality is always this high, people won‚Äôt leave here unsatisfied with their choice of dining for the night.
owner_answer:
Hello Jeffrey,
We're so happy to hear you had a great experience here. Your review made our day! Our whole team works very hard to keep our customers happy, but we can only do it thanks to amazing customers like you. Thanks again, and we hope to serve you again soon.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: They show allergens on menu. I had a gluten free burger, which was safe but mediocre in taste. Unfortunately that day they did not have gluten free onion rings. No gluten free beer.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
The fish and chips were delicious - the prices are ok .
The service is correct
To recommend a 100%

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Attend the musical pub crawl here. The service was fine. The food was just adequate. Seafood soup was great. Salmon meal was bland.  Chocolate dessert was very dry. The room we were in was too small for the pub crawl dinner group.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Very delicious food. Atmosphere was very nice and everything was just lovely.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
We had lunch there and had a good lunch. They have an a la carte menu and they have a lunch menu. The lunch menu which includes roast of the day is unbelievable value. Check it out,
The desserts were good and the staff were really friendly. All in all it was a good experience.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Went on two separate night.  Had salad and Irish stew 1st night and it was great (4.5).  Stew was a touch salty but not over powering.  2nd night had bacon cheese burger and it was alright.  A bit dry and tough (2.5).  I was lured by the thought of a juicy 8oz burger and I was hungry.  The size didn't disappoint as it was a fair sized burger, but definitely needed a pint to get it washed down.  Service was great both nights so I'd probably go back to try the lamb shank which seemed popular and looked awesome on the tables around me!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Food was really good! Crispy fish and chips. The burger was also tasty! Good coffee and drinks. Dessert was fresh! Nice service.
owner_answer:
Hello Jesslyn,
Thank you so much for taking the time to share your experience with us. We take pride in knowing our customers are happy with their dining experience.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
After unpleasant rule that we can't have starters an 2 drinks,  we order main dish,  It arrived fast,  but after 20 minutes, when we obviously didn't finish waitress was keep coming to table asking us did we finish, until she took last slice of pizza and put other plates on it and said you are finished right!?
Like that wasn't enough, I still had some drink in my glass, the other waitress just took it, and immediately brought the bill.  We feelt pressure entire time .
I would maybe understand if it was busy, but entire place at the back was almost empty.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Had a two night stay in dublin and flanagans was are go to restaurant for breakfast. The staff were so friendly and the food was excellent.Will visit again on my next trip.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: The best meal we had in Dublin! Beautifully decorated and clean. Lovely red haired lady served us, had a smile on her face all night, very friendly and attentive. Great restaurant!
owner_answer:
Hello Tanya,
We are happy to hear that our team provided you with excellent service. I'll make sure that they receive your feedback. I'm sure it will make their day! We hope to welcome you back!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Ordered the chicken and ham off the lunch menu and my whole dish was dry and vegetables tasted like they were cooked yesterday and left sitting there for hours ‚Ä¶I was also asked to pay upfront for my meal before receiving it? I was sat in the smoking area and told I could smoke ,then one of the workers decided to pull over the roof cover and informed me I can‚Äôt smoke ? I‚Äôve had a terrible experience and surprised this establishment is still up and running ü§¢

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: My mum & I had breakfast in this wonderful restaurant yesterday morning. First class service from the friendly staff. Food was beautiful. So reasonably priced and the restaurant was a lovely setting and clean. They also take cash.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: First impression of Dublin centre was lunch at Flanagan. The food was great I had Irish stewüòã.  Everybody in our group (7 people) were very satisfied. The beer was great as was the atmosphere. A great location, great food with reasonable prices.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
On our Europe trip, after driving from Belfast, we were super hungry and found this place right before  closing.
Despite the fact that it was near closing time, they let us in.
The food was amazing and well prepared. We had salmon and mash, beef stew, pizza, and burgers for the kids.
Staff was friendly even though they had a long day.
We are definitely going back here  on our next vacation.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: I had the Bap Bun... Wow!! Totally recommend!! Best breakfast in Dublin!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Have eaten here before. Was really looking forward to an irish breakfast. Sadly, we got a breakfast 5 mins after ordering which can only mean it was NOT freshly prepared.. only the tea was hot....not impressed

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: We could not split a check at our table in any way, so one person had to pay for a large party.  Great food; lamb shanks and the stew were excellent!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: The Seafood chowder was actually quite nice but the salmon salad for almost 20‚Ç¨ was just too sad for that amount of money. No dressing just sweat and sour chili sauce. So sadly too dry and not flavorful.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: We ordered two plates of noodles, one is seafood noodles, and the other is chicken and garlic noodles. It tastes good, but there are fewer dishes and seafood in the noodles. I don't recommend beef burgers. It's not very good. It is recommended to book a larger table in advance, otherwise you may order up to three dishes.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Ordered steak, at 30 Euro you would expect more. They describe themselves as a steak place but it was frozen steak and not cooked to standard. Definitely not worth 30 euros. They did take it back and cook it slightly closer to how we wanted it, but by that point everyone else had finished eating. Overall food was generally quite greasy and oily. The pizza was great though. As meals out go, I am deducting major points for the price here. I appreciate it is city centre, but definitely too dear for what you get.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Great lunch stop right on O‚ÄôConnell Street.  Great service and food.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: The owner was a chatty guy and very accommodating kid friendly really nice place lovely location. Breakfast was perfect ‚Äútry the granola lads‚Äù üòã the full Irish perfect amount for a hungry belly THANKS YOU GUYS WE WILL BE BACK‚Ä¶.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: The food was phenomenal! The drinks were fabulous! Our server (Belinda, I think) did an excellent job. She had great recommendations and was very friendly. We loved our visit!!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Awesome, the food was delicious, the staff are attentive and jolly. There is a lovely atmosphere.  Lovely memories of my husband and I eating here. Making new memories with my daughters. We will definitely be returning üåüüåüüåüüåüüåü‚ù§Ô∏è

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: A well established restaurant with good old fashion services. Still surviving in a main thoroughfare of our capital city that has been named and shamed in the media for petty crimes and drug taking. The burger was nicely cooked but the fruit in the Ice cream Sundae was frozen. But still as good as I first visited them in the 1990s and kept their prices reasonably. My bill came to just over ‚Ç¨32 for 2 courses and a half litre of their own lemonade.  Their customers were of all ages with a party of 20 something girls to senior citizens.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Food was excellent,  atmosphere great and very welcoming,  staff really helpful , value for money
owner_answer:
Hello Ryan,
Thank you so much for the lovely review. We always try our best to provide the best dining experience to everyone and we appreciate that you were able to have that. We look forward to your next visit!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Was here at Christmas and food was lovely,Unfortunately I came back yesterday and it was awful. I had garlic mushrooms which looked and tasted stale. For mains I ordered chicken and ham and my wife had beef. The ham and beef were like slices from a deli. To be fair to the waitress she realised we weren't happy,and she offered us to order something else off the menu,but we declined. We just had to pay for the starters as she didn't charge for 2 cokes either. Nice waitress but we won't be going back,very disappointing.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text:
Came here for lunch. I had the homemade burger and peach tea. Yummy all round.
I even changed the toppings on my burger with no problems.
My partner had bacon burger and bubblegum soda and she loved them.
The staff were so nice and friendly.
Great place to stop and refuel

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Large portion sizes. Very nice service and tasty food. Very glad we decided to give this place a try while in town.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Irish stew was delicious! Filling and lots of potatoes. Service was great.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Went there for a drink and dessert after 7:30pm place was half empty. We were told we couldn‚Äôt order just dessert and would have to order ‚ÄúMain Course‚Äù in order to get dessert. Could hardly understand what the host was saying but he was getting pretty rude so we just left. Now I wouldn‚Äôt waste my money going there! Planned on trying their sticky toffee pudding!

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Had a lunch and a breakfast here on 2 different days. Sat in the same booth and had the same Amazing person wait on us, " Emily " . Just a beautiful person and she was great to chat with.  Highly recommended this spot.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Lovely place, with an amazing tasty food and reasonable prices. Every time when I'm visiting Dublin I'm eating mostly there. Love their steaks and deserts! Also worth to mention stuff, friendly, with a good sense of humor will always help to choose the best for you if you can't decided yourself. The place is not very spacious, wouldn't suit for a big company's dinner.

name: Flanagan's Bar & Restaurant
review_text: Great atmosphere and nice staff. Food was good and the portions were very large. Try out the fried mushrooms!
owner_answer:
Hello Merressa,
Thank you for the lovely review and we are so glad to hear you enjoyed your dinner here! Thanks for checking us out and taking the time to share. Hope to see you again!

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: The rigatoni and pizza were amazing and our waitress was so lovely. The brownie dessert was a 1000/10, whoever made it deserves a raise and a Michelin star. Loved this place!
owner_answer: Thanks for the 5 stars and the lovely review!!!

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: Tried Sophie‚Äôs for the first time and really enjoyed it. The view is great, the staff are friendly, and the food‚Äôs pretty tasty. Wasn‚Äôt keen on the üç∑ and the area tends to get quite noisy, but it‚Äôs well worth a visit and overall we had a great time. Great shout for a night out or for a party. üëåüèº
owner_answer: Thanks for the 4 stars!!!!

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: Went for Brunch on Saturday. Everything was perfect, from the reception to the service of the staff, including the food later on. The prices are good regarding quality and quantity. Sophie‚Äôs is a place I would recommend 100% for a special brunch or dinner :)
owner_answer: Hi there, thank you so much for the lovely review and the 5 stars! So glad you enjoyed you time with us, see you again sometime...The Sophie's Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text:
I recently visited your restaurant and had a great experience. The ambiance was fantastic, and the waitresses were lovely and attentive. I particularly enjoyed the tempura prawns for starters and the creamy mash for sides. The rooftop location on the 5th floor provided a breathtaking view of Dublin, and the swings at the elevator were a thoughtful touch that added to the overall experience.

However, I would like to suggest that customers should book a table well in advance, especially on weekends, as I found it difficult to secure a reservation.
owner_answer:
Hi there,
thank you for visiting and for the positive review.
The Sophie's Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text:
Second time at Sophie's! Love it. Both times for mini milestone celebrations.

Food always delicious. Staff very friendly and the DJ always on point.

*Booking essential and You MUST arrive on time.
Indoor and outdoor seating - excellent
owner_answer:
Hi there,

thank you so much for the lovely review and the 5 stars!

We'll see you again soon...

The Sophie's Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text:
It's good, and kitchen was surprisingly nice. But for me it's still Irish food) Don't get it offensive, it's just how it's.
The most men from another tables ordered pizza, so probably they serve good pizza.
Preferably, I don't like such expensive restaurants, but if you want to have a good date, it's nice, but don't expect it will be very quiet, because could be busy. Not for the romantics)
owner_answer:
Hi there,

thank you so much for the 5 star review!

The Sophie's Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: I tried to make a reservation online for 12:00pm, as it said it was available but was unable to get the website to load correctly. I called the restaurant and explained the situation and they stated that they did not have any 12:00pm reservations available and could not guarantee us a table but to stop by anyway. We got there about 12:20pm after fighting traffic, and we were actually seated at a table immediately! The server was very kind, and the food was very VERY good, but I will say that I was a little disappointed with the views, and the pricing of the food was high
owner_answer:
Hi there,

thank you so much for visiting and the four stars! So glad we could get you sat quickly! See you another time...
The Sophie's Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: Sophie's had a great ambiance and a perfect view for the sunset. the food and drinks were really great too. More of a cocktail bar vibe. Can't give it a full star rating as they prioritize seating for the hotel guests, so if you're walking in you have only limited areas for seating.
owner_answer:
Hi there,

thank you so much for the 4 stars!

The Sophie‚Äôs Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: Always best to get a reservation, but they were kind enough to let us sit at the bar. We ordered some cocktails which were so good and cheesecake for dessert. Love the ambiance and their pizza is delicious. Definitely coming back!
owner_answer:
Hi Nina,
thank you so much for the lovely review! We‚Äôre delighted you had a nice time. See you again soon!
The Sophie‚Äôs Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: This is awesome for photos and ambience. There is also a live DJ which plays amazing songs. Food is average and not that great. But cocktail and mocktails are amazing. Good for drinks and ambience average for food. Staff is nice. Also this is in Dean hotel and it is located at 5th floor of the building. At entrance there is dime coffee and 5th floor is sophies roof top bar üç∏ üëå üòÄ
owner_answer:
Hi there,

thank you so much for the 4 stars!

The Sophie‚Äôs Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text: Must visit whenever I‚Äôm in Dublin. Came for brunch once, and drinks the other day. Always a great idea. Excellent staff and good drinks / food! Nice atmosphere even though can be crowded at time. Nice view over Dublin though!
owner_answer:
Hi Julia,
thank you so much for the lovely review! Looking forward to seeing you again soon.
The Sophie‚Äôs Team

name: Sophie‚Äôs
review_text:
Wow. What a fantastic place. We enjoyed it so much that having visited for dinner we returned the next day for lunch.

Superb venue, really striking with amazing views. Delicious food and friendly service.

Will definitely return next time I am in Dublin.
owner_answer:

Enjoyed a lovely family evening here t Sophie‚Äôs.

Steak was cooked as ordered, lacked a little seasoning. Greens were extra but worth it as cooked fresh, not microwaved or reheated - this drives me nuts and a lot of high end places still do it!!

Chicken with Nduja sauce and Orecchiette pasta was superb - I‚Äôm going back for this. Pasta Al dente, sauce rich but not sickening. Small piece of chicken - but enough for me.

Cocktails and soft drinks priced high, but not unusual for Dublin or type of setting.

Looking forward to a repeat visit, maybe to see the sun set or check out the outside area ‚Ä¶ car parking 5 mins walk at Stephen‚Äôs green.

Older kids loved the pizza and skinny chips - fresh dough

Well if it had taken less than an hour to get my food after we had ordered, maybe I would have had time to eat it comfortably and then pay. Wasnt really even time for dessert.

Just a shame with their timings really.

I had the pancakes and was pleasantly surprised by the large bottle of maple syrup meaning I could have as much as I liked! They even went out of their way to give our friend a plate with icecream  rasperries and chocolate crumble as well as happy birthday written on it using choclate. I'd say for the views and the quality of food the price is justified, it was just ashame we had to leave in a rush to catch our flight home.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: I'm a little disappointed with the food, i guess, for the price, it was OK . Only one dish came out delicious. The rest were fine, nothing to brag about. I expect the old metal winding stairs inside the bookstore in the back. But we fot regular stairs. Overall, it was great service, one delicious fish meal, and cider drink.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: We happened to be in Dublin during our anniversary (we travel full time) and wanted to pick a place that was nice, served Irish food, and wasn't too stuffy/proper or trendy/posh and had good food. We read about Winding Stair in a few lists and our friend Tara who used to live in Dublin recommended this place. This place was PERFECT! We got a great seat on the top floor on the corner with a  view of the Ha'penny bridge and all the machinations of Temple Bar across the river. The service was perfect and the food, presentation, ingredients was divine. The wine list was also expansive, I would say our only minor complaint was that some of the dishes came over sauced. My scotch egg was perfectly cooked with a runny center, crispy sausage wrapping, served piping hot but was sitting on a bed of some sort of aoli or mayo based sauce which I wished was on the side so it didn't mess up my perfect egg. My gnudi also had a really thick sauce. I wish I had ordered the Cod which our friend ordered which came with a generous side of lightly prepared veggies. The Cod was a giant slab, crispy on one side and perfectly flaky all the way through. Difficult to do with such a big piece of fish. The pork chop which my brother in law ordered was also a generous piece of meat and tasted divine. My husband ordered the tongue appetizer. So good! But once again we had to scrape off the dollop of mayo. Now that I've been there once we would know what to order and maybe the chef would be amenable to a request for light sauce. I guess I wouldn't ask for it on the side because the presentation is beautiful, but to our taste, less is more especially when you're working with such talented cooking and great ingredients. The interior design of this place feels like the  interior of your tasteful aunt's place. Old book shelves artfully placed, gorgeous old floors, love the tables and chairs and of course all the windows and light. If I lived in Dublin I would eat here once a week. (Though a tiny bit pricey, most things are big enough to share). Oh and before I forget, the cheesecake! And I don't even like cheesecake!

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Incredible meal and cozy atmosphere with a great view. We got the broccoli starter fish plate, lamb main and gnudi main and they were all phenomenal. Would recommend a thousand times over

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: This place had the best food we had during our trip to Ireland. Located above a bookstore and through winding stairs is a cozy little restaurant. We ordered the lamb and the fish and it was very delicious. The wine was very good, definitely recommend the strawberry Irish wine. Service was great as well and it looks like the window seats get a great view.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Cute little bookshop atmosphere with delicious Irish cuisine. Absolutely loved the Gnudi, it‚Äôs a must. They also have a great wine selection that includes recommendations perfect for someone like me who is an amateur wine drinker. I emailed for a reservation and they were quick to respond and set it up for me.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Everything we had was just right. The flavors were subtle and balanced. The portions sizes perfect. Appetizers, main course and dessert. Left satisfied but not feeling like we'd overdone.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
The Winding Stair is a charming restaurant that offers a delightful dining experience to anyone who enters. Its beautiful ambiance provides a warm and inviting atmosphere for diners to relish in.
The restaurant offers a great selection of Irish food. I recommend trying the fish plate which offers a great variety of delicious flavors, especially the salmon and the herring, and it was presented in a beautiful manner. The Irish Black Angus with chips and vegtables was cooked to perfection, rare as I asked. The haddock was an absolutely amazing dish! The onions added an extra layer of flavor, and the white Cheddar mash perfectly complemented the flavors of the haddock. A truly enjoyable meal.
Portion sizes were also generous and left no room for dessert.
Overall, I highly recommend The Winding Stair to anyone looking for an exceptional dining experience in Dublin.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: First meal in Dublin and it was great. Very fish forward and happy to have perfectly cooked fish. Good wine list, good starters, almost did not have room for the main dish let alone the pudding.  Think Sweet and kick it up a level, but we finished it and would get it again.  Happy we found it and would come back to the great food and nice staff.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Food was excellent and the view out the window was very nice! The server was really good, the restaurant itself is pretty small but has a great atmosphere. Was definitely a great way to end our trip.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: The Winding Stair was an... interesting time. The service was sometimes friendly and knowledgeable, but our main waiter was eccentric and rude. If our group weren't quite so laid-back and jovial, we'd have been offended by his words and actions. The lamb was quite good, though the charcuterie board was disappointing for the price, even compared to other starters. They have a very large wine selection and are certainly very knowledgeable about it. The atmosphere was fine, unremarkable, a bit noisy.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
We had a very pleasant stay here. The food was exquisite, one of the best places I have ever been at.

Note you might need to book in advance, but it's totally worth it.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Gem of a place with incredible food. Staff were lovely and very accommodating. We were a walk in of 3 and within 5 minutes they had cleared a table and sat us down. Food was gorgeous and very reasonably priced for the quality.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Every dish we tried tasted absolutely delicious! We started with Potted Dingle Bay crab with pickled cucumber, toasted soda bread and organic leaves. The bread was perfect and it went perfectly well with the crab. The greens also tasted very good. I just found the pickles a bit too sweet for my taste. Then we continued with main dishes: Irish Waters hake, Dublin Bay razor clams, brown shrimp, saffron butter, samphire, roasted baby potatoes and Grilled Organic Irish king oyster mushrooms, sweet corn pur√©e, kale, grilled corn, pickled veg, caramelised onion, Hegartys cheddar croquette, lime yoghurt. I loved every bite of the main dishes. The croquette was my favourite part of the mains. The service was great. The staff was super friendly and helpful. They ask for reservations, but we didn‚Äôt make any and the restaurant had free tables at the time so we managed to find a table.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: We ordered the Turkey, grilled fish, and the potted crab and everything was delicious. On top of that the service was quick and the staff were not just professional but also very lovely! Will definitely come back again.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Lovely winter meal. Fish is fresh. Chefs clearly know what they're doing. The mash and haddock brought back some old memories. Proper homely food. Restaurant is above the bookshop, short walk from the Temple Bar area. Service was smooth and friendly

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Outstanding eatery featuring the best of Irish cuisine. Do try the Irish seafood platter! Lovely vibe and great wine list.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: The atmosphere is cosy, quirky with an air of elegance. The food is absolutely delicious! I highly recommend the crab for start and the wine list is varied, something there for everyone. I had a fantastic experience here!

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
Quality Irish food
Recommended: fish plate for starter, Irish cod in main, butter pudding for dessert

Highly recommend to book reservation in front

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Food was very good but this place is VERY expensive compared to other places in the area. The staff will call you you out if you don't order a "Main". The menu was different from what they posted online and nothing really seemed appetizing. Also as a side mention, this has been the only place in Ireland which requested a tip.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Cracking old bookshop crammed full of all sorts of books and a few chairs so you can sit a chill and flick through a book.  Didn‚Äôt realise there was a cafe upstairs though but that was stupid as the shop‚Äôs called The Winding Stair for a reason - it has a staircase!  Very friendly staff.  Got a canvas bag for ‚Ç¨5 along with a few books.  There should be more of these old independent bookshops as they‚Äôre way more interesting to potter through and they can be very competitive in comparison to the chain stores

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Enjoyable evening, great atmosphere and service. Everyone enjoyed their food, I had the King Oyster Mushroom to start - very tasty. The lamb was delicious as well.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: A fine restaurant In a previously famous book store. If you have mobility issues this might be the restaurant of choice. We had the scotch egg to start. This was well cooked and very tasty. The Gem salad had plenty of anchovies and was worth trying. The smoked haddock was a bit disappointing for me but I've never had this type of dish before. I felt it lacked different flavours and was rather monotonous. Maybe that's the way it's supposed to be? Meal for 2 with no liquor was 77 Euro.  The restaurant is worth going back to and trying other delights. Worth the trip.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
We got recommendations for that restaurant from a local, and it was a fantastic experience. We tried potted crab, the mussels and lamb belly, and everything was cooked to perfection. The mussels portion was also so huge it could easily be enough for two. Finished with a bread pudding, which was delightful.
Service was great as well. Highly recommended. Just make sure to book in advance.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Wonderful experience!  The ambiance is perfect.  It‚Äôs upscale, but not snooty, so still feels laid back.  The food was incredible.  My husband ordered the pork chop and said it was the best pork chop he‚Äôs ever had.  Will continue to come back here whenever we‚Äôre in town.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: This was the best meal we had during our 2 week stay in Ireland. Quality fresh ingredients, great taste, perfect portions that meant we had three courses comfortably.  Lovely vibe, excellent service and all in a fabulous venue overlooking the river and Ha‚Äôpenny Bridge. I can‚Äôt recommend it highly enough. It was perfect for a special meal out on the last night of our holiday. We had a number of meals during our stay that were more expensive across two courses, but nowhere near this quality so it makes this restaurant great value for money.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
Dining for 1 & arrived by 6pm with no reservations, was seated at perfect table for 1
After 7pm place was packed.
Service was fantastic & my cod was absolutely delicious
Enjoy

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Perfect place for lunch to escape the tourist hustle of sightseeing. Food & drink menu are fabulous. For Lunch I had the Sole with a Red Ale, while overlooking the river and Ha‚Äôpenny Bridge. Good music, chill atmosphere, perfectly lovely staff. Wish I could have stayed for longer. Blissful place on a Summer afternoon.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: This was our second time eating at this restaurant (the last time was 6 years ago) and it didn‚Äôt disappoint this time, either. Nice wine selection, delicious food, and good service.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
Great restaurant just across the Temple Bar area. High quality food with good service and great views of the Liffey. If you‚Äôre visiting Dublin and in the area, I would highly recommend.
*Just be mindful that they are true to their name and you‚Äôll have to go up multiplier stairs.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
Scotch egg.
What a lovely surprise. An egg lightly boiled before wrapped in a mask (maybe yam) then rolled in a nut mix before deep fried to finish the egg to be smiling. Really nice.
Pork chop. Large chop on the bone cooked to be juicy and tender served  with a whole cooked sweet apple and deep fried black pudding ball.
Cauliflower (whole) in blue cheese sauce served with bok choy, green peas. The blue cheese a little overpowering but still delightful.
Service very fast, great happy attitude and knowledgeable on the menu and wines.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Food was amazing. We ate at FRESH last night which the service was great but food not as good. This was the other way around at the Winding Stair, food amazing, but service not as good - overall a good experience though so no complaints. The Lamb which I had was very tender and my partner had the cod which was also very tasty. Limited range of puddings, so went to the Gelato shop nearby for that.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
A cute little restaurant hidden behind well trodden winding stairs. The brunch here is a must try. The selection of wines is exceptional and the one I liked the most is that they have a suggestion of wine with every item on the menu - that‚Äôs nice.

The Irish Strawberry wine, and the bread and butter pudding in whisky sauce is a must try.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Didn't get a great seat... But had no reservation so I can't cry too much. Well restaurant was empty when we got there... Anyhow service was excellent, wine and only bottle beer. Good Beer! Food was good, except don't order the steak & bone marrow plate. He wasn't kidding it's dry. Even at medium it was nice red but so lean it's not good.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: One of my favourite restaurants in Dublin. Not to miss if you want to experience local cuisine with a modern twist and a view on the river Liffey. It‚Äôs airy and spacious and has a bookstore on the ground floor. Our choice of their hand smoked haddock and steak didn‚Äôt disappoint. We‚Äôll definitely be back!

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Lovely restaurant with fresh delicious food and good service. Keep in mind that if you want to have a table by the window you should book at least with a few good days in advance.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: This is a lovely setting for dinner and the atmosphere and service was great. The scotch egg and charcuterie starters were delicious but we were a bit disappointed with our steak main course, it was nothing special and for the price would expect more. If we went again we would just get all the snacks/starters as they all looked amazing and avoid the mains as more of a risk!

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Wonderful Irish restaurant with views of the Liffey. Excellent Cod and also the Fish Platter. Clean flavours of farm to table recipes

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Cozy restaurant space with great food and wine cocktails! It doesn't have a kid friendly menu so definitely check before you go to make sure there is something the kids will like to eat.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
Really beautiful dining room and service

Food was great and the steak was Cooked to perfection. Also greens were crunchy and fresh which I love.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: We meet a couple of lovely Dubliners on the west coast. They recommended The Winding Stair when we passed through Dublin. They were right and we weren't disappointed. Great food. Loved it.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Absolutely amazing. Have been here a few times now and think the quality of the menu, produce and the team really make this a fantastic experience. We had the crab and the fish board to start and then the haddock and the lamb and everything was stellar. Washed down by a very reasonably priced MaconVillage. Marvellous! Thanks to the team who looked after us well throughout a memorable evening.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Nice restaurant and great atmosphere.   Simple menu but with good choices, food was tasty, well presented and well cooked.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Wow - great meal in the heart of Dublin. This second floor has giant windows - try and get a window seat. The favorite meal was the smoked haddock. The Bixby potatoes was a close second. Mussels weee excellent and a nice portion. Lamb and steak

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: The food was pretty good but overpriced for what it was. We booked a table to have a great view, and they seated us in the back, far from the windows. I know you roll the dice on these things, but if you don‚Äôt have the view, the price is too high for the food.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: One of best food I had in Dublin with out a question, menu was only couple of choices but it is preferred from my side knowing every dishes would be prepared with love, they changed menu from time to time so it is always new experience, place is ok has ok view but service was one of best in long time all the time we had some one asking do we need anything or is everything ok but not to intrusive so you don't feel jumped, as soon as starters were finished table was cleaned and prepared for main dish same was after main dish and before desert but again it was not intrusive, would recommend and will visit again.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Food is delicious and quality is extremely good! The place is located right in the heart of Dublin over a old and well known book store. We dined here over New Years and alright it was delicious, if I conceded the price and the service is it was little over priced. I would still recommend but it was not enough for 5 stars. Happy new year!

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Wonderful food and an even better atmosphere. Good, creative vegetarian options too! If I had one complaint, more Irish beer options would have been nice.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text:
Amazing food and service.
The steak was sooooo delicious ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: I came here with a group of coworkers for dinner.  The restaurant is literally up a winding staircase and is just across the river from the Temple bar area.  They have an open concept and you can see right in the kitchen which I really like.  The menu is simple and short and the food high quality with a good pace to the service.  I had the Irish Seafood Chowder, which was a white chowder loaded with fish.  I wish they had pulled the mussels out of the shell as it was clumsy to get the meat out of the shell in a soup, but I did really like the soup.  I had the hake for the main and it came over a cheddar mash and was simply amazing.  The wine list was good, but the prices seemed too high.  The service was very good and overall I recommend.

name: The Winding Stair
review_text: Such a cute looking place, overlooking the Liffey. The wine was really good. Was unfortunately really disappointed with the food, although I am vegetarian so maybe their meat options are a lot better, wouldn‚Äôt recommend as a vegetarian though. The waiter we had was so rude as well :(

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: This was the best meal I had in 9 days across Ireland, and, was the best steak I've ever had in my entire life of steak-eating. The cook on the steak was a perfect medium rare, the steak on its own tasted heavenly, and the creamy potatoes and garlic butter were a big compliment to the steak. I also ordered a side of sugar pit bacon which the sweetness of helped cut the richness of the steak and potato. I used most of the garlic butter in the potatoes, because the steak was just so good on its own with flaky sea salt. I sat down for dinner around 16:45 and was served by 17:00, and gone by 17:25. The waiter was very kind and very knowledgeable and explained a great deal of information to me regarding the steaks they had available. The drink, Checked Out, was really well done. I enjoyed that I could actually taste cocoa and cherry and it wasn't just overloaded with whiskey. I honestly could not have asked for a better last meal in Ireland during my vacation. Would highly recommend you stop in and enjoy a cut of Irish beef.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Loved my visit to this FX Buckley and would highly recommend. Starters were delicious and got sharing steak/sides for main which was well worth the price. I had mentioned it was my boyfriends birthday a few weeks previous when booking and they remembered and brought out a free dessert with candle. Service was outstanding, very attentive and friendly staff. It can be a little too loud at times but I guess that depends on the groups also present. Can't wait to come back.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Originally a butcher F.X. Buckley now has a few amazing stake restaurants as well in Dublin. The location is great, atmosphere in the restaurant is amazing, and the service is helpful and attentive. We had the Porterhouse plate for two, and it‚Äôs the best stake I‚Äôve ever tried. The meat is of amazing quality and the charcoal grill gives it an interesting twist and makes it taste even better. The starters, sides and dessert were all amazing. The price corresponds to the quality, so it‚Äôs a bit in the expensive side, but we‚Äôll worth it

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: This was by far the best meals we had in Dublin and I will go as far as saying one of the best meals I ever had.  I recommend ordering one of the shared steaks "for two" as it comes with so many extras as compared to ordering a single steak.  Service was excellent and the food was delicious.  Next time I will skip the appetizer.  The meal was plenty and the scallops we ordered were very small and in my opinion way overpriced.  All in all FX Buckley for the win!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
Honestly, the best steak I‚Äôve had in my entire life and so perfectly priced! Felt like we should‚Äôve paid more.
Over in Dublin for a few days and this place was exactly what we needed after a busy day of travel. Excellent service, waiters were all friendly and helpful, even talking you through each cut of steak and what the best choice was!
Great visit, great food, we WILL be back!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Book in advance, it's well worth it! Excellent value for the best steak I've ever had. Will definitely return, if and when I'm back in Dublin. Great attention to detail by the staff who did everything they could to accommodate an additional late booking a few days later for my friend.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: I probably had the best steak I ever had, 22 Oz Tenderloin on the bone. Every single penny worth, I could have eaten an other one. üòÅ. The pepper sauce... What shall I say, a dream. You need nothing more than that.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: I had my birthday dinner here and I was unimpressed. My overall impression is that they put a lot of effort to get quality meat, which is actually really good, but completely ignore all the rest. I had the pork belly for starters and it was decent but under seasoned. As a main course I chose the ribeye, medium-rare. It was nicely cooked but totally unseasoned, which is frustrating when you're paying a high price for it. It came with a bone marrow jus that sounded promising but it was tasteless and had a slightly bitter aftertaste as if the bottom of the pan had burned. The side dish was a undercooked bland beef tallow chips. For the high price point, it was disappointing.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: PER-FECT! Best dinner in Dublin so far. The whole family was impressed by the food and lovely staff - thank you!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Yeah it slaps. Good meat, well cooked. Good wine selection. A nice setting for a long dinner. Friendly staff, good knowledge of whole menu. Sides all paired well and reasonably priced. Lives up to the hype I guess. Option for large groups.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: I can honestly say that this is the best steak I have ever had. We were a party of 4 hungry men and it was amazing. I had oysters to start and then we had T-Bone with garlic butter, mash and the tastiest crispy onions. The others had rib-eye on the bone, rib-eye off the bone and sirloin. Each steak was perfectly cooked. Followed by really nice desserts and coffee. Would definitely go back.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: This was by far the best meal of our trip! I‚Äôd even rank the steak within the top five of all time for me. Beyond the food the service was excellent and we even got some great recommendations for other bars to visit. Cannot recommend this place enough!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Visited twice. Once on a Friday Night for steak and once on a Sunday for the roast dinner. Both were fantastic. The service was great and the small setting makes for a cozy atmosphere. The portion size of the roast dinner was great!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
Disappointing food
Ordered 2 porterhouses, supposed to be their best, ordered medium rare and came out rare on one and was well done on the ends for the other. Steak itself was not tender and had fat cap running through it. Flavour was good, particularly the smoke from the grill. Was expecting much better though considering the reputation and price. Would not recommend and try other places if you want to try Irish beef.
Waiter was excellent and the drinks were well made.
Sides were pretty good and we liked the starters
But when you tout yourself as one of the best steakhouses in the world and don't get it right you are left disappointed

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: We sure enjoyed their great steak. It was cooked just right and so tender and tasty; especially, with the peppercorn sauce. The Cesar salad was good way to start. We had a glass of red wine to go with our filet. The host was wonderful. He helped us yesterday with making out reservation for dinner tonight. He made us feel right at home. Same was with the other staff members. You should go and enjoy a wonderful meal there, as was the many people dining there!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: I recently dined at this steakhouse in Dublin with a group of nine people, and it was truly outstanding. The fillet and t-bone steaks were cooked to perfection, accompanied by a variety of delicious sides and sauces. The wine selection was excellent, and the staff executed every special request flawlessly. The service was awesome, adding to the overall enjoyment of the evening. I highly recommend this steakhouse for an exceptional dining experience.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
We recently visited FX Buckley on Crow Street, Temple Bar, Dublin and had a great experience. Service was excellent and the food was amazing.
For starter‚Äôs we had Leek and Potato soup with an Onion Scone, the scone was nice and warm and it tasted so nice, as did the soup.
Then for mains, there are lots of Steaks and sizes/weights to choose from too, which are cooked to perfection! A few great accompaniments are Cream Spinach with Parmesan, and Onion Rings are a must, (these were awesome with great batter coating) and some lovely Pepper Sauce to complete it! Couldn‚Äôt actually fit in a desert after all that, but I‚Äôm sure they will be as equally nice. Highly recommend this place and will definitely visit again when we return to Dublin.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Great find in Dublin. Top class steak and I had the oysters, which were DELICIOUS. Bonus points for the random music covers playing in the background. Jazz version of "Never Gonna Give You Up" was brilliant! Friendly service, not cheap but you pay for quality.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
Amazing place with amazing food. Nothing to complain about between the top notch service and the delicious meat. Even their burger (which a steak house rarely does well) was reasonable enough.
Definitely coming here again, but doing so when I'm up for a nice slab of meat.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Meat was perfect, sauces and side all good, only desserts needs some improvements to match how good the rest of the food is

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Second visit here . First one back in 2014 and it‚Äôs still an impeccable place to eat . Not cheap but the quality of food drink and service earns it . A great evening was had by the six of us

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: All of the steaks were perfectly cooked to our liking and the staff accommodated a slight delay in the arrival of some of our party which was appreciated. The meat was tender and delicious but some parts of my steak were slightly salty. Great flavour nonetheless to the rest of it. Scallops were amazing.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Had the most amazing meal here for my fianc√©s birthday. The staff were incredibly friendly and attentive, and the steak was the best either of us ever had. They even brought out a cake for free as we were celebrating a birthday. 10/10

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
I would advise getting the early bird menu as it's by far the best value for money. Off peak hours, it does seem rather expensive compared to the early bird and you'll be kicking yourself.

I thoroughly enjoyed this restaurant, the steak was delicious. The staff were nice and attentive but the middle seats are a bit odd. The place is much smaller than I would have thought.

The desserts were also wonderful, light and refreshing compared to most that make you feel stodgy afterwards.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
Disappointed, as this steakhouse has the best reviews in Ireland.

To be fair, our order came out very quick, however, a few of our fillets had been over cooked (ordered medium rare).

In addition, when looking back on the bill, our group had been charged for extra drinks. May have been a mistake by the staff but I guess we'll never know‚Ä¶

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Absolutely lovely steak, we skipped starters! I had a 16oz ribeye with beef dripping chips and for dessert had the cheesecake! The steak was absolutely perfection, it was done medium rare as requested. I had the Buckley‚Äôs Ale to wash down the food and that was also tip top, came to around ‚Ç¨113 for two people which was surprisingly cheap for the quality of food offered.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Delicious! A bit pricey but the steaks and service were fantastic. 100% recommend this for an upscale dining experience in Dublin

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Excellent Restaurant - oysters, kidneys and beef tartar recommended at most, sunday roast and steaks are the favourites of the locals.  Definitely a must when in Dublin.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Excellent steaks. The porter house for two with all the sides was definitely worth the price tag, you could easily share between three.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Smokey charcoal Porterhouse steak for 2, medium rare. Sides and sauces galore. Good cocktails. Good wine. Lovely service from Greg and the staff. Nice ambiance during early sitting (pre 6pm). Hard to fault. A treat.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
The steaks here were incredible, they cut like butter, were cooked beautifully and tasted amazing.
The waiter brought out a selection of steaks for us to choose from (based on the options selected and was very helpful in helping us decide what steak would best suit us - and boy did they choose well!)
We ate here just before Christmas and the restaurant was very busy, but that in no way lowered the quality of the service or the food.
Would absolutely go back when we visit Dublin again, couldn't recommend more highly.
Also - their cleaver door handle is very cool and original.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Great moment with nice food and exceptional cocktails

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Really cool place. I would say the meat is a solid 4.5 and the sides are a good 4, the overall experience is great!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Great atmosphere with even better food! The quality was unmatched. Staff were professional and appropriately attentive.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Staff were so friendly and accommodating. I visited here with my heavily pregnant friend and they couldn‚Äôt have been more accommodating in ensuring her comfort while seating us. There is a nice subdued lighting which creates a relaxing ambiance. As a butcher there were high expectations for the food which Im glad to say were met. The steak was obviously the star of the show. It was cooked perfect medium as requested, lovely and tender melt in your mouth. I wasnt 100% on the sauce. The accompanying home made chips were really good. For dessert we tried the Double chocolate tart and the blueberry cheesecake. Both were tasty but the blueberry cheesecake wins hands down.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Great range of steaks available and cooked to perfection. Service was excellent just make sure u've deep pockets and enjoy the experience.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Don't miss trying the Oyster here. If you want to get the meat, they come and present different pieces of the meat and explain which one it's better in Rare or medium or other forms. Very friendly staff. High quality food.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: I have already visited several steak restaurants and find this place by far the best among them. Friendly staff, nice ambience and very good food at a fair price, it's worth a visit.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Absolutely incredible. Steak cooked to perfection. Beef dripping cooked chips were to die for. The staff were incredibly welcoming and friendly. Fantastic night!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
As you sit, you get a nice demo of types of steaks.
The waiter was very attentive and the small place could be very busy but not loud. All in all, we enjoyed our dinner.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Quite honestly, the best steak I've ever had. It's definitely a pricey place but once you go in, you know why. Food is impeccable while the atmosphere is authentic, fitting and premium.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: A fancy yet simple meal. I got the sunday roast and it was simply amazing. Both the generosity in portions and friendliness of the staf contributed the amazing experience I had. I can see myself become a regular customer.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
This restaurant is always fabulous to go to . The service is super and the steaks are amazing.  I suggest booking

It is with a heavy heart I need to amend this review . The last time we were there it seems to be under new management or something.  Organisation was all over the place . My cocktail was not nice , more importantly my steak was average at best . Service was not very good . It really disappointed us as we loved it here .

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
Unbelievable quality and cooking of steak. Chewing the steak was effortless as it was so fresh. The chips were the one of the best I've ever had too. The seasoning mix that is on each table was delightful and added a extra dimension to the food we ordered. Peppercorn sauce served with the steak was exquisite.
Staff were friendly and restaurant was lavish. Place was clean and spotless. Prices were on the high end but definately worth a try if you're a steak lover.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Fancy presentation of all the different meat cuts. The steak was nicely presented, perfectly cooked. The side dishes were great as well. Wonderful experience

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
An exquisite food
Such a great experience
The steak was amazing

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text:
Still and always the best!
And the nicest French waiter, it's always a.pkeasure to see you again! A la prochaine!

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Pate was fabulous asked for extra bread which was no problem. My friends had the mussels which were lovely but the bone marrow and the scallops weren't worth the money.I asked for a rare steak but came out medium sent it back and was given a rare with an apology which was lovelyand the chips and gratin were amazing.

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: The best steakhouse I have been so far in Ireland. I booked a table for 2 on Thursday and they have our table ready 10min in advance. The waiters were really kind and receptive. Our food were just amazing and delicious. I will go back soon with friends. Fantastic ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

name: FX Buckley Steakhouse Crow Street
review_text: Amazing food. Top steakhouse in Dublin

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: To say this was an experience was putting it mildly. I‚Äôd eaten in ‚Äúold‚Äù Chapter One and loved it, but new Chapter One is something else. What an incredible culinary treat. You can see the care, attention to detail and creativity that has gone into this menu. Mikael and his team have done wonders and deserve every bit of those 2 Michelin Stars. Highly commendable to both Declan and John. We adored every minute,

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Very strong French base with Asian touch. Impeccable service and good cocktails. The atmosphere is nice and also offers some private dining experiences. Correct price quality ratio considering the 2 stars. Stellar Amuse-bouche.

Limited and expensive wine list as a downside.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Wonderful memorable experience - amazing treats, tastes, textures & surprises - delicious flavours - beautiful artistic presentation. A rare and extravagant indulgence. Excellent service - friendly, expert & professional. Faultless.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: The place is phenomenal from start to finish it's more then a meal it's a whole experience. We were lucky enough to try the 6 course tasting menu with wine pairing and cocktails. From the first moment you walk in the staff are fantastic and couldn't be nicer. I wasn't sure if we would have enough time to start with a drink in the bar but there is no rush at all the staff make you feel at home. The bar is small but it's not why you visit, it's perfect sized as they move you to your table and it's not overcrowded. The range of whiskeys and cocktails is unbelievable and I would definitely recommend starting with one. When the food starts the flavours and presentation is incredible all the way to the last bite. They showed us around the place as it was our first time to visit. The building itself is remarkable with the chefs table in the kitchen and the Midleton room for private dining. I couldn't recommend this place more, it is on the pricey but that's the only thing that could put you off. Or I could say against Chapter One thanks to all the staff for looking after us so well.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Amazing night,  great friendly staff, wonderful food, every mouthful enjoyed,  not a bad course or morsel eaten

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: One of the few two michellin star restaurants in Dublin. The staff are top-notch and very elegant. Despite being sceptic at the beginning and being a vegetarian, was quite blown away by what I experienced. High attention to detail and wonderful experience. Highly recommended.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: An amazing lunch at Chapter One! Delicious food and flawless service in beautiful surroundings. As you can see from the photos the food is of an incredibly high standard.  Every single mouthful is delicious. The service is exceptional while keeping the atmosphere relaxed. A total treat!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
We had my birthday dinner with the tasting menu, got blown away with the top quality of produce and culinary skills.
Lovely people, beautiful environment with great service.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: When I last ate here three years ago, it was the best meal and dining experience I'd ever had. This week, it's certainly been topped. You can taste the extra Michelin star. Photos can't do it justice. It's worth booking months in advance, and not just for an occasion, but as an occasion of its own.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Great atmosphere and food.
Great place to experience food at his best.
The only downfall was the cheese selection\choice.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: A wonderful experience! We had the pleasure of having the Chapter One lunch earlier. Service was superb - relaxed, knowledgeable, and friendly.  Food was delicious with an element of surprise with every course. Service was relaxed, and we were allowed to stay for a couple of hours. Even though it's expensive, I think the lunch menu is excellent value for what you receive and the fabulous experience from start to finish. The best restaurant in Dublin in terms of food and service, it just gets better every time. Irish coffees lovely to top everything off! Thank you for the special treat and memories.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Totally enjoyed the experience,  the staff and food were absolutely superb. We had the chef's table and it was fantastic to see all the buzz and activity

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Went to Chapter One last month. Top 5 meals I have ever had in my life. Absolutely wonderful from start to finish.

The staff were wonderful, the ambience superb and just a lovely place to be. The food is out of this world and I couldn‚Äôt recommend this restaurant more. Perfection in every way and the benchmark for fine dining.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
The chef‚Äôs table is the experience of a lifetime; you get to interact with the chefs and observe the action like a kid in a candy store. If you love cooking and fine dining, go for the chef‚Äôs table - you‚Äôll experience the bustle and heat of the kitchen with extra attention put on your experience.
The food is divine as expected, and the service extremely happy, energetic and friendly.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Wow. Incredible food. We had a 3 course lunch and it worked out at a very reasonable ‚Ç¨55 each including a tip (no wine). Lovely restaurant, great staff, very interesting and delicious flavours. I had the braised beef cheek for my main. It was incredibly tender and the red wine jus was incredible. I would normally expect to pay a lot more for such a gourmet experience. Staff were fantastic and the chef came out and chatted with us about our food. I would highly recommend this Michelin star restaurant. Thanks!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
