review_text: Liked it here. The dining room strikes a nice balance between traditional and modern. It feels luxurious but not stuffy. Staff are warm and sociable in a way you don‚Äôt usually get in high-end restaurants. We went for the pre-theatre menu ‚Äî it was good, but not outstanding. Starter of ravioli were delicious: incredibly fine pasta and rich, mellow cheese. The main course of venison was well cooked but lacking a bit of excitement. Dessert of milk and honey textures was slightly bland, for all the skill and processes involved.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: A truly magnificent meal. Also really enjoyed the buzz of all the coming and going in the kitchen that could be seen at the chef's table.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Went for the lunch set menu, it was really nice. The room is bright and spacious, the staff very friendly and professional, food really good. Didn't leave hungry at all after two canapes, starter, main and desert + bread and butter, pairing wines and Irish coffee prepared live in a very "showy" way. Definitely recommend as a "test" if not sure about going for the full tasting menu (you'll pay less than half): definitely good value for money, if you consider what you might pay around half the price in any Dublin normal/expensive restaurant for mediocre food and service. We will come back for sure for another occasion!!!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
So... where to begin.
I visited Chapter One in August with a friend. I was prepared to blow my budget, I just knew it was gonna be pricey.

But, all I can say is that, if you love food, and appreciate the art that food can be, it was,and is, worth every penny.

We went for the tasting menu and wine pairing because why the hell not. Its not an experience you can do every day.

To say our minds were blown and tastebuds truly satisfied would be an understatement.

Wines were paired perfectly, the staff were attentive and funny, not overly stuffy which you may expect from such a fine place. And the food! Well the lobster dish was top class, it came with this insane lobster bisque and risotto...insane. we also got 3 desserts and the lavender ice cream with crystallised fennel was so unique and surprisingly delish.

I could go on but I won't. If you have a good budget, go here for a celebration or go here if you appreciate amazing fine food and excellent service. Give them another star üåü

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Fantastic food, so creative it's almost a shame to eat it, staff were lovely. Quite pricey but the ingredients and presentation are top notch, so you get what you pay for.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Have eaten here twice in recent weeks, and a number of times previously and I can honestly say it‚Äôs just getting better and better. The food has a refined quality and the raw ingredients are clearly excellent. I love the dining room and the private/semi-private dining options are fabulous as well. Staff are excellent. Perfect service without being overly stuffy, they are friendly and personable.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Had the most perfect meal! From the mouth watering snacks like the beef tartare and the cheese puff and then the main scallop and lobster, every course was a dream! The service team were so friendly, helpful and so knowledgeable about each dish, I was so impressed! Honestly will be daydreaming about that truffle sauce with the Anjou pigeon!

Fully recommend!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Food and wine was just fabulous and atmosphere was so relaxing and refreshing. We had reserved our special birthday and anniversary booth which made the evening more private and romantic. We went for tasting menu with matching wines. It was the best choice we could have made because wine matched food just perfectly, taste was so complementary and made food pop even more. I recommend everyone to try out the tasting menu as the food was just unreal. All my tasting buds were excited. Just amazing.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
This is somewhat a belated review as we were there on March of 2016.  Overall, the experience was positive. The atmosphere was cozy and it was the first time I'd experienced very talkative serving staff and clientele.  Obviously Chapter One has a number of regulars who all like to converse and did not strike me and my wife as a Michelin starred restaurant.

This feeling was however short lived as we too got into the fun and conversed with the locals who gave us great tips on places to see and restaurants to try.

Now, onto the food.  We went with the 5-course tasting menu.  Presentation was fine however,  the mushroom risotto was a bit on the salty side.  The wine pairing were quite complementary to the dish.

Service was good and overall experience was positive.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: I am a former chef and current business owner who has traveled the world for nearly 20 years, during which time I have focused much attention on culinary arts.  I have done culinary focused trips in most major cities from NY to Paris to Tokyo to Dubai.  I have been to half of the 3-starred Michelin restaurants in the world, among other things.  I can honestly say that Chapter One is one of the very best experiences I have ever had anywhere.  It is far and away the top restaurant in Dublin and I've been to most of the other places in town that are in this conversation.   When I went to Chapter One the conversation was over.  Clearly the best.  The kitchen here is creative on a level not often paired with such masterful technique and flavor fusion.  As of March 2023 they were truly in their best form.  Just a week prior I had done a 10-day culinary explorarion in Paris and when I got back to Dublin this place beat anything I had tried recently.  You will not be disappointed.   If I could give it more than a 5 point review here I would.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Had the lunch for 65 euro each. Both of us were delighted with the experience and staff were very helpful. The taste was amazing and beautiful interior.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Fabulous experience. Food sublime and service impeccable.  Unfortunately  we arrived 45 mins late but were greeted with a warm welcome and understanding. Thank you!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Had the pleasure of visiting for the second time last Saturday. After looking forward to our booking for a number of weeks our high expectations were exceeded.
The tasting menu was absolutely faultless from the canap√©s to the petit fours. If I could have the foie gras starter for every single meal from now on without inevitably developing gout in my mid-30‚Äôs I would.
The service was also spectacular. We were mainly served by the wonderful Olmo who even remembered us from our previous visit last year (hopefully for a good reason).

Already planning our return visit.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
I‚Äôm not used to such fancy places but had a great experience at Chapter One.

All the staff treated us really well and the food is amazing, really tasty and beautiful. Also got invited to visit the kitchen, which was a great extra treat.

I‚Äôd go again on their pre-theater menu as it fits my pocket better but highly recommended if you‚Äôre ready to pay for it.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Food was amazing, service was amazing, and the ambiance and decor were fantastic too. I will definitely go back and would recommend it to anyone. We went for lunch, three courses for ‚Ç¨39 which was great value. The atmosphere was fairly laid back (I was wearing jeans and a shirt). If you go, order an Irish coffee, they make it in front of you at the table.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Historic location, below a museum; impeccable services as per expectation; menu is creative, a combination of exotic ingredients with a unique twist on preparation and combination.  While there is no ‚Äúmust-have‚Äù to recommend, every course is a journey of its own.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Amazing, worth every cent!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: The absolute best dining experience we've ever had, anywhere. Every single item was perfection. We just didn't want it to end. We almost forgot there was a pandemic going on and just escaped for the moment with the pleasant vibe. Would highly recommend for a special occasion!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
I was in Dublin for 5 days attending a training session. I took the opportunity to nip out one evening to Chapter One as I'd heard a lot about it. So glad I did!
Food was superb with innovation and technique combing to great effect. Beautifully presented, interesting and above all damned tasty dishes just kept coming! Also the matching wines were  brilliant with 3 that I couldn't initially envisage working with the dish but to my surprise were brilliant matches. In particular a Pedro Ximinez matched with the amazing milk and honey dessert was amazing.
Service too was warm and genuine throughout. All in all a memorable experience in all the right ways!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Pice and quiet atmosphere. The lunch menu was perfect and very delicious,  amazing mix tastes in one dish! Irish Wiskey Coffee making was like a luxury performance! The best my coffee makibg experience!!!Strongly recommended Chapter One 2 Michelin stars!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely stellar service, attentive but in no way pushy. I am a pescatarian and was blown away with the fish dishes. Staff were beyond helpful, Cannot recommend this place enough.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Staff excellent .Food amazing if you like fine dining this is definitely place to go

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Simply the finest restaurant in the country.
The food is incredible, the service is top class and friendly without being over the top.
The best meal I have ever had.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: So glad to have made a point to dine here during my weekend getaway to Dublin. (Pre-Covid) The staff was super friendly, ambiance was classy and cozy, food was delicious. If we are ever able to travel abroad again I‚Äôd definitely love to come back to this spot!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely amazing.  Everything was amazing from the very start to finish. The canap√©s were extraordinary burst of flavours.  The starters were stunning I loved the Comte souffl√© and the foie gras signature dish has been refined further from the Green house days.  Lobster as the fish dish at lunch was such a treat.  And the sweetbreads were to die for.   The price tag was hefty but I had plenty wine and a few glasses of champagne.  I hope they get a third star soon as I have never had a meal like that before

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Fantastic meal! Service was extremely good with everything you would expect from a restaurant with such a good reputation. Food was beautifully and perfectly prepared. The beef in particular was perfectly cooked and the dessert was simple amazing. Highly recommend this place.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Superb! Absolutely  flawless,  food is really  tasty and great presented. Service was a top notch, a lots of passion delivered  from the start to finish.  Very  recommended,  and definitely will back!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: My wife and I went here. One of the best restaurants I've eaten at. Staff is very professional and helpful. Highly recommended

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Really exceptional food, presented exquisitely. Service is wonderful, explanations are given of each, glorious dish. A delightful experience. Chapter One lives up to, and exceeds, its terrific reputation. Well done, Ross & great team

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: I had dinner with my husband, we really love every dish. Just the dessert we‚Äôre expecting to be more impressive. Good service and fantastic Sommelier. Decoration the restaurant beautiful, elegant and cosy. Thanks for a lovely dinner!!

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Truly amazing. While too expensive to make a regular occurrence, still the food and overall experience was beyond anything I have had the pleasure in Dublin

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: We made reservation several months ago and I was afraid my expectations were too high. How wrong I was, my expectations were far exceeded. Art and taste in a dish. Tasting menu pairing with amazing wines.. What I liked the most was when chef came to our table. Thank you to all the professional staff, especially Jimmy,  Exceptional experience.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Just amazing! We managed to get the chefs table for lunch, and what an experience it was. Kitchen team are on a different level and produce some of the best and creative dishes you will ever taste. Service is 10/10 and so attentive & they notice the fine little things!

The beetroot soup as an amuse-bouche kicked off the whole experience and you know from then on that you are in for a treat! Souffl√© for dessert was the best I have ever had! Well done to everyone involved as this is by far the best restaurant in the country! Thank you.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text: Lovely food for a special occasion, excellent service and the quality of the wine was also a standout.

name: Chapter One Restaurant
review_text:
Almost perfect.
Modern restaurant, service was more than excellent.
The raviole of Cr√®me de parmesan was amazing.
With regards to the main I didn't appreciate the association with the pudding.
Cr√®me au chocolat Guinness, very good.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
There are only few seats in this restaurant, and I was very lucky to get a bar seat without booking. (So remember to book! But also feel free to walk-in and ask :)) Service is really great they are very kind.

Food is amazing although it seems that they've made adjustments to their menus (comparing to photos on Google). The dessert is a bit sweeter than I expected but still very lovely. Overall, I would definitely revisit if I have a chance to come to Dublin again!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
A fine dining restaurant that combines sophisticated original fusions with Irish flavour. Everything was very tasty, it was an interesting taste journey!

It is definitely an original place. A cramped restaurant with a few tables, lots of paintings, and an open kitchen from which the smells and hot air from cooking come.

I was surprised when the waitress brought the bill when we were still eating and said we had 15min left to leave, as they had another reservation after us. In a restaurant of this class, where prices start at 60eur per person, this is unacceptable. It is certainly not a place where you can sit, talk and quietly enjoy the cuisine.

All in all, it is a place of a very high culinary standard that lacks space and time comfort.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Just chose this place on a whim and absolutely loved it. The wait staff were amazing, and the food was so tasty. Keep in mind its more of a price fixed menu with various options for how many courses you receive. Knocked a star off because the portions are heavy/dense, which is great in some cases but it makes a three course meal nearly impossible to finish. That and there is a really strict seating capacity. You will likely have to book in advance, or if you walk in, be prepared to stick to your timeline! Still would HIGHLY recommend for a nice evening out!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: What a delicious and delightful experience this is a must if you want something that is high quality and excellent presentation. The food was amazing, our complement to the chef.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
We had a booking for Saturday night for 2 hours slot as a party of 4. As a slow eater, 2 hours felt quite rush to be able to enjoy the whole set menu.
Even though the portions were generous and the food was delicious, the prices are a bit expensive.
My personal favorite was risotto and the hake fish. The meat was decent.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
I recently visited The Vintage Kitchen and had a decent experience. While the food was good, it wasn't the best I've ever had. I suggest seafood risotto for sure! The prices were also a bit steep for what was offered, so I think it could be a bit cheaper. Additionally, they only have set menus available, which was a bit disappointing as I would have preferred to order a la carte.

That being said, the service was prompt and the atmosphere was pleasant. If you're looking for a quick bite (~2 hours) or a place to grab a meal with friends, this restaurant is worth checking out. While there is room for improvement, I think it has the potential to become even better with some tweaks to the menu and pricing.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Beautifully plated food that tastes even better. Creative dishes and a must when you are in Dublin! Yum! Get a reservation in advance. Walk-ins are hard with more than one.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Small hip restaurant. Modern interior. Excellent food creatively presented. Pleasant, very friendly. Reservations is a must‚Ä¶two seatings 2 hours.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: We were lucky enough to get a table here at short notice. Staff were very attentive. There is lots of interesting artwork to look at as well as being able to see into the kitchen. Although the space is small you don‚Äôt feel like you are being squashed by the next table. The warm brioche roll and duck butter was delicious, we enjoyed our starters and the surf and turf was excellent - there was plenty of fish and the meat was cooked perfectly. We had the mango dessert and the cheese to finish, both were ok. Maybe we were just too full at that stage!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Great restaurant close to the city center of Dublin. Very good value for Dublin prices. Cozy environment, casual decoration, great service and fantastic food. Without a doubt a hidden gem.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Service was very good, almost Michelin star.
However the food (although well presented) was a big let down and extremely overpriced for the quality.

My starter was Irish pudding which was essentially a large liver/lamb/blood sausage in bread crumbs. Big, dry and un-appetizing.

The mains were bad, my partner got the sesame pork belly and scallop which resulted in a large block of pork fat and a fishy tasting/smelly scallop, unappetising, who would want to eat a large block of pure fat!? Only had a sliver of actual pork meat.

I got a massive, tough piece of steak which was a chore to get through as there was nothing special to the meat although it was cooked well. With a sort of pickled ginger on top which did nothing for the steak.
The potatoes were great, though, probably the best dish of the entire meal.

My dessert was a 'cake' with ice cream. Same quality as a chocolate muffin and ice cream in a  Supermacs.

Altogether, 65e for those 3 courses per person. Should be max 40e for the quality of food. Felt disappointed and ripped off. (For example, Six By Nico does 6 courses for 60e)

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Such a little gem. Made a reservation and it did not disappoint. They seat exactly for the time, so no need to arrive early. The meal is so delicious and well thought out and full of flavour. Lots of locals frequent this sweet little spot and the restaurant is vibrant with amazing energy. 10/10 would recommend.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: This meal was a gastronomical experience that left me full but still wanting more. The chef outdid himself. Looking forward to try more dishes.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
We reserved a table for the Saturday 5pm sitting. The servers were very quick and attentive in seating us. The restaurant itself is very small and only seats roughly 20 diners (9 small tables and 2 bar seats) at a time, which is why you only have your table for 2 hours for quick turnover.

The 3 course fixed menu has a decent variety, you have a choice of 3 starters, 3 mains and 3 desserts. Note there is no al a carte option. To accompany our meal, we ordered a bottle of Merlot.

We ordered the housemade goats cheese, fig, tomato starter (which was served on an interesting glass plate) and smoked haddock with prawn reduction. For main course we had the crispy pork belly with a rich truffle risotto and beef fillet en croute, which came with a potato crisp and brie mushroom sauce. We were surprised with the large portions of meat in this course. We finished our meal with a mango pudding with meringue and a fresh out-of-the-oven half baked chocolate cake with vanilla ice cream.

Very enjoyable meal and glad we tried this small sought after restaurant.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: We were welcomed with no booking as a party of five. Absolutely stunning food and presentation. I honestly think it‚Äôs the best Surf and Turf I‚Äôve ever had in the world! This little gem is highly recommended!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: This was place is quite the gem! I highly Recommend making a reservation. Everything from the decor, the staff, the surrounding, and especially the food were excellent. If I can make any recommendations, the prawn risotto to start, followed by the lamb, and then the mango dessert were all divine. There pre-dinner drinks are quite refreshing as well. If in Dublin for the first time, this is quite the treat to satisfy your palate.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
I was brought here for my birthday and I was amazed by the food in this place. Not taking away from the service, which in itself was truly excellent, I was taken back by the food I had.
Usually there would be one course that would let the meal down but not here. Each course exceeded what I was expecting and the flavours in each course worked incredibly well together.
I loved the decor in the place. The atmosphere was relaxed and laid back and the whole experience made my birthday one to remember.
I will definitely be going back to try some of the other food and I would highly recommend it to everyone.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
I went on a whim, when looking for a fine dine near the Airbnb I was staying. The place is usually full, (I've heard) I got lucky and got seated within 5 min. The servers were attentive, friendly and informative. Loved the atmosphere and the vibe. I had the chef's special 3 course meal. OMMFG! The risotto was freaking amazing! The best I ever had! Every dishes were awesome!

Only thing bad thing I will say is that... I dined alone and it was a shame not to share the experience with anyone.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Thus far, my favourite dining experience in Ireland in 3 years. The ambience was perfect, the staff ridiculously attentive without being overbearing, and the food simply SCRUMPTIOUS! The flavours were all so powerful but perfectly balanced. They didn't make a single misstep so I couldn't imagine giving them anything less than 5 stars.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Slightly disappointed with our meal, food wasn't as good as first time I was here a few years ago. Restaurant seems to have lost a bit of its magic, eccentricity and personality that it once had. Service was good, the food was nice not great. Goats cheese parfait was a bit bland, main course was much better, beef wrapped in pastry was excellent, panna cotta was again just fine, nice. For ‚Ç¨65 a head with no tea or coffee included it felt a little over priced. Overall still a nice restaurant but won't be running back.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Got a late booking here recently for a party of 4.
Food was absolutely delicious.
I had the chicken wing with beef for starter. Very rich, hearty dish. The standout for the starters was the pate with beetroot jam.
For the main I chose the beef wellington as a friend is somewhat of a wellington aficionado. It didn't disappoint.
My partner had the cod which received no complaints.
Wine list was a little short but we chose a delicious bottle which hit the spot.
It was not overly busy on the night but service was still very good. We were never rushed and plates were cleared appropriately. Price was very reasonable.
Another bonus is the restaurant is right next door to arguably the best pint of Guinness in Dublin. (Mulligan's)
Overall we were very impressed and will definitely be back.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Very small and unassuming restaurant but the food is amazing.

Very hearty and soulful, perfect for autumn when we went.

‚Ç¨40/pp is unbelievable value for the quality you get.

Highly recommend! Booking in advance is a must.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: The seafood chowder was very tasty. A big portion for a starter. I couldn‚Äôt manage a main course after that. My partner had the duck and it was tender and had barely any fat on it. The accompanied gravy went along well with the duck and potatoes. The staff was attentive despite being very busy. Reservation is needed as the place is quite small and very popular it seems. I would go back for more chowder, should I return to Dublin one day.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: All the dishes we tried were wonderful. Make sure you are hungry because the portions are huge! The beef and the chowder were some of our favorites. Make sure to book in advance, the place is very small, but it is worth it.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
The service could have been much better. We where not told about the specials and only found out about them when people around us started ordering them.

The food was made with amazing ingredients, however; the dishes are severely lacking. The spin on beef Wellington was terrible. The loin was blue and the puff pastry was very undercooked. The desert cheese plate was also a huge disappointment. It was supposed to have a pear compote, but it was just a few drops with a couple grapes with seaweed. Why would you put seaweed on a Camembert cheese? For desert it should be with something sweet like figs and and actual pear compote.

When you charge 65‚Ç¨ per person the food needs to be spot on. This was not it.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Food is not good.  Set menus for 65 but worth 30 at best.  I ordered the haddock appetizer which was more like a salty and fishy jerky.  Main course I ordered the beef in puff pastry and that was bad as well.  Puff pastry burned on the outside, uncooked and doughy soggy mess on the inside.  Beef was extremely blue and unseasoned.  And the desert was a cheese plate which consisted of a supermarket grade slice of Brie topped with 3 grapes and seaweed.  So weird and zero creativity or effort.
I really wanted to like this place; it seemed exclusive and cozy but it‚Äôs overrated

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: My boyfriend and I visited here for dinner last week and had a great time! It was such a quaint lovely dinner environment and the food was unbelievable. For a menu with courses, there was lots of choice which was nice and we also enjoyed their red wine. Would definitely recommend this spot to anyone looking for a local small dining experience

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Delicious food and amazing staff!
Reservations recommended, but we were lucky enough to be seated without one.
We had the Cajun seafood chowder and the risotto with chorizo and red hot chili peppers. Recommend this place 100%

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
We went on the recommendation of a friend and were not disappointed.

The menu is relatively small, but there is a lot of variety in the dishes, I started with a duck liver creme which was delicious, followed by steak wrapped in a pasty, almost like an individual Beef Wellington, which came with some mini hash browns - a really unusual and great touch.

Wine list was good, but should really be extended now it is no longer BYOB. Overall excellent and highly recommended.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Made reservations for my SO‚Äôs birthday during our visit to Dublin. The place opened up at 6pm and filled up pretty quick. You have the option to do the 2 course meal or the 3 course meal with dessert. By the end of this meal, I was so stuffed I couldn‚Äôt do dessert. I got the seafood chowder as my starter and I have to say it was absolutely amazing. My second course was the beef fillet, which I enjoyed but I was still thinking about that seafood chowder. My SO got the lamb shank as his entree and said it was super good. Would highly recommend this place. Staff was also kind and welcoming.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: A cozy restaurant with friendly and warm staff. The food was excellent, I had seafood chowder which is recommended. The chef was passionate about his food and eating was one of the highlights of my 4-day visit to Dublin

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Staff were lovely, atmosphere was great and the food was superb! We ordered the goats cheese, Cajun chowder, prawn & chilli risotto and a special main of cod, scallops & truffle risotto. Everything was delicious. Cannot wait to return.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Excellent food and service. We had the goats cheese and risotto of herbs and for the main the plaice as a special and the gnocchi. Everything is really top class here

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: First time traveing to Dublin from London. And wow. Absolutely sublime food. Me and my partner agreed this is the best food we have ever eaten. The flavours were complex and everything was 10/10. They brought my desert out with a candle for my birthday which was cute. thank you:)

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Lovely place to visit.  All dishes we had are delicious. And the staff are super friendly too.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Very busy eatery even at 8.30pm on a week day. Nice ambience and friendly staff. Food is great. And portion is generous. Same taste as before covidüòÄ

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Cute little place with BYOB! Reservation is necessary if you're going in for dinner as this place is so popular.

Food is absolutely fantastic. I have had few Christmas parties here and you can bring your own booze.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Every food was great Loved the duck butter so much.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Best meal my fianc√© and I have had in ages. The prix fixe menu is a gamble for any restaurant to do regularly, but this place knocked it out of the park with every single thing we had - appetizers, entrees, deserts, and drinks! Every dish was a very modern take on classic Irish cuisine. The culinary highlight of our weeklong trip by far.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: Easily one of the best meals my wife and I have had. Lovely relaxed atmosphere and the waiters were really pleasant and friendly. Definitely recommend.

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
A must for dinner. Make a reservation now.
Small place with attentive service and kitchen in the rear.

Started with Guinness bread with fennel butter. The menu changes and we were lucky enough to have the Cajun chowder which was like a gumbo with a lot more fish, to start with a gluten-free prawn risotto with fresh parsley, cheese and tomatoes. Very flavorful and creamy risotto.

Limited wine menu, although the Tempranillo was a delight.

On another note the owner Sean nicely squeezed in our party of three. A d we enjoyed his varied Spotify playlist.

We are looking forward to coming back on our next visit to Dublin!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
We came here at 2:30 for the set Christmas lunch! It came with some puff bread, a starter, a main, and dessert. For our starters, the three of us had the vintage kitchen Cajun stew, the prawn red pepper chili risotto, and our third friend is vegetarian so she asked for the prawn risotto without the prawn and they offered to make her a special vegetarian risotto which was incredible! The prawn risotto was delicious and I still think about it. There was an abundance of prawn in it that I had prawn in every bite.

Our mains were the pork shoulder wrapped in chicken skin with truffle gnocchi and the acorn squash. They paled in comparison to our starters. For dessert, we tried the cheese board, the chocolate lava cake with ice cream, and the set caramel with limoncello. Wouldn‚Äôt say the cheese board or the chocolate lava cake were anything special but the set caramel with limoncello was unique and tasty! A great mix of flavors.

Overall would recommend coming here for sure and 35‚Ç¨ was a good deal for the quality and amount of food we got. Great way to try a bunch of different things. next time if we come back to dublin I would probably just come back for one dish because it was a lot of food!!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Had such a wonderful meal here. I have recommended it to so many people since I went. The restaurant itself is compact and has around  seating for 26-30. The service was so great, the hostesses very attentive and friendly. The playlist of music they had on was also very good.

All of the courses were so delicious. The smoked haddock starter was my favourite, closely followed by the set mango dessert and the beef on croute main.  I tried some of my dining partners black pudding terrine starter and half baked chocolate cake dessert and would have been happy to have had them all to my self also. We will be back again!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Wonderful restaurant with a very nice atmosphere and friendly service. The room is very tiny, the kitchen included - anyway around 30 people find a spot. Food is presented in a nice way in nice pans and/or on wooden plates.  The drink menu is simple - one white, one red, sparkling wine and that's it. The red wine was fantastic. Water is included. The food was good, my steak was more medium well than medium rare which is the only negative point. However, for the overall experience the vintage kitchen deserves a 5 star rating!
Thanks for the nice evening!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
The best chowder I have ever tested!! Honestly such a cosy place with really great food and lovely service.

If there is one restaurant you should visit while in Dublin, it‚Äôs this!!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
The place is absolutely amazing.. First important thing is its very neat and tidy...second the hospitality is amazing.. the peoples working in the restaurant is fantastic and more over the food is good and last but not the least I'm one of the kichten porter of this restaurant and a blogger too..

And do visit whenever you are in the city. I bet you will love it..

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: The food as usual was fantastic.  Piping hot value for money

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: This place has amazing food. Really loved it. The duck liver cr√®me as a starter was fantastic. Best duck liver I've had. The pork shoulder was very tasty as well. The place is tiny but very cosy and there's lots of great art on the walls. Would recommend!

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text:
Fantastic food, great value, BYOB, it‚Äôs no wonder it‚Äôs one of the top restaurants in Dublin on TA, and deservedly so.

Be warned it‚Äôs booked most nights 12 months in advance, so if you want to go soon lunch is probably your only option. (They are quick to reply to emails for reservations.)

name: The Vintage Kitchen
review_text: They tried to seat me at a bar table for dinner when they had 2 sets of two tables available just because I came on my own. I think that‚Äôs very unprofessional - fair enough for a drink but not for eating meals. Not cool to segregate

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Great food! Each dish was unique and I would have been happy eating any dish my part of four ordered. Definately worth it and we had a lovely time. Water is also included free. My only disappointment was we went here as google maps said they had sticky toffee pudding but they did not. Google maps does not seem 100% up to date in Ireland.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Great place! The smell of the food draws you in and does not disappoint. We had the whole restaurant to ourselves for the first half hour. Beautiful establishment and staff üòä

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
Brought the entire team from India, Romania, and Germany. Everyone was delighted. The place is small and very cosy, the staff are super attentive, fast, and efficient.

The food, whether vegetarian or traditional, was extremely good value for money. The beers were fresh and well poured.

Overall, highly recommended.  Thanks to the Millstone Restaurant team for a lovely evening.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: We had a delicious meal. Top quality traditional Irish food at a very reasonable price. I had the seafood chowder and lamb shank. Highly recommended.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
I was drawn to the Millstone because of the excellent reviews, and their full additional coeliac menu for one of my guests. The service was excellent - the ladies were all very knowledgeable on the techniques used on the menu items, and they paid very good attention to the details of my booking. They were also not overly present around us the whole time, and knew exactly when to check in on us.

We tried a variety of things and everything was excellent: the mussels were some of the best I've ever had (I had to ask for extra bread to not waste the sauce), the salmon, the lamb shank, even the Portobello mushroom dish, all excellent. The cr√®me br√ªl√©e was the icing on the cake!

All I can say is the Millstone deserves every good review it's received, and I'm adding mine to that long list of fans!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
I highly recommend this place üíØ
Offers a Gluten free menu, great selection! I had GF fish & chips, GF mussels & frites, GF garlic, tomato & pesto cheese toast.
My Mom had the stuffed yorkshire starter & lamb shank entree.
Delicious food, wine, & wonderful friendly service.
I recommend making a reservation‚Ä¶
Thank you for making our final evening in Dublin so special!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
Excellent quality / quantity price ratio
13‚Ç¨ for a rather large range of meal for lunch, 7/7, which is very good in Dublin.
Service is very good and the atmosphere is nice.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
We chose this place due to there great deal of a starter and main for ‚Ç¨26.95.

Food was amazing and beautifully cooked, with attentive staff and a calm atmosphere. I will definitely be returning.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: I had my lunch here awhile ago. They place a ‚Ç¨12.95. signed board for lunch meal. I ordered steak and frites with the same price on their menu. But they charged me ‚Ç¨14.95 plus 1 euro for service. Very disappointed! They scammed me! To the management of the restaurant, please be true!!!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Booked this place to celebrate my husband‚Äôs birthday, the lady who‚Äôs served us that evening was very lovely. Food were great! We love them, I had mussels as my main and they were delicious. They sang happy birthday to my husband + a choco mousse to share. Made my husband‚Äôs birthday extra special thank you!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Perfect place to have lunch and good atmosphere. I tasted roasted salmon with salad. It's was delicious. I recommend this place for sure.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
Was here with a group of 16 diners for lunch.

Had a wonderful time.

Staff especially Mattias Andrea and  Caroline were super!

Nothing was a problem to facilitate everyone in the group. Everyone was able to choose from the differing menus without any problem.

Food was freshly cooked beautifully and creatively presented and offered really good value for money given the Christmas period.

All in all an excellent experience and everyone in our group was really happy with their experience.
Thanks everyone!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Me and my partner had an amazing meal here. They offer a good gluten-free menu and the service is outstanding. A must go!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Great stew, greater seafood, the best whisky sour I have ever had going out

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Perfect place to have a dinner in Dublin. Quick serving and delicious. The only issue that they don‚Äôt have Guinness beer - but they served us with another stout option and we liked it.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
We had mussels (good sauce, not many fries or bread though) and desserts (I did like the mousse).

The dinner itself would deserve a 4, but the voluntary-tip-as-part-of-the-bill (for a table of 2) was definitely a mood-killer at the end (didn't even see a warning in the menu like some places had). Final price was not even excessive, this just feels dishonest to do in Europe.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
Best cheese burger ever!!!
The service was impeccable and loved the atmosphere. I loved this restaurant and totally recommend eating here.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
Small restaurant at Dame street with a Vintage vibe. The food here is good. I went in attracted by the garlicky fragrance coming out of the place and had ordered Pesto garlic bread and chicken with fries.
Loved the garlic bread (& the white coloured sauce served with it)! Chicken was too dry for my liking but it was good too.

One thing that could have been improved was if they had the facility to Let customers pack and take away the remaining food if they had ordered too much and do not wish to waste it. I love fries and hated to see them go waste coz I couldn‚Äôt finish it all.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Amazing service. From the moment we stepped in till we left. Gluten free menu has plenty of options and it‚Äôs delicious. Both me and my friend were happy with everything. And thank you for that Baby Guinness ;)

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely delicious meal for all of us! They have gluten free options (best fish and chips I‚Äôve ever had) and the meals are incredible. Also, all of the staff are lovely, patient and knowledgeable. We loved it so much we came back a second night for more!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely delicious! The food is extremely tasty and beautifully presented. This is a must visit if you are visiting Dublin. The staff are amazing and we were lucky enough to sit at a table right in front of the chefs. They are outstanding and the camaraderie and team work between them helps to produce a first class meal. A massive well done to each and everyone of you!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: The piri piri chicken had a nice kick and was very tasty, service was welcoming and attentive, prices were reasonable. I would come back.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: The whole experience was very rushed and it seemed a bit like a canteen. When we arrived we were told we had to vacate the space in 1.5h. As soon as we finished eating our plates were taken and the new course was brought. It was very clear that they wanted to get people in and out as soon as possible. Food was okay for Irish standards. Very bland and not very flavourful but that seems to be the case everywhere in Ireland. Not a place for a relaxed meal though- just be aware of that.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: The host was excellent at accommodating us. Let's say this, you need to make a reservation, as this is a very busy establishment. However we did not make a reservation as we were just out about touring the city got hungry and decided to stop in.  We were lucky enough to seated at one of 2 small tables upon entering the restaurant. It is a bit secluded but understandable given the circumstances. There's a heater to put on to make the dining experience quite comfortable. Food was simply amazing!! I did not know what to expect from a Yorkshire stuffed pudding but it was delicious. Staff is very friendly as well. If ever in Dublin, give it a try. I'd certainly revisit.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Reservations are suggested but we arrived early enough they were able to fit us in without too much fuss and they were very pleasant about it.  I had their Guinness beef stew and my wife their salmon. Both were delicious.  Portion sizes were good. If I had any complaints, I would have liked another slice of their bread to go with the stew.  It was great. But that might have been too much food. Places like this make our trip to Dublin wonderful.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Came here on a Friday night with a reservation which I would recommend doing as it‚Äôs very busy. Food was amazing and the staff were brilliant! I had noted it was my partners birthday when booking and they came out at the end with a dessert plate and sang him happy birthday, was a great touch! Will definitely be back

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: I brought my girlfriend to this restaurant after reading many reviews commending how great and accommodating this establishment was to people with celiacs disease (such as my girlfriend) but realized shortly after that she was not actually served a celiac friendly fish and chips. We asked several times before if it was truly gluten free and were assured that her dish was truly gluten free. We later came to realize that the staff had served her fish and chips with malt vinegar and weren‚Äôt provided with a fresh meal but instead told that ‚Äúthere will be very little gluten‚Äù. My girlfriend ended up having an allergic reaction later that night that could only be described as ‚Äúthe worst she‚Äôs ever had‚Äù which leads me to believe that the fish and chips she was served not actually gluten free but rather a normal fish and chips. If you have celiacs beware when eating at this establishment!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
How this place is only rated 4.3 is beyond me. I had to return to this location for a second time with coworkers so they could enjoy this place as well.

The food here is honestly the best I had in Dublin; obviously fresh vegetables, tender meat, perfectly seased mash and the sauces are excellent. The bartender also makes an incredible gin cocktail.

If in the future I return to Dublin, I will be sure to visit this establishment again.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Fantastic gluten free options, delightful taste. I ate the gluten free toast (best I've ever had), the lamb shank and the creme brulee. Plenty of options, and I'm looking forward to visiting again. Service was fast and polite. They didn't have coeliac beer when I visited but it is on the menu. Highly recommend.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: I really liked the cosy atmosphere. This place seems to attract quite a few tourists and with good reason. You can't go wrong with the fish and chips.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: We sat at near the kitchen which was very busy with walking staff and lots of unpleasant noise from the kitchen and no music. I booked a week before online and had ask for a better table. There were tables free they give them to the persons who were half an hour later than us. The Ober was asking 3 times if we want to order but where looking at the menu. It was very rushed. The vegan burger was terrific and the fish and chips was tasteless/flavorless. We had ordered a nice bottle of wine but after 1.5 hour we are unkindly asked to leave but the wine was not finished yet. We get the receive unasked and the there was a voluntary tip calculated on the receive. When we asked to pay by card the Ober typed in the price inclusive the tip and we said he need to change it. He become angry about that question.  Overall very unpleasant experience and don't recommended at all to anyone.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Absolutely delicious food, wonderful atmosphere. No negatives at all. The staff were lovely. Gluten free menu with gorgeous bread, so didn't feel like I was missing out. The wine list was excellent too.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Delicious food and great service. Get the rib eye, perfect medium rare. Totally recomended.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
My family has gluten free, vegan, and seafood free members. To find a place that meets all of our dietary needs is difficult. Millstone not only met our requirements but far surpassed our expectations.

My fillet was so beautiful it was almost a religious experience. A new religion could be founded on the flavour that exploded in my mouth. It was the purest meat enhanced by a perfect blend of simple spices that never overpowered the meat's natural taste. The sauce made the cut pop, without hiding the true essence of the steak.

My husband's vegan tofu steak was beautifully crafted by someone who knows vegan cuisine and did not try to recreate a meat dish. My daughter's lamb shank was tender, falling off the bone, and perfectly matched with the sauce enhancing all of the subtle flavours of the meat.

My tip: Make reservations. This place is always full, for a reason.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Everything was really nice,tasty, fast and good price

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: The steak and the lamb shank were both delicious, well priced, and cooked perfectly. The rest of the food just okay though, so highly recommend one of those two.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: The Guiness beef stew was not one to amuse the tastebuds. The food was a disapointment but still tip was added to the bill without asking. Overall feeling of the restaurant a bit of tourist trap.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Incredible ! Wonderful decoration, smiling and attentive employees. And it's really delicious (especially compared to local restaurants). Typical dishes (like stew) and served quickly. It became my favorite Dublin restaurant.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
It is a restaurant in the city center. The atmosphere is average, nothing to praise or criticise.
The prices are OK, it is best to get the menu.
The service is nice, really polite people, attentive, and available.
The food is average. The salmon was overcooked and dry, the green beans were flavourless, and the mash potatoes that came with it lacked everything, tasteless. The steak is OK. The fish and chips were the best course for sure. What saved the meal was the cr√®me br√ªl√©e and the chocolate mousse, which were absolutely delicious. They do have a children's menu, which is good.
I do have to commend the fact that they do have a menu specific for celiacs, which is great!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: This was a little hidden gem we found off the may strip. The restaurant was founded in 1909 and it has an awesome vibe inside, wonderful food and excellent service!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
We came in early on a Friday evening and had the two course set menu (~‚Ç¨26 pp). We ordered buffalo chicken wings (with sauce on the side) and calamari for starters and then salmon and fillet mignon for mains.

Food was delicious and service was fast. Could not fault anything hence the 5 star. Chicken wings were fried but without the thick breadcrumbs that you often see in restaurants. We appreciated the fact that they agreed to put the sauce on the side. The buffalo sauce was incredible - I don‚Äôt usually like it (hence the sauce on the side) but this sauce was not too sour and it was creamy. Calamari was huge too

Both the salmon and the beef were cooked perfectly.

Overall we would definitely come back. The quality of the food and the price were really 5 star!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Food is good, but the service is a gong show and the restaurant is really cramped, even for Dublin.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: This was a comfortable, eclectic more upscale restaurant. It has a dedicated gluten free menu where we enjoyed our first meal in Ireland. My husband enjoyed his stew and my salmon was delicious. We thanked our server for his attention to detail and reminiscing about the water bottle with the pop top tab like grandpa had. The downpour of rain that day didn't put a damper on the day due to the relaxing environment and good food.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Went here twice for afternoon lunch- dinner it was so good. Good choice on menu including a gluten free menu. Nice beers on tap. Staff attentive and not clearing table until everyone is finished. Lovely heritage building.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Great restaurant! Was easy to get a reservation, and has a full page gluten friendly menu with lots of options. Highly recommend and priced very reasonably

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: The food was very tasty, the staff was polite, the food was a bit on the expensive side especially for the amount given, but it's still a nice place to eat once in a while!

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Food was tasty, we both got starter and desert. Burger was full of flavour as was the salmon. Enjoyed the Wings as well...just felt the server could be a bit more prim and proper for the setting in which she's working. Was very very noisy (granted it's a Saturday night) overall enjoyed

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text:
Great little spot for some delicious food and great service! If you are gluten free they have an entire menu dedicated to what you can get.
Highly recommended

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: We booked at table during our weekend in Dublin. The process was easy and when we arrived the restaurant had listened to our notes that I was dairy and gluten allergic. The waitress was prepared with knowledge of my dietary requirements and explained which dishes were suitable or could be altered. I didn‚Äôt feel like an inconvenience like I have been made to feel In restaurants at home. She was polite and welcoming, as were all other people we were served by. The food was amazing, one of the best meals we had our whole trip. I would definitely visit again if I were to travel back to Dublin.

name: The Millstone Restaurant
review_text: Really cute place with great style and yummy food! The lamb with roasted veggies and the apple ‚Äúpie‚Äù were delicious. The service wasn‚Äôt that attentive but the live music helped to distract us from the fact we had to wave the waiter down a few times. Lots of gluten free options for those that need it.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: The service here was excellent and the staff were knowledgeable about the gluten free options. The food was good, we will be back to try more of the options. I especially enjoyed the gluten free chocolate brownie, perfect to share after a carb heavy main. ü•Æ

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: We were in the lower level. It was lite up well but still dark and very loud because it was so enclosed. However,  the food was fast, very delicious, and the servers were amazing.  Very friendly and helpful.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: A great place to be at with large groups, food is really good and service is even better, very friendly staff! Book in advance as it gets busy, and I would highly recommend their desserts too. Set menu available for large groups.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Had dinner at Luigi Malone‚Äôs in Dublin city‚Äôs Temple Bar with a large group during a busy night. Loved the atmosphere at Luigi‚Äôs but unfortunately, the place seemed understaffed at the time and as a consequence, the service wasn‚Äôt as quick. Also, it can be hard to get the attention of members of the waiting team.

For dinner, I ordered their vegan pizza which was decent but what I was delighted was were the textures of the pizza, which were similar to that of non-vegan pizza. Reasonably priced gin and tonic too (for Temple Bar anyway). Based on feedback from other members of the group, the food was cheap but the quality was OK. Don‚Äôt expect mind-blowingly excellent food but overall, I think Luigi Malone‚Äôs is a good place for large groups to get decent food and affordable drinks.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Really nice place, big portions for both starter and main,  and the cocktails were fantastic especially the mist one. The meringue dessert felt like a dinner itself.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Ordered the Gnocchi with blue cheese and spinach, so good! The jungle mix mocktail was okay. The Toblerone cheesecake was stunning.

Recommend this place for good pasta and pizza (a friend ordered the margarita, was really crusty and cheesy).

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: I was always a fan of lungi Malones I think the first proper date I ever went on was to this place many centuries ago lol found these old pics on my Google drive and had to share cos the place I don't think has changed I have seen recent reviews and it's still delivering top service always very lively right in the center of temple bar. It's the food heart of good grub at good prices with great speed and staff and ul be bursting after it

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: A treat at the temple bar.  while strolling through the Temple bar region we found this restaurant which was a great surprise, for starters we chose a portion of beef taco which was amazing, for the main courses we chose a BLUE cheese Gnocchi and a Ragu lasagna both were very tasty, just for the gnocchi that came in a small portion compared to the other options.  to drink we ordered an alcoholic lemonade, it was very sweet but we drank it anyway.  I highly recommend this restaurant.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Disappointing. Can‚Äôt really think of another word to say. We‚Äôve wanted to visit for a while because there‚Äôs always people inside and it looks really nice. Well all I can say is that the food is okay. It‚Äôs not amazing but it‚Äôs not bad either. It‚Äôs just okay and because of that it‚Äôs disappointing becase you can‚Äôt complain to them about the food but you can‚Äôt also just say hey I just wanted to tell you your food is just mediocre. So I‚Äôm very upset because we wanted to visit for a while but ultimately the food arrived just medium warm (hot in some places) and on my Burrata pasta I only had a tiny little piece of Burrata on it. For the prices they‚Äôre charging their services nor their food is up to par. Save your money and go somewhere else

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
We went here yesterday for dinner and service was awful staff seemed to ignore the table. We were sat at a table with little to no light so it was dark and gloomy.

The service was slow we were waiting for 20 minutes for someone to ask if we even wanted drinks. Asked for water to the table along with cocktails and this didn‚Äôt arrive and we had to ask the waiter again to bring water.

Food service was slow with Mozzarella missing from Bruschetta which is a ‚Ç¨2 extra. We had to wait 10 minutes to get the mozzarella before we could start eating together.

After starters plates were cleared and it was 30 minutes before we got main courses with no staff checking in or explaining anything to us. We had to ask staff again for an update on when the main courses would arrive.

We were given a free round of cocktails for the delays however this does not make up for bad service. This was appreciated but bad service outweighs anything else in a restaurant.

We won‚Äôt be returning and think they should look at improving service a lot - staff seem to hide away from the dining room in a little private service corner.

‚Ç¨75 for really bad service with no communication. We can understand if a place was extremely busy there would be delays but the restaurant wasn‚Äôt that full and there wasn‚Äôt any communication about delays etc etc.

Please improve service as the food was great but the consistent need to try get a staff members attention made the experience one of the worst we have had.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Came in to Luigi Malones in a rapid heartbeat on St. Patrick‚Äôs Day with the busiest crowd (of course). I‚Äôm surprised we got a reservation during this time. Regardless, it was my dearest friends birthday, and during this national holiday, I asked for the manager or someone in at least a manager position to give us a birthday/holiday deal, any sort of surprise or excitement that would catch everyone off guard. My dear friend is named Patrick, he was born on st. Patricks day, turning 21, we are American and here to celebrate his specific day, and the manager made sure that it was personal. He looked me in the eye, asked what this person looked like, asked what kind of surprise we could give him‚Ä¶

Long story short, we have him a birthday we won‚Äôt ever forget in Dublin, Ireland. He surprised my dear friend Pat with free shot of whisky, gave him a hug from behind, and even had the staff sing with him. This place has only exceeded expectations, not only on top of food and taste, but personality and pleasure. I 100% recommend coming to this restaurant in the heart of Dublin, as the employees will make you feel like you are valued. Yeah, the food was good, but it‚Äôs so much more. Have a good time, send well wishes to the manager, and happy st. Patrick‚Äôs day.

Nice

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Loves the ambience. Being a vegetarian, Pesto Pasta and Vegetarian was too good. My friends tried Chicken Fajita and Chicken Burger, they loved it. Have to mention this Dilek was so friendly and accommodating. She recommended the Pesto Pasta, it was worth it. Overall it was a great experience.
owner_answer: Hey Nikhil Thank you for taking the time to review Luigi Malones and for your 5 star review, sound one! üòÉ Delighted to hear you enjoyed your experience at Luigi.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Some dishes were lovely! Ragu and wings in particular!
The pesto pasta was very oily, the lasagna was not good at all and the atmosphere was very loud and manic!

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: The food it's regular, like an average restaurant in Dublin, prices little bit higher. But the staff was really lovely, the food that we ate was like we ordered, and the environment was ok as well.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Absolutely adore the decor and aesthetic of this place. It‚Äôs such a gorgeous environment! The food is a bit pricey but delicious.

Just to note, the Chicken and Prawn pasta is a little on the spicy side - something that I wasn‚Äôt quite aware of from the menu description. The lasagna was incredible though (dish pictured in the background) - I would definitely order that next time! Overall good experience.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Lovely restaurant.  Food was very tasty and good-sized portions. Staff were lovely and service was great.  Chicken fajitas were delicious, and so was the Toblerone cheesecake.  Only our 2nd time there, but we'll definitely return again.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: The portions are huge so be prepared. We planned to have the 3 courses but after 2 courses we were full. The chicken burger was very good and huge! The chicken wings starter was great as were the nachos. Highly recommend.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Food was amazing and it‚Äôs not Temple Bar prices considering where it‚Äôs located. Portions are very generous too. Staff were very friendly too. They‚Äôve a huge space downstairs that would be ideal for party or group bookings

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
This restaurant was really nice. The staff were extremely friendly and the service was flawless. Drinks were spot on, and the atmosphere was great! (We ate yesterday evening, a Saturday).

My only issue was that the steak I ordered as rare appeared to only have been cooked for 20 seconds a side, and was barely warm in the middle. Sure, I did order a steak at an Italian restaurant, sure I did order it rare, and sure I could have asked for it to be taken back and re done. However, I didn‚Äôt want to cause a fuss (I take full responsibility for this), and the steak actually tasted really nice! I had the garlic butter with it and the skinny fries were great too.

I will attach a photo of said steak, and perhaps it could be a lesson to future customers not to order a rare steak, and also maybe the chef just to double check the temperature! No hard feelings though, would come back again.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Luigis went downhill badly just after covid but thankfully seems to be getting back to the good aul days slowly but surely, the food was much better than my last visit in May and in general things felt better however the staff still nowhere like the old days. I visited Sunday 18th December, service was sloppy and haphazard and the manager sat over at reception for the night ,then just after 9 the place emptied out fast so ended up around 9.15 with only around 3 tables left . We had had 3 courses and cocktails etc and been here since 7pm.  All of a sudden staff came from everywhere to remove anything left on our table the same Irish gir(who wasnt our waitress BTW) came back 3 times within 10 mins to literally strip the table including taking away even my own kleenex tissues I had on the table so talk about being rushed out. Look I get the guys work long hours etc but we weren't long past 9 pm, it wasn't midnight, so this area definitely needs work. I used to be one of their best customers, now it's a place I'll just frequent the odd time.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: We showed up 20 minutes before close and they didn't rush us our anything ! The garlic knots and homemade pasta is amazing! Definetly a favorite of mine since visiting the area!! Highly recommend.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Visited recently on a Saturday. Very busy. Good food and drink. Service friendly and efficient. Plenty of atmosphere with hen and stag parties so don't expect a quiet meal.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Lovely food, great atmosphere - service was excellent, meal came very quickly despite the restaurant being quite busy. A few dishes are listed as being vegetarian despite containing non-vegetarian ingredients, especially pesto & grana padano - just a little heads-up for fellow vegetarians!

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Got served by a lovely gentleman named Vincent. When I told him it was my birthday meal he got me a cocktail that was not on the menu and got the staff to sing happy birthday when my dessert was being brought out. Not only that the food here is to die for.

Try this place you won‚Äôt be sorry.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Came here last night for a friends birthday. The food wasn‚Äôt bad and I did enjoy myself.

We got the buffalo wings to share which were really delicious. We also got a sharing pint of Strawberry Daiquiri, which was grand too. I got there Chicken BBQ pizza and for dessert I got their cheesecake.

We had to sit outside because some people in our group weren‚Äôt fully vaccinated, but there‚Äôs was almost zero lighting outside. It was pretty dark and we could barely see each other. They have us little table lights but I do think they could try get some better lights.

Apart from that I had a great time and the food wasn‚Äôt too bad.
owner_answer: Hello! Thank you for all the feedback. We will for sure get that sorted. See you soon!

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
I hadn't been in Luigi Malone's in more than ten years.  It's not as good as I remember.
Staff were generally lovely helpful friendly couldn't do enough to help. One gentleman had a problem, understanding us, taking the order.  My partner / boyfriend's main was sent back, as the chicken was dry, and the sauce was claggy, but the wine was lovely.  Cheesecake was lovely.
Could be another while before I go back. Xxx

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
I do recommend this place for TOURISTS .

Really nice restaurant at a good location close to the temple bar area.
The staff was super nice and helpful and we did not needed a reservation.
God the bbq pork ribs .. super good seasoning and not dry. The sauce to sweet for my liking and to store like, but that's personal preference.
That pork lasagna was a hit .. very unique and tasted like pulled pork roast.. super good.
Cocktails were ok, nothing fancy.

Service 5/5
Location 5/5
Food 4/5
Drinks 3/5
Price 4/5
owner_answer: Hi Karen! Thank you for your review! It's a great one! We really appreciate it! See you soon!

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Great food selection from salads to pizza, pasta, burgers , large portions, cocktails were tasty, but staff is very slow and very young standing around with their phones in their hands so that was the only minus. Otherwise definitely visit!
owner_answer: Hello Katka, Thank you for taking the time to review Luigi Malones and for your 4 Star Review, sound one! Delighted to hear you enjoyed your experience with us. I will pass your compliments and your feedback over to our team. Thanks!

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: absolutely amazing staff! So friendly and accommodated a large group of over 20. Good service, amazing food and overall a great night

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Extremely disappointed. As a group of 6, celebrating a birthday, the service we experienced in this restaurant was appalling.
From the time we sat down, it took over 1 to receive our starters, and a second hour after that to receive our mains. At no point within this time frame did anyone come to take a drinks order, meaning we were left waiting on food and drinks for the majority of our time.
After the starters, fresh cutlery was not provided, meaning we had to request fresh cutlery for the mains we assumed would be out within a reasonable timeframe of 25-30 minutes.
This is of no reflection of our lovely server, who clearly looked over worked in an understaffed environment. This is a great reflection on the management as when we complained, he tried to argue that we were ‚Äúonly‚Äù waiting 40 minutes for our mains, when it was in fact an hour at that point. At that, the mains arrived at once and left one person without their main for a further 10 minutes whilst everyone else was eating.
To add to our frustration, the food arrived almost cold, but due to the fact it was now 22:30pm, we ate and decided to leave.
Myself and 5 others would not be returning, especially as a group. As it is clear that this restaurant cannot cater for the capacity that it holds.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
we order a bit of Italian dishes.
and it's good üëç

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Very nice place inside, quite busy but with good atmosphere. Good food menu. Unfortunately I was waiting about 50 minutes (or even more) for main course - chicken fajitas - very good, a bit too spicy but it wasn't a problem, however soup of the day was too spicy. Additionally price for that (24 ‚Ç¨) was a bit too high...

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Carbonara was a glutinous heap. Very fatty "lardons" Grande nachos were ... Meh.
Service, if a little slow, was attentive & charming. Not slow in asking for the table when we'd finished eating however üòè
Very much a young people's "grab n go" type of place

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
The wine was ok, but the food‚Ä¶
Only the pasta was OK, and the salad starter I ordered tasted as tasteless as the Mexican main course...The only good news is that the food isn't expensive, even if it's tasteless‚Ä¶
owner_answer: Hello Ada, sorry to hear this. It's definitely not the experience we are trying to create in Luigi Malones. Can you send a message to hanna@luigimalones.com and give us more details about your order? Thank you!

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Food was fantastic, lovely staff and setting. Also a great location, we went for lunch at half 12 sunday (mothers day) without a booking, they were accommodating.

We had chicken wings and garlic bread for starter. I love chicken wings and these chicken wings were incredible. I could have sat there all day and eating them. Garlic bread was great. Really nice bread and then they give you tonnes of super nice garlic butter to dip into.

We also had a margarita pizza and a pesto pasta and they were both unreal. If I lived in Dublin I would be a regular and if I return to Dublin I will for sure return here.
owner_answer: Hello Rob, Thank you for taking the time to review Luigi Malones and for your 5 Star Review, sound one! Delighted to hear you enjoyed your experience with us. I will pass your compliments over to our team. Thanks!

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
I have been there for a baby shower and the staff told us that was mandatory to consume 25 euros anyway from the set menu, I argue that it was possible to get access to the a l√° carte menu because I really didn‚Äôt like to spend 25 euros in hamb√∫rguer, pizza and the plates presents to the set menu, I could not have access to the full menu and otherwise I must agree to pay 25 euros or I should be invited to get out.

Totally disrespectful police and ilegal once the consumer code says that nobody is obligated to consume certain amount of money in given place.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: We used to go here many years ago and we reckon its been about 6 years since we have been... it is probably fair to say you get what you pay for... its not very expensive and the food is ok for what it is... the buffalo wings for starters were plentiful... the burger was good... frozen chunky chips seem to be the norm now but I would happily pay a few quid more for actual chips... overall ok, venue is nice and central...

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: We went for lunch and it was pretty amazing with the decor and spacious... we went for lunch deals. I had nachos and steak and my friend had soup and pork ribs it was perfect.. also tried the cocktail it was good. Good service and staff. Definitely recommend the place.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Great food, the lunch menu is really good value too. Really enjoyed the wings and the burger. Also the staff are lovely and really attentive/accommodating‚Ä¶ We were there with 2 prams and they couldn‚Äôt have been more helpful! (I did take off a star because they didn‚Äôt have coffees due to frother being broken and they advertise 2 beef patties on the burgers but there‚Äôs only one.)

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: The food was way to tasteless and bland. The fries were the same as if they have been made with an airfrier at home and the Cheeseburger was bland. Also the drink seemed like it has been mixed with water.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
A very limited menu means that they have to make sure the food is of a very high standard.
As another reviewer mentioned it's for the tourists, and I think I would agree.
You have the classic 4 options.
Pizza
Pasta
Burgers
Chef special

The pizza was really good, needed a little more seasoning in the tomato base.
Stone fired which is the ONLY way. I didn't try a menu item, I customised my pizza. Crunch thim base pizza. Yummy.
The lasagna was also pretty good, the portions are a tad smaller than you would expect, so try a starter. The buffalo wings are a good bet, but a little pricey for 16 small winglets.
Atmosphere reminds me of a Madrid restaurant style. Lots of folks enjoying meals with us, so it's a popular venue. We were able to get a table in arrival.
I think the best tables are in the lower section which is cosy and more loungy in atmosphere. Service was ok. Would have been nice to have a special of the day, if there was the server didn't call it out to us.

They cater to vegan palettes.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
The Merlot wine is gorgeous!!! Ordered the steak Medium......
. Was perfect!!!!!! The double espresso was as good as I have ever had!!! My only critique would be the chips but that's not an issue really!!! Thoroughly enjoyed the meal thank you!!! I will be back!!!!! ü§óü§ó

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Disappointed since the begging when I was told that the kitchen had closed already. The person who talked to us at the entrance said I should know that the restaurant closes at 10pm, I told him that there was a table available for 10pm in their website ‚Äúwhich shouldn‚Äôt be there if their kitchen closes at 10pm, right?‚Äù. Anyway, overall they treated me and my family as if we were doing a favor to them, plus: the bill was dropped at our table before we had finished eating. I would never recommend this place for someone else. Thanks anyway for seating us and offering a bit of your precious time.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Staff were friendly and helpful. Atmosphere nice although very busy. There seemed to be too few staff given the amount of customers. We had a starter (Nachos Grande), main and dessert (Chocolate Brownie) here as well as a few cocktails. Starter and dessert were very tasty, and the highlights of our experience. Our mains (lasagne & burrata pasta) were a bit disappointing unfortunately, missing flavour. The burrata pasta had only a tiny piece of burrata on top, & the lasagne had only one sheet of pasta instead of pasta layers. We would consider going back, but probably just for starters/desserts.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: The worst and only bad meal/experience we had in Ireland. Was nearly 45 minutes from the time we sat down that anyone even came to take drink orders. There was a set menu and all of our pasta dishes took two hours from the time we ordered to come out. The food was cold and incredibly bland. The staff were nice but incompetent, drinks and food orders were forgotten, and we had to physically get up to track someone down to pay and finally leave. All in about 3 hours of time wasted on terrible service and food, would highly recommend looking elsewhere.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Tables packed together a little tight. Staff and service were good , my wife got pesto chicken and the pasta was under cooked.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text:
Amazing food. We've been here at lunch time and got a proper, filling 2 course menu + drinks for 10‚Ç¨. You can choose between Pasta, Salad, Pizza, Burgers & more. All of the food is proper size and  you struggle to finish it. The service is quick - we got seated and immediately free water. Also the food arrived really quickly and was absolutely delicious.
The waiters are great and make sure everyone is happy. They also refilled the water immediate after it was empty.

Even though there aren't a lot of gluten free options (I am gluten intolerant) the food was delicious and filling. I got the chicken wings and the chicken.

In conclusion - absolutely amazing, can highly recommend this restaurant.

Thank you to all the amazing waiters and waitresses as well.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Great cost x benefit. Affordable price and a reasonable portion of food. Good variety of pasta flavors and types of meal.
