Staff seems very prepared to serve the clients functioning fast and politly. The restaurant offers different promotions depending on the week day. Roomy and cozy place, great for events.

name: Luigi Malones Dublin
review_text: Good food reasonably priced. The cheaper red , a Spanish, ain‚Äôt great so don‚Äôt go for that. Try to get seated on the entrance floor- the basement doesn‚Äôt look great.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Over rated and overpriced.
Food is average and edible. The chicken boxty was decent and the lamb stew was average. The baileys cheesecake was very sour and was not flavourful.
Service is poor -
On observation, except for the senior servers, the rest are just plain ignorant and some extremely rude.
Snatching away drinks at the exit when one of your servers said its okay to do so, is NOT OKAY. Not to mention, I asked for a to-go cup and I was told you guys don't have one. It could have been said in a polite way as we had just paid for the dinner. Instead of saying ' thank you for visiting us', that's how they treat their customers once they have gotten their money. Not a homely feeling at all! The senior servers are actually making an effort but unfortunately the overall experience for me and my mother was not a good one.

Verdict - I would recommend to have your Irish meal, with a pint or two, somewhere else!
owner_answer: Hi Naiyna - not sure what happened with the service you received but we would agree it fell short of the necessary politeness. Very sorry this was your experience of the boxty house.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Very tasty food. The prices are not small, they are quite big, just because is Temple Bar and it's an area mainly for tourists. You will find the same price ranges everywhere in that area.

The lamb that I've ordered was very well done üëç although, the beef we order to be very well done, but it tasted like burn, like smoke. I thing it was someho6over done.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Great food in the centre of Temple Bar - very high prices. All dishes very good, waiters pleasant, location perfect. We had issue with beers on tasting, all were too bitter - seemed like production mistake to us since smooth ale, pale ale and lager had the stout bitternes. I would avoid it.
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for your review. About the beers, we're always checking if there's something wrong with the production, but usually, craft beers can be bitter. Anyway, we're glad that even though, you had a good experience. Hope to see you again soon! :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
During the COVID pandemic years, my husband and I watched Somebody Feed Phil on Netflix to fulfill our desire to travel all over the world.

One of the episodes was in Dublin, and I didn't think I would ever make it to Ireland. So when the opportunity came up, we prioritized going to this restaurant highly recommended by Phil Rosenthal.

My father-in-law, husband, and I made dinner reservations at 9:30 pm after their round of golf at Portmarnock. The food was delicious, as advertised.

What we ate:

‚úÖ Boxty Sharing Platter

‚úÖ Gallagher‚Äôs Lamb Stew

‚úÖ Beef & Stout Stew

‚úÖ Traditional Irish Corned Beef

‚úÖ Sticky Toffee Pudding

I highly recommend coming here with an empty stomach because the portions are big!
owner_answer: Hello, Michelle! Thank you so much for this fantastic review. We're happy to know that you had enjoyed the food and had a good experience with us. Hope to see you again! :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Definitely love the chicken wings, the fries and the staff!!! The staff were super friendly and really patient with kids as well, the lamb stew was awesome, not as heavy as other restaurant that I tried. Kids loved the soup of the day which was the veggie soup, the boxty chips IS A MUST!
owner_answer: Hello, Angela! Thank you so much for this amazing review! Looking forward to see you again in the restaurant!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Very busy place. Glad we made reservations on OpenTable. Place is smaller than I thought and quite tight to move around. Very loud also so had to repeat our order several times to the server.
Had the beer sampler, chowder and chicken boxty which were delicious. Son had fish n chips, and hubby had a beef boxty.
Overall glad we came and do recommend eating here.
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this review, it is really important for us. Hope to see you again soon! :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Great night in the Temple Bar district.  Amazing Boxty originating from Leitrim available with delicious toppings.  Friendly wait staff and efficient service - even have their unique beer!  No wonder Phil from Somebody feed Phil came here.  And gluten-free friendly!
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this lovely review. We're really happy to know that you had enjoyed your experience. Hope to see you again soon :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: The staff at Boxty, especially Mike, were extremely friendly!! I had such a lovely time and was a great first food stop in my first ever trip to Dublin. The blood pudding was extremely delicious and the chicken boxty was incredible!! Highly likely I will be back on my next trip :)
owner_answer: Hello! Thank you so much for this awesome review! We're happy to know that you had enjoyed your experience in the restaurant. Hope to see you again soon! :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
I‚Äôve had dinner there for my entire stay in Ireland (4days) I tried other places for breakfast and lunch but to be honest this one was the best and I enjoyed the fact they have traditional Irish dishes it was a great experience. I recommend the dishes I had they were all delicious, had  soda bread, Boxty fries, Colcannon, Champ potato and vegetarian chili Boxty. As for the dessert I had bread and butter pudding, and Boxty bread ice cream. For the drinks I only had the non alcoholic drinks the blueberry mojito, homemade sweet lemonade and homemade ice tea they were nice but my favorite was virgin sour!
I had virgin marry but I don‚Äôt recommend it because it tasted like tomato soup with ice, but I like to try new things it‚Äôs fun, so if you are brave to try new things then go ahead and try it.
Service was great and the staff was very friendly and super sweet!
Thank you for having me and for being part of my journey while exploring Ireland üáÆüá™ ü§çüçÄ
owner_answer: Hi Toosha, thanks for visiting us so much and for trying so many things. We will work on improving the Virgin Mary for your next time over.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Had a lovely early dinner here tonight with the family.  I've been meaning to come here for 20 years and finally got to it! Food is delicious and the staff is friendly and gracious....it's kind of like stopping at your aunt and uncle's place  for a fun evening.
owner_answer: Hey, thank you so much for this lovely review, we're really glad to know that you had a good experience! Hope to see you again soon.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
We couldn't secure a table before 9 pm, so the 2 dishes we wanted to order weren't available anymore - a good sign, that everything is freshly prepaired!
Absolutly friendly and professionally acting staff - asked, if all were ok, I mentioned that 2 dishes were a little be cold, they immediately brought 2 fresh hot ones.
To be honest, Irish Boxtys and stews are not my favorites, I loved the Irish fillet beef, the bread varieties and the excellent, fluffy and light mashed potatoes

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Amazing place for our first night in Dublin. Food was great, service quick and very kind (thanks Mike), and cosy/musically ambient place ! A must go if you're downtown.
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this lovely review! Looking forward to see you again at the restaurant! :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Stopped by at boxty because it was chosen as one of the best in Dublin on TripAdvisor and their menu looks great with a great selection. Unfortunately, the service was bad and the food was not up to snuff. The fish and chips were good but a small portion. The Irish breakfast platter looked good but most of its components were overcooked. The food was pretty pricey and the service was slow. Our server did not come back to the table after we ordered except to bring the check. Overall, a good restaurant, but not one of the best in Dublin.
owner_answer:
Hi Umpy

Thank you for visitng us and for taking the time to write your review. I was very sorry to read about the problems with your meal. We will address the issues and work hard to impress if you come by to visit us again.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Simple place with excellent food. The staff is friendly and care about your experience. Fair prices considering is near temple bar. I tried the boxty, which  I didn't knew and loved It.
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this amazing review! We're happy to know that you had a good experience. Hope to see you again soon!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: We stopped here because Phil Rosenthal ate here for his show ‚ÄúSomebody Feed Phil‚Äù and my mom and I absolutely adore him. And THANK GOD we did! This place is amazing. The food was top tier - we got the boxty platter and the beef stew. Both were very delicious, and if I lived anywhere near Dublin this would be my go-to place. The stew came with homemade bread and even that was to die for. We also got the bread pudding and WOW ü§©. Bread pudding is one of my favorite deserts, and this is probably my favorite one now. Our server was also great! I don‚Äôt remember what his name was, but he was very warm and welcoming. Personable and always cracking jokes.
owner_answer: Hi Allyson, the amount of people who come to the Boxty House because of Phil continues to amaze us. Glad you enjoyed both his show and your meal here.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Phenomenal food with superb service. Angela was incredibly friendly and helpful with our questions about the food. She and the quality of the food made our experience 10/10. We initially stopped here because we learned about the restaurant through a Netflix show and we were blown away. Long live Ireland üáÆüá™
owner_answer: Hey, Bryan! Thank you so much for this amazing review.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
author_title: JustNatural Holistic Spa & Institute Inc. Timmins
review_text: We loved the food! We tried a few dishes and everyone was happy. Great staff, and so nice
owner_answer: Hello! What an amazing review, thank you so much for that. Hope to see you again soon! :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: I definitely fell in love with that place !!! Amazing food, great service and topical Irish atmosphere ( as much as I know what the Irish atmosphere is :) ). The kitchen was so tasty and delicious! Me and my family have a great time in Boxty and we would love to come back for another lunch on our next visit to Dublin! So if you are thinking of visiting this place- just go!
owner_answer: Hi Ivaylo, thanks for coming, and for the lovely review.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
We were located in the basement, in a very warm room. I am still wondering why they did not switch on the air conditioning.

Food wise, I didn't choose well, don't go for the chowder or the fish and chips. Chowder is tasteless and for the first time in my life I had to add salt to it. I have no idea how you can find seafood as bad, but somehow they managed to do so. Fish and chips are not good, with a super tick bread on the fish, and way too oily. The salmon looks good, so go for it if you have the chance.

Desserts were the best, and still I wouldn't go for them.

Service was nice but slow and overwhelmed. With the money they charge for the food, I was expecting way better and faster service. We had to request several times for water, and napkins. Not great, but still their effort is appreciated because it's not their fault.

The bathrooms... Well, judge for yourself, but basically I had to go to another place because they are basically dirty.

In short, a place a won't visit again; overpriced to the extreme and with lack of staff.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: We had a good time at Boxty. Food was delicious, the portions were reasonable for the price. The restaurant is really cozy.
owner_answer: Hello! Thank you so much for this amazing review! Hope to see you again soon.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Offensively expensive place. I mean... The food is really good, I had a lamb boxty, typical from this place and it was delicious. But in my opinion the price made this experience no worthy. It was the most expensive dinner I had in Dublin by far
owner_answer: Hello, thank you for your feedback. We're glad to know that you liked the food.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Boxties are a traditional Irish pancake made with potatoes originating from Leitrim in the west. This Dublin restaurant in the Temple bar district serves amazing Boxties, and you should definitely give it a try as it is something you can‚Äôt eat outside of Ireland.
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this amazing review! We're happy to know that you had a good experience at the restaurant. Hope to see you again soon!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Cozy pub. Awesome service. Gaelic Boxty was a hit.
Story is they used to have a Michelin star but the chef turned it down because he didn‚Äôt want to scare off the ‚Äúnormal‚Äù customers.
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this lovely review. Hope to see you again!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Went to eat lunch here after the St. Patrick's Day Dublin parade! The location is in the heart of the city and had a cozy/warm atmosphere inside. I got the Gaelic boxty with the Stonewell cider. It was a bit pricey and a smaller portion than I'd like, but it tasted great and was a treat to have
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for the 5 stars review! Hope to see you again at the restaurant soon

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Quality food and service. The fish and chips were the highlight but the vegetarian chili boxty and the corned beef and dumplings were also very good. Prices are reasonable and the restaurant was available early for brunch on a Thursday.
owner_answer: Hi Mitch, thanks for the 5 star review

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Unfortunately not the experience we were expecting. Food quality was acceptable, but nothing exceptional. You eat on top of each other, like in a canteen. We book well in advance and we got seated in a cramp corner in the basement. Toilets were very dirty. Service was very pushy, the faster you eat and get out the best. In the end just another tourist trap in Temple Bar
owner_answer: Hi, sorry to see we did not match your expectations. We would love to hear how we could improve so feel free to contact us at info@boxtyhouse.ie

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Enjoyed brunch at this restaurant today. Had a flight of beers which was pretty good, but a bit pricey (‚Ç¨12 for 4 glasses, 1/3 pint each). Got the fries which were REALLY good (kind of had a similar flavor to carnival food, in a good way). Got the lamb stew which was pretty good and my wife got the vegetarian Boxty potatoe pancake, sort of burrito style with beans and such inside. I tried it and didn't like it, but she enjoyed it. Overall a pretty nice brunch.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Little but cute place. The traditional lamb stew was good, even if too much strong in taste in my opinion. Prices are aligned with the other places like this into the center of Dublin.
owner_answer: Hi Serena, thanks for reviewing us and we appreicate the comments (the good and the not-so-good)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: A must visit, the food is unmatched in taste and the tasty beers are all their own brew! I had the corned beef boxty and it was out of this world delicious!
owner_answer: Hey, thank you so much! Hope to see you again soon.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Bringing aspects of the traditional Irish food with a fresh twist. My chicken boxty had flavor with a nice cream sauce.

Can‚Äôt forgot how Amazing the dessert was and our waiter Mike made the experience enjoyable!
owner_answer: Hey, Anthony. Thank you for the 4 stars review, hope to see you again at the restaurant soon.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: I tried the fish and chips and unfortunately it was flavorless, the wings were tasty but the blue cheese sauce could use more blue cheese and the wings can be bigger in size in my opinion
owner_answer: Hi Ramzi, thanks for visitng and for taking the time to post your review. We will look into the points you raised and hope to see you again

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Conveniently located and very hearty food. Our server was so friendly and helpful, which already put us in a great mood. He did a great job pushing the Boxty fries--which, I have to be honest, I was skeptical about at first, but wow am I glad we followed his advice. The stews and the steak were great but the fries are what I would definitely go back for! Also, if you are a beer-lover, get their house lager (Jack Smyth).
owner_answer: Hey Val, thanks for such a wonderful review.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Fantastic fare & even better service! We were blown away with the whole affair! Mike took such great care of us, he really made our last night in Ireland something special! And the food was absolutely divine!
owner_answer: Hey, Colleen! Thank you so much for this amazing review!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: I loveee everything about it, the food is just so yummy, please order the gaelic boxty, so so good and for dessert you have to try the sticky toffee it blew my mind ü§Ø
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this lovely review! We're happy to know that you had enjoyed our gaelic and the sticky toffee (it smells so nice, doesn't it?)  Looking forward to see you again at the restaurant!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Being promising a visit here every time we came to Dublin. Booked a week before arriving and took the family. Thought it was a little pricey but the quality and standard and service was worth every Euro.
owner_answer: Hey, Chris! Thank you so much for this lovely feedback. It's really good to know that you had enjoyed our food and service. Hope to see you again at the restaurant soon! :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Had a lovely dinner at Boxty House and food was great. Nice portions and lovely presentation. The cheesecake was a tiny bit disappointing because we could not taste Baileys at all and chocolate sauce tasted a bit like cocoa powder. Cocktails were very tasty but I think a bit overpriced. I suppose the whole place is priced according to location (Temple Bar) All in all it was a nice experience. Staff is very friendly, that's a bonus.
owner_answer: Hi Alexandra, thanks for the review and the comments. We have raised the issue on the Baileys Cheesecake with the Kitchen Team and hopefully next time you visit, you will taste the difference.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Such great food! I was fortunate to try multiple new foods. It is family owned and well loved. The brew was tasty too. Check it out. Expect crowds on the weekend.
owner_answer: Hi Karen, thanks for coming in and for the lovely photos. Glad you enjoyed everything.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Amazed by the taste of the 3 dumplings platter: Lamb Stew, Braised Beef and Stout, and Dublin Coddle. Really suggested. The 3 kinds of breads they comes with were incredibly tasty and good too. Also, being not a sweet tooth person I got pretty impressed by the taste of the bread and butter pudding. Light, good, and well balanced in taste. Turkey was good too. The waiter we had was very friendly and available with us!
owner_answer: Hi Stefano, delighted to read your review. Thanks for visiting and for the recommendation.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Really good brunch spot
Good food and good service.
Vegetarian options available; though I wish they were a bit heartier. The meat dishes always have so much food on them whilst the veggie dishes surely don't have the same caloric value.
owner_answer: Hi Jordan, thanks for visiting and for the review. Interesting point about our vegetarian options and one we will look into.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Delicious! Highly recommend the sharing stew platter with three options and boxty "fries". Once you're done with bangers and mash, Irish stew, and fish and chips, this is something different, local, and delicious.

Note: the appetizer plate looks sparse because we ate a bunch before we remembered to photograph it!!!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Great atmosphere, friendly staff available to assist and some traditional options available to try.

Had the main and salad deal with the Irish lamb stew. The Boxty Fish & Chips was very good as well.

The Jack Smyth stout and red ale were delicious as well. Irish coffee to finish off, which was lovely.

Give it a try!
owner_answer: Hi Ryan, thanks for the lovely review and recommendations.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Very cozy restaurant and amazing food. Recommend it.
Their Irish coffee is very good.
owner_answer: Hey, thank you so much for this amazing review, hope to see you again :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
A great place to have lunch at, really tasty food, reasonable pricing, quick service and friendly staff. The menu is one of the best I've seen, there are not too many dishes, but there's something for everyone.
It was a bit crowded when we visited, and there were no tables available, but it certainly was worth the wait.
owner_answer: Hi Roman, thanks for visiting and for waiting to get that table. We are quite busy for the summer but we always try and make room for guests.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Best Burger üçî ever!!! My husband was delighted with their burger and kept saying this was the best. The flavors were rich and complimented each other amazingly. I am intolerant to gluten, so I couldn‚Äôt have it. But I am so thankful to their awesome staff and menu for helping me find the best gluten-free friendly foods. The boxtys are amazing!
And I always love a good gluten-free desert, this place did it!
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for this lovely review. We're really happy to know that you had enjoyed your experience. Hope to see you again soon :)

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Been a long while since we've been here but the food was every bit as awesome as we remembered! Will most certainly be back.
owner_answer: Hey, David! We're glad to know that you had a good experience again at the restaurant. Thank you so much for your review and hope to see you again soon.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: Food was tasty, shared the blood sausage starter and stew platter. While the presentation of the stew in 3 mugs was visually appealing, some side plates or extra crocks would have been nice to better organize the "sharing". Overall great food with so-so service.
owner_answer: Hi Danielle - thanks for visitng and for the comments. Great point about the sharing plates and this is something we will take on board.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: The spicy carrots, which are listed as a side dish make for an excellent starter, and are truly delicious. The Beef & Stout was lovely, and came with mashed potato and 3 different types of bread. Unfortunately, no-one told me what kinds of bread they were, and I didn't have the heart to ask the staff who were being kept very busy, as every table was full. I've had better bread, but the rest of the main dish was great. Worth going just for the carrots.
owner_answer: Hey Robin, thanks for the review and the helpful comments - we will work on the bread!

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Pros:
A cozy place

Cons:
The cheesecake wasn't taste like a real cheesecake + Corned Beef Dumplings was lower than okay and cause the meat was salty, it was easy to eat
owner_answer:
Hi Hossein

Thanks for coming in. Sorry to read you did not enjoy your meal with us. Our Cheesecake is very popular but is a bit different to the more typical baked cheesecake.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text:
Lovely atmosphere, unique dishes and good choice of gluten free options. Wait staff were very charming and hospitable. Large windows to the street so good if you like people watching, but not great for shy diners!

Especially recommend the boxty bread ice cream, it was delicious
owner_answer: Hi Ru, thanks for the excellent review, so glad to have had you visit.

name: Gallaghers Boxty House
review_text: The food here was delicious! We ended up going back to back nights and loved the chicken boxty and the Gaelic boxty, as well as the boxty fries. Only thing I‚Äôd say is it‚Äôs pretty small so feels a bit like you‚Äôre crammed in, but it was worth it for the yummy food! Very friendly wait staff as well

name: Mr Fox
review_text: I came here for my friend's birthday.  This is a great spot for fine dining and tasting a little bit of a lot. The chicken was my favourite dish here as it was so juicy. One of the desserts was very interesting, reminds me of the Mikado biscuits we had as kids. Nice atmosphere here and quite chilled out. Staff were very nice and attentive.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Overall, the food was good (I probably enjoyed the desserts the most) and I think the price is reasonable compared to the cost of many other "upscale" dining experiences. That said, nothing was super "memorable" and we regularly forgot about this place when telling people about our best dining experiences. The tasting menu, while made up of tasty dishes, wasn't extremely cohesive and maybe lacked a fun/interesting quality that would have made the experience more memorable. The service was good but the overall energy was strange and confusing (it seems like they want to be a "fun" place based on some of the wall decoration, the name/logo, etc... but the music and energy felt designed for an older crowd that wanted a more traditional fine dining experience).

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
This hidden gem in Dublin 1 takes you on a tasty excursion mixing regional treats with a touch of french and asian standards. There is one extensive tasting menu which can be adjusted as per dietary requirements. All the dishes were beautifully presented and had fine textures + well balanced taste notes. Highlights were the tuna starter and the bits served as appetizers (skewers, fish tartelettes). Desserts also had great taste all in all
were a bit too much (5 desserts - wow). Wine list is small but has some really beautiful options - check out the 1er cru White burgundy. One big minus of this restaurant is the fact that the atmosphere is stressy. Ultra noisy and bad lights atmosphere - tip: invest in some more fabrics to have better acoustics - insulation really is on the negative and ensure the lights are more dim. Very friendly staff that looks after you.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Despite the green curry being too spicy for a tasting menu, the food was amazing. Different textures, flavors, and colors. The three-hour dinner was a bit lengthy but we thoroughly enjoyed each and every course. I I highly recommend this place.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Found this unique gem from a google search. Tasting menu was exceptional.  Intimate atmosphere and knowledgeable wait staff. A fixed price menu, but lots of courses equals plenty of food.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: I think I will talk about my experience at Mr. Fox for a very long time. It was simply stunning. The food was literally Michelin. If I were the food critic that night, they would have gotten a ‚≠ê.. such lovely people. I would tell everyone about this place. It was worth every penny spent.

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Background
A Michelin guide restaurant in town that was highly recommended. It is a fusion of Irish and French cuisine.

Ambience
Located at the basement of a red-brick terrace house. There were 2 doors, one for entry and the other for exit, which I obviously do not follow. The interior was charming.

Service
The host was nice and friendly. We were explained the menu and was attended attentively.

Food
The food was superb. I enjoyed the bread and entree to the dessert.

Overall
A must visit if you are in town.

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Visited for my husband's birthday this year and had a fantastic experience!

The restaurant does a tasting menu and also offers a wine paring which we decided to do this time.

Honestly everything was fantastic. The food was delicious, the wine pairings were wonderful and well thought through and the staff were amazing!

We had a wonderful experience.

The menu changes regularly so if you want to revisit you will have a slightly different but still brilliant experience!

I recommend booking in advance as the restaurant is not walk in style.
The restaurant is perfect for a special occasion, to treat yourself or as an excuse to get a bit dressed up with some friends!

Highly recommend!

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
If you are into tasting menus this is a must-try when in Dublin, food and staff were great plus a good selection of wines.

They were also very good at adjusting the menu to accommodate food allergies and preferences.

The only thing missing is a pairing option and you will get the full michellin experience.

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Had dinner here on my first night in Dublin. I got the premium wine pairing with my meal. Here are some notable and memorable highlights from my experience. To be noted- Their menu has since changed.

Ham hock - the perfect bite. Texture varied in every layer. Savory and creamy and smokey and salty and slightly sweet. Most delicious bite I've ever had.

Tuna tartare with chipotle tartlet- amazing fish quality. Never had tuna that tasted that fresh. Well seasoned. Perfectly spicy chipotle cream. Textures also on point with the thin crispy tartlet shell.

Scallops "Waldorf"
Amazing tender scallops. Not fishy at all. The apple and cabbage and yellow (can't remember what it was) mousse were amazing. The walnuts were a perfect nutty addition that added a bit of sweetness and crunch that the dish truly benefited from.
Stunning presentation.

Cod and mussel- amazingly tender. Melt in your mouth. Most buttery tender mussels and cod literally melts when you chew. So good. The green curry sauce was a tad overpowering for the delicacy of the fish, but was still good flavor. Just left my mouth tingly and unable to really taste the fish. The squash with crispy seeds was a good addition. I always enjoy crispy grains and seeds on a plate with soft textures.

Duck and blackberry with cevennes(caramelized onion) and salsify-
Duck wasn't as tender as I expected. A tiny bit on the chewy side. The salsify- never had it before but absolutely loved it. Large portion for a main in a tasting menu. I was getting too full to finish because I wanted room for dessert so they gladly gave me a take away box to finish it later.
The blackberry and onion accompaniments were delightful and cut through the richness of the duck perfectly. Still wish the duck wasn't so chewy and hard to cut through but the flavor was delightful.

Lemon and rhubarb dessert was phenomenal and perfectly tart. The dessert wine pairing went perfectly with the flavor. Was a perfect intro to their sweet offerings.
The coconut and chocolate desserts weren't my jam but I'm not a huge fan of either flavor. However the coconut ice cream between dehydrated chocolate mousse wafers was great and I'd definitely eat that again.

The passion fruit jelly with passion mousse was delightful. Perfect ending bite.

Ambiance was noisy. Conversations at every table were very overpowering. Definitely feels very casual vibe despite the menu and drinks.
Decor was minimal in a good way, a tad rustic and homey. Staff were very friendly and helpful but were less attentive than expected. Dirty plates/glasses sat on the table until right before the next course was served.

Overall delicious and good experience.
Food: 4/5
Ambiance: 3/5
Service: 4/5
Drink pairings: 4/5
Creativity: 5/5

name: Mr Fox
review_text: The food the amazing. The snacks are out of this world. The duck main was one of the best I have ever had. Wine recommendations superb. Loved the red.

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Very cosy atmosphere,
The service was very friendly and good,
Food absolutely delicious.
The vegetarian menue could be improved: instead of the massive steak, two/three small oyster mushrooms were served as 'main dish', which was quantity-wise and i assume also cost-wise quite disproportional and left our vegetarians disappointed.

Overall very great experience & food

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Food was very ordinary. Nothing creative or special compared to other Michelin-recommended places in Europe. Some flavors not balanced enough, duck quite chewy, desert very sweet.
Service friendly but not good. Food started coming before we even had a chance to order wine. We always had to ask proactively for water, more wine etc.
All in all, a little overpriced for an okayish dinner.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Great food. Great experience. The staff made it even better. Special thanks to Nat√°lia who took care of us. Warm welcome and excellent customer service. See you next time!

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Firstly, can I say that I really regret giving five stars in previous reviews as nothing I've ever eaten has compared to the food in Mr Fox. In fact, maybe Google might unlock a 6 star review option for special places. Mr Fox is certainly worthy of it.

So to start, can I say that I hate fish. I've never liked it. Or so I thought. I had 3 courses of fish. It wasn't forced but I really wanted to broaden my mind and really enjoy the Mr Fox experience. Suffice to say that I can see fish dishes being a feature of future posts and reviews.

From the moment we crossed the door until we climbed the stairs back up onto Parnell Square after our meal, the service was incredible. Not pushy or pretentious, just warm, friendly and attentive. The server spent plenty of time explaining the dishes that were coming.

I honestly couldn't fault anything. I've never been to a Michelin Star restaurant but can see Mr Fox featuring in the very near future. Our visit was a very special occasion and Mr Fox made it all the more special. It'll take me a long time to forget that food!!

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
I love the chicken wing and soup there.
ü§£ All the courses r amazing, but i had a very strong impression with the small/tiny chicken wing. Eat a lot of sourdough with the sauce.
it is such a good value. only ‚Ç¨70, but with such a good taste and service.
The decoration is quite interesting, a lot of fox paintings inside.
Hope they can change menu, wanna try it again.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Always amazing. The staff are fabulous and friendly. Place has lovely decor and nice use of the space. The little bar when you arrive is nice, to relax you into your meal. Food is Michelin standard, I'd say they are very close to a star. Love the mix of their classics along with new changing menu items.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: A group of us went here to celebrate my brother's belated 40th at the weekend. It was absolutely faultless, the food was sublime and the wine pairings complimented each dish spectacularly. The staff were brilliant, and clearly explained each dish and the wine pairings. We had a fabulous evening and would highly recommend for a special occasion (or any occasion really!). Will definitely be back!

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Simply outstanding! Every bite was excellent from fresh vegetables, delicious fish & spectacular dessert. The service was on point. Opt for the premium wine pairing-it‚Äôs worth it.
Enjoyed the food, service & atmosphere too much to take pictures. See you on our next trip to Ireland

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Hands down our most delicious meal in Dublin! Very cute little place. The staff is all quite friendly and helpful. A big thank you to letting me sub chicken for the venison. The sommelier was great at describing the wines and how they would pair with each dish.

On to the food. I am not a fish eater, but the fish courses/dishes were so good I really enjoyed them. The deboned panko crusted chicken wings were so good. So much flavor and crunch in a little package. I really enjoyed all the interesting flavors and little accents included in the dishes. They really elevated the meal.
I was delighted that we each got each of the three desserts. I loved the coconut flavor and the passion fruit gelee.
I would recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a fantastic (Mr Fox) meal! ü¶ä

name: Mr Fox
review_text: So far my favorite dining experience in Dublin! Everything is 10/10 from the service, setting, food taste of course, and value. Actually value is like 12/10 we couldnt believe the price at the end - feels like getting a way fancier experience than we paid for (shh don't let them know!).

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Amazing place in the Dublin city center, having already the fork and the plate, but it deserves the Michelin star. The prestaurant is starting with professional and friendly staff, always ready to help - ending with exquisite food. üëå We had the course meal of the evening, each dish was amazing, the taste can't be described in words, you must try it. Don't miss the opportunity to visit this restaurant, the experience will be remembered for a long time.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: I absolutely loved our dinning experience. The food was exquisite and well presented, the staff is very attentive and the atmosphere is delightful. I really appreciated the variety of the menu. It was my husband's birthday and I loved their attention to the occasion. I highly recommend Mr Fox ü¶ä

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Loved our experience!!  Adorable almost speakeasy setting.  Professional but welcoming and warm servers.  Attractive and clean. Dining an elegant flow of excellently prepared delectable bites.  Wine pairing perfect.  Price extraordinarily reasonable.  Didn't know we'd have prix fixe dinner coming in but Loved it!!!  Allow 2 1/2 hours. Bring on the ü§© stars

name: Mr Fox
review_text: The food was excellent and had unique flavors. Service/hygiene standard has room for improvement - the waitress was a bit precarious when placing down a new plate and touched our cutlery with her hand.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Another fabulous experience in Mr Fox. The staff are fabulous and accommodating from the moment you walk in the door. Myself and four of my friends went and were looked after so well! The May menu was my favourite one so far. My highlights were short rib with the little potatoes was divine and all starters. The sourdough with the cep butter the essential constant! Can‚Äôt wait for my next visit!

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Set menu with a few small bite size dishes to start with, the tomato consomme with sliced of strawberries is a highlight along with crab, fried chicken; followed up burrata cheese with sliced peach and chilly sauce is so delicious, the flavor combo is so unique! Absolutely loved it!

One main dish dish Halibut, and finished with duck which was so well cooked with perfect pink.

A few desserts followed by but some of them were way too heavy to finish off the meal. Would rather prefer something much less dairy based, and more a palate cleanser with citrus flavours etc.

Overall it's an excellent place to enjoy a nice meal! Good selection of champagne and wines by the glass, ‚Ç¨65pp for food is a bargain in my opinion. We spent ‚Ç¨230 in total and the service charge is not applied by the restaurant so we tipped in cash as a gesture of appreciations! Very friendly staffs!

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Absolutely incredible food and service. They have a wonderful back garden area with fantastic seating which is primarily covered from the rain. Everyone from the front of house staff to the management made the experience excellent. As for the back of house - the food was exceptional, as the pictures will surely attest. Solid aperitif list, solid sweet wines and sherries list - missing a PX which I think would have made for an excellent last sip to end the night, a menial recommendation for the menu - because everything was perfect.

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Lovely resstaurant with an amazing top class friendly and professional service!

The staff would explain each dish as they serve us the food. The time they deliver each course to our table was quick!

You can really taste the freshness of their seafood.

Exceptionally good deal and price for a tasting menu. I would highly recommend this restaurant.

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
We came to Dublin for a weekend away and this was the biggest highlight of our time there. Everything was cooked to perfection and we came out feeling very satisfied after the 6 course tasting experience.
Everything was presented so beautifully and the flavours were out of this world.
I like how adventurous the menu was, from Eele to Guinea Hen and Carpaccio. The cocktails were very tasty (although I wish they were bigger!).the service was friendly and I could tell they were all working hard to excel the superb food and dining ambience.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Such a good moment. Large cosy place, very good services. The unique menu changes every month, and for 65‚Ç¨ you have a wonderful 6 services menu. Appetizers, fish, meat and desserts. That s really fresh generous and well cooked. Perfect

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Loved everything about this place! The food was amazing and the wine pairings were perfectly matched. I was particularly impressed by the friendly service and the customisation of the menu in occasion of my birthday. I would definitely go back!

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Super good food and service. The price is normal for the quality offered. The only thing I wasn't happy about is that there was a service charge of a 12% at the bill with a table of 4 persons ,with an invoice of around 500 EUR it was a tip of around 50 EUR. I'm happy to give tip, but I want to decide myself how much I want to give, and not to be forced , as we are in Dublin and not the US. Will be back for sure as it's a great place, and recommend it to anyone who loves good food and trying new things. Thanks!!!

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Adorable, delicious and extremely unpretentious fine dining. It was playful and fun to eat. Nicely curated selection of wines.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: We took the 5 course menu with red wine and sparkling wine both recommended by Boris the sommelier. Great choices with great price. Service was fenomenal and the food exceptional. A must do in Dublin if you are a foodie.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Fantastic experience. Food, wine, and service all exceptional. Thoroughly deserving of a Michelin star, can‚Äôt believe it hasn‚Äôt got one already.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Absolutely amazing experience tonight at Mr Fox. We didn‚Äôt know what to expect and it‚Äôs safe to say that we were blown away by the excellent quality of the food and the friendly staff. Each dish was a roll coaster of different flavours and textures, each one better than the last. Can‚Äôt wait to go back next month when the new menu comes out. Highly recommended. It‚Äôs very good value for money.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Very good quality for the price tag - same concept of Bastible or Variety Jones.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Stunning food and service is excellent. The set menu is reasonably priced and i recommend the wine pairings because they're very good.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: It is a very nice place to go for a birthday dinner. We recommend the Premium Wine pairing. It goes perfectly with the great and tasty food served. We loved it! Thank you.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Stellar experience! As a chef it is always a great pleasure to find a spot like this. Not many people can pull off a cohesive coursed menu. Mr. Fox delivered spectacularly. The pairings were spot on and the food was absolutely delicious!

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
It was a fantastic evening, and I obviously loved the food very much. Particularly the quail egg, and the smoked eel ham hock. The lemon dessert was also amazing! Comfortable atmosphere, much more casual and affordable than most Michelin star restaurants, at 75 euro pp for the full set menu for dinner.

The modern art decor was interesting, though I think it was maybe underutilized in the space available and was overwhelmed a bit by the patterns on the floor and walls, but I really liked the overall vibe. Overall excellent!

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
It's the 3rd or 4th time I'm here and I can say I'm never disappointed. The staff is so attentive and friendly, the presentation of the dishes so carefully made and of course the food itself is delightful, so many delicious flavors. The home made bread should have it's own mention as it might be the most tasty, fresh bread I've had on the island, with an unbelievable butter.

My favorite course this month (November 2021 calendar) was the halibut. For dessert, even though I'm normally big into the citrus desserts, their clementine vanilla was heavenly! The beautiful champagne was a surprise gift from a fine gentleman to my friend for her birthday. He called reception and had to explain the situation because he doesn't know me and the table was under my name. Kudos to Natalia, our lovely server who found out about the plot!
Thank you Mr. Fox, for a beautiful evening!ü¶ä‚ù§

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
Make no mistake the food is excellent. The service is ok but they seem to be needing some training. We counted at one time that the waiters 11 times walked by our table, looked at our empty plates and then did not take them. They mostly got frantically removed seconds before the next dish. Not once were the cutlery put down in a proper way. Always very random.
We got the Fine Wines pairing but every single wine came in the same type of glass from the Cava to the Pinot Noir. Simply not good enough given the price.

The atmosphere is also very loud and hectic. Maybe because it was Saturday night however the acoustics were poor. We loved the food but service and atmosphere were lacking. They did cater very well to my wife‚Äôs allergies we just say so I can recommend trying Mr Fox but I think they can improve a lot with few adjustments in the decor and training of staff.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Tried the At Home menu last week and it was absolutely fabulous. Best take home restaurant food we have had. Parmesan agnoloti with beef and an amazing French onion style broth was sublime. The lamb was so tender, nibbles and bread delicious, those olives! I would buy the whipped cep butter if it was sold separately it's so good. Chocolate fondants were perfect and came with cherries and almond custard  Everything was so easy and effortless to prepare. And the quantities were generous. Also came with cheese and pear. Finished off with their own walnut whips. Amazing value and really felt like we were eating in a restaurant. Paired it with a lovely bottle of wine and some cocktails for an extra treat. The staff were lovely and so friendly when I collected our order. Will be making this a regular dinner event. Highly recommend.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: First time visiting and it was an excellent experience, the food was so good! Service was also great. Be prepared to be there for over 2 hours and enjoy every mouthful.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Mr. Fox have been the best choice that I made in long time. There they know how to make you feel good. Nice atmosphere, adorable team, great and professional service and the menu is to die for, beautiful. If you are looking for real gourmet creative and delicious experience, Mr Fox is your place. Do not miss it. We will come back! Thank you.

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Words cannot describe the impeccable experience we went through at this extraordinary establishment! Truly Michelin deserved, the menu is limited but for a reason, each and every dish was flavoured perfectly and prepared to the finest excellence! Service was fantastic and they made sure we were accommodated to whilst providing me and my boyfriend the privacy we‚Äôd liked.

name: Mr Fox
review_text:
That was a first restaurant we went after a long lockdown in Ireland. It was a wonderful experience: all 11 courses from the evening menu were amazingly delicious. The wine selection is also good and pairs well with every dish.
5 out 5: book the table and visit Mr Foxü¶ä. You won't be disappointed üôÇü•Ç

name: Mr Fox
review_text: Lovely place!  Very private and great food!
